user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jaja Lorenzo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDK-T9FfLmZEuW_l049UdwygdppD4IXBm5QI051Dm3EMsHPw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food is good. The place is great. But the service needs improvement. The prices are a bit high but worth it.

We ordered the fried chicken, which was oily in the middle. The waffles that came with it were superb, however--having a buttery and creamy taste.

The garlic steak cubes as a bit salty because the sauce was absorbed by the mushrooms. The meat was tender and well marinated.

We had a hard time finding any waiters even though the place was not full.

The place is spacious and cool. They have a second floor that gives a wide view of the people strolling in the mall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-c48SjBEPr7sArx_nQ9t4Fzbnfm9x8gRTWFRD"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Ianne Buluran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPsnMXsJ-OAu5ZMl4RLmNIVpCaG0R7TtycrRmJCIE0za3O9tQ6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Waffles were very nice but sometimes they can be overcooked and too hard. Almost like a croissant waffle. Salted caramel coffee had a lovely cooked caramel taste and barely avoided being hyper sweet. The open sandwich Benedict is a little too difficult to eat with a butter knife","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq3ozvzqpg0D-SaLRKmV0raGxvHyKBOGJgrBUc"],"When":"2024-5-21"},{"Name":"Gerardine Alcala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWV4Zab0FWpjzo-PZlEbknelARv4oLuN_2gR9rzQ3m3vt8e4Uab=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I had dinner here with my family in celebration of my graduation and we ordered these dishes: Honey BBQ Chicken Salad, Chicken and Waffles in Honey Sriracha sauce, Miso-glazed Salmon with Red Rice, and a slice of Calamansi Pie.

The salad was alright, with the flavors being balanced with the chicken bits being quite crisp but was lacking in meat. My family shared the same sentiments on this.

For our main, I had the chicken and waffles while my family had the miso-glazed salmon. I quite liked my order, especially the crispness of the waffles and how it pairs well with the chicken, although I feel it would have been better to get the original and dip it in the syrup as it is quite sweet and mixing it with the honey sriracha made it much too sweet for me.

As for the salmon, my family enjoyed it but did not feel the same towards the red rice because of the texture - a matter of personal preference.

For dessert, since we were quite full at this point, we shared a slice of calamansi pie. The flavor was just right but I personally would have preferred it to have a slightly stronger calamnsi taste.

All in all, the food is good and so was the service although there were times when the staff had their backs turned to us which made it hard to get their attention.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKCAXQmIG6fN0X_B8_4VpRrK413KY3lCQ7LeJC"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Alwin Goh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMDyffRk8CvIHiZZmx_N7PuODTzwdVI7a6g0Tw4iT57mGxBtg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here is absolutely delicious, especially the sourdough pizza. Don't miss out on the cheesecake—it's a must-try. The restaurant is beautifully decorated, making it perfect for Instagram-worthy photos.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOn4N0zQjvB4AxDMEzREozVzLQ64yqHY3RgcAxB"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Cher Payuyo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpgaQXJ3c5FQ4OwBekJZfdZlzxBudGqnhH3-sYp33Eaa1FwHt0mw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family had a pleasant dining experience. Staff were very courteous, professional, and accommodating. Great food! We ordered the cheese dumpling, Nono's salad, 4-cheese pizza, truffle cream pasta, fried chicken and waffles, and a complimentary strawberry short cake. My fave was the cheese dumpling! Would love to come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_Sjbm8qi-o8HdN8fLfyiHCpx-o7Y3-Jov9AUc"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Eugine Carlo Pascual","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_t4DS1o7HF0-4fKWZH9VfNSMNXAg_F39rrtWHyi0dQd0bRgxn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nono's Restaurant provides a delightful culinary journey that is nothing short of memorable. From the moment you step inside, the warm and inviting ambiance welcomes you, making it suitable for various occasions. Whether it's a casual dinner with friends or a special celebration, Nono's ambiance sets the stage for an enjoyable experience.

One of the restaurant's standout features is its diverse and extensive menu. From classic comfort food to innovative creations, there's something for everyone. The food consistently excels in quality, with each dish prepared with attention to detail and flavor. Whether you're in the mood for a hearty steak, a flavorful pasta, or a fresh salad, Nono's delivers with excellence.

The service at Nono's is attentive and friendly, enhancing the overall dining experience. The staff is knowledgeable about the menu and is always willing to make recommendations or accommodate special requests.

If you're looking for recommendations, don't miss out on Nono's signature dishes – they are a testament to the restaurant's commitment to culinary excellence.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7P9N56Zsv2kwbvt4eh-7y8YLcAiOqYGfBn6Vk"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"Jet Chavz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJlktC0hvlt8yTAb1oeZKHD7M1shAnBeNL3PBZtD07M7QaFCKSXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was so good even my kids love it! One of our new favorites!!! 🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9-sTqksWTc8NYVNOVcba-mCiAYTUOS1KAmjXo"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Pat Ventura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxL_PW3LGdNCwMt8vJVo4LUH4N-ZcEF62LzcKGx05QbsXdJWOB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were pleasantly surprised and truthfully delighted to have stopped by this restaurant while roaming inside Okada Manila.

The items on the menu were comfort food to sum it all up. From the pasta dishes to the breakfast meals and even down to the scrumptious soup and well balanced coffee, everything was delicious.

The pastry scent and the aroma of the coffee is very welcoming which is why there were a lot of customers.

P.S.
Their chocolate cake is the perfect way to end a hearty meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSGOw__-zT9rRqxZtAaNoyYoOLE4kQ4uDlevWn"],"When":"2023-7-2"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Your Local Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTRSOCE9Fue5jq3uIkX1lxZ-I5tymkA_KeH0mRJiZRGM1EWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing service! We dined in one of the private rooms of Yu Lei and experienced such VIP treatment from the staff. The food was perfection, and I tried jellyfish for the first time, which was a unique texture that I enjoyed. Everything we ate was beautifully presented and tasted delicious. We were definitely very full afterwards! If you're looking for a luxury dining experience while visiting Okada Manila, I recommend trying Yu Lei atleast once. 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_lOWlQX_OAHAUwknPD8A-PLE902qSdvgMM_Io"],"When":"2023-10-27"},{"Name":"Michael Ranola","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4-fl3wGuZQRaxCwo5KWee6acqKIkb1Iu7HJh_5TtbiJa7BC3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We met up with a friend from Japan. We had dinner at Yu Lei. We ordered char Siu Pao, Shrimp Dumplings, appetizer sampler, hot & sour soup, sweet and sour pork, and many more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOocwdkWtvJLcRBP96oOebxVbJ86G6E9yFK_1WK"],"When":"2023-5-6"},{"Name":"leo vl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKv-LQl9iljwp23DOT_bIz7A5TjO12T8IPvacYj9XYXyuP7qA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great afternoon tea set! You can choose between 2-tier or 3-tier, depending on how hungry you are. And choose either tea or coffee. It's good enough for two people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP68IrrTRX1aNrtcM1P4coFLEQaryo6k3irTtfW"],"When":"2023-10-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Law","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2Tea3B4k80gZW7RKH3M7Nfp426m49h55nWpNotJOueTaxLdtZMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stunning decor, very friendly staff backed by some of the best Chinese dishes available in town. Would definitely go back when in Manila again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPatjFtXu6TNKMLJ7oT8tb7Li4PhNr5a7PFDpN6"],"When":"2023-2-9"},{"Name":"Mayuyi Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXPUPW_SiNpV_jRnMF3WYvUGh9iGQgFcANA-xei76Hj0HPVo8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty, elegant dishes that aren’t too heavy due to the chef’s restraint, with slight gearing towards Japanese tastebuds.

Modern, dramatic and luxurious Interior design with beautiful details.

Really happy and satisfied.

Great value for money for something that is very comparable to the Michelin star Chinese restaurants in Singapore with fairly large portions. Even came with complimentary appetisers and after-meal snacks.

Highly recommend the seafood dumpling, Yangzhou fried rice, prawn Chee Cheong fun, mixed seafood noodle soup, prawn in chili sauce, kurobuta pork in 3 kinds of vinegar.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Reuben Matthew Estabillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK375xRgNTwua8atjt_RZ45cSAOAYGund5YR7dW7nQGR3g-eA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chinese fare with a bit of a modern twist (ie, barbecued pork lathered with honey) Very good dishes, obviously, coming from a 5-star place, but a bit pricey (Nearly P20k for seven pax) and uh, dare I say I liked the kung pao chicken better at Panda Express!? Lol. The good thing is they don’t use an inordinate amount of MSG compared to others, but the food tends to be a little heavy. We were almost full after the appetizers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peyton Eleazar Bravo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUi6qOMtcVT5SuV3Fw7dIwcAT3maMVqqXZ95FdY3qoOsqk2KdphhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"if you're looking for a luxurious fine dining experience. Yu Lei is the place for you. Upon entering you will walk through a beautiful hallway covered with 10,000 pieces of glasses imported from Czech Republic.

The dishes here are described as Modern Shanghainese originated from the city of shanghai. it integrates light japanese ingredients making the taste subtle yet flavorful.

Okada continues to amaze its visitor on its new restaurants. The concepts are well curated designed to amazed every customer.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ferdinand Mercado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZKWbKcS004J_zHtbb8ycym6HziqKGnkItRmJndz51iLanmA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Servce downgraded needs to call for water refill tea refill unlike before impeccable service no need to call the attention of the waiter/ress they anticipate ur needs seeme like the new ones arent trained as before","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"A VG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8HJaJWgnJYg_VlZAoYkwghk5le4J090nSntEa6pHDvv5ziA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wanted to eat in a restaurant that was not in every other mall so we ended up here in Bistro Charlemagne, an Asian fusion  restaurant. We weren't really expecting much because this branch was particularly hard to find.
The thing is, it had no other opened establishments beside it so it must be serving good food to survive where it is.
We had the beef rending which we all loved. The beef was so soft and flavorful. The prawns with aligue was also so yummy.
We have decided that this bistro is worth a second visit so we can try their other dishes and  for another round of beef rending.
The staff were nice, because we were the only patrons there. We were seated outside because we had a dog. They provided an electric fan for us. Unfortunately, the smell of the outdoors was not pleasant.
Another plus is their bathroom. Very spacious, clean and was kept cool.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSDeCZCRcFmihMVWWa7MJhCBNZhZVhrQXp4b-8"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Normal Panda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAlc18aLtH3SHQPmt782BO6rGI2PENtful_QII9hcbtQQ1OA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Expected more based on favorable reviews. The cheese stuffed tenderloin is what you would expect, with the sauce was sweet. I have mixed feelings with the sisig.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMUpHsffy29692_W4keqC10-q3j1jYvJxYcJM"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Ai Angkiko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnz5luVhh64S6sIO9CetsUYL-RZXc6AsFi1V8EwDlfbkjZjKCy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went here on Labor day at almost dinnertime, the place had a fair amount of people, was clean and spacious, and had their own comfort room. As for the feel and ambience, it was comfortable however it was pretty dim inside because of the lighting, it just feels that the warmth of the light was contrasting too much with the red couches/seats. The staff were accommodating and answered our queries in full.

For the food, I would like to emphasize first that my review of this may be heavily influenced by the imbalance of the types of food we ordered but nonetheless I'm still going to review each dish individually. Our appetizer was the pumpkin soup which was delicious, it had a great consistency as well as good serving size, perfect way to stimulate your appetite without an overpowering taste. The yang chow/fried rice was our favorite here, I feel I could eat this by itself! great ratio of rice and other ingredients. We ordered the Ox Sisig to try something new, it has what I believe are chicharon bulaklak in it, so good but if you're looking for crunchy sisig this is not for you, delicious still. There was also Slow Braised Pork Belly, so tender that it falls apart while trying to grab a serving, there was a strong taste that overpowered the dish itself that I cannot quite point out (tasted kind of and was probably a strong spice) but maybe less of that it could've been really good too, I was expecting something similar to hong shou rou. Lastly, the beef tenderloin rolls with cheese and teriyaki sauce, this made me lose my appetite, the cheese was overkill, couldn't even taste any of the beef, just cheese, it even beats the taste of the teriyaki sauce. In the end, we finished the soup, ox sisig, and fried rice. Some of the servings are worth their price and taste, some aren't. Will still go back because we're hoping to try the other dishes especially the lengua and the crispy pork belly in hoisin glaze.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRO4a4gRa_Xxj7xMKv01QJWGJ1v03fwuAP07JF"],"When":"2024-5-3"},{"Name":"Paris London","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgQC2OJqM6mOQr-guvjkEV8CP0O0nEYwQhpWbN733e33dyp8NE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Mixed  Asian  cuisine presented differently and non-traditionally. Dishes are just 1 size.
(Chinese, Japanese and Vietnamese)
Too oily though and others are over cooked like the Appetizer Bacon with Shrimp 🍤
Standıng Pansit is nicely presented like Instant Pansit Canton taste but with lots of ingredients.
Yang Chow fried Rice is not bad.
Spring Rolls are crunchy.
Lumpia is presented like a plate but taste very Filipino. Too sweet and salty.
Soy Chicken is overwhelming sauced and salty so no need for to e ginger sauce.
Generally ok but not for me to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKVvAOEG8QpUyy8ZFsQotC6aEIEdTRRR4LmOft"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Lian Laguio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnYlMjadudoK5_XLa-C3uwUR_1D2qVF5-uipv9_y9_Fgegncsdfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible food. For its quality and price it's not worth it
I ordered the set meal and was disappointed with the amount and taste, it didn't match the price of the item.

Service was alright.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPxswY5zOp_QAoXw96ek-An6FY2tsjidhTo3_ja"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"Kay.Tolentino Gaspar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqXi8pOJAM0TAeQw8Gg-N5v-EhfeKHTYseAhaIJ6Vmtzju9M5kVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Enjoyed our lunch. The food was good. Friendly staff and quick service. Their set meal for lunch is fine. Will return to try their other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhP-jOmndDvHqsaHfjoIeDyWcMjhV2IiWzR26_"],"When":"2024-2-7"},{"Name":"Jay Bryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0rPRpIAOJHS_0i6TndD6vocyslDwnLAu0UR7SKjkPgr1SJyBF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We enjoyed our dinner last night. We decided to just order their "set meal" as we were kind of full when we got there (late meryenda).

But still, their set meals are worth the price. The Coconut Fish Fillet and Pork Belly with Green Mango Shrimp Rice are delicious! I love how both of the sauces were made, Thick and full of flavor.

Restaurant ambiance is quite great. Staff are attentive and polite.

I'll definitely go back to check the other food in the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN4Mq2gwl5CrQP5R6663M_SlSf_TjtDLa7oAP9"],"When":"2022-6-9"},{"Name":"Laine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKG6ufNbmbe5PMTKeUegcTxJ1p16QjqVyGLwYA4g7XNcXOmdOH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pricey but okay.
Did not expect that the Beef Tendeloin cheese wrap was small. As in a thin slice of beef strip with cheese inside. Naka zoom in ang picture sa menu. Masarap pero mahal. Cheesy baked seafood rice was okay. Ang dami sahog than rice which is good. I think 2 crabsticks, 2 shrimps and several battered squid. Big onion, bellpepper, bean sprouts, mushrooms.
Crispy pork belly in hoisin sauce was not as we expected - dry and a bit bland on its own. Pares rice grabe ang generous ng serving!! Mga 3-4 pax. Malasa and bagay sa mga ulam.
Beef brocolli was good. Malambot yung beef, saucy and generous din yung brocolli pieces.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5XDkd68cG4pum_CzPONyhf24Tc98EIdgsobp7"],"When":"2022-12-25"}]

We frequent this resto and a family fsvorite in the 90's, havent visited the resto for like 20 years or more. I must say this resto lived up to its name with time!

A must dine once in a lifetime.
Food, service, ambiance is what it used to be, perfect for intimate dates or simply a dine out with family. Youll never go wrong with any food you order.

Price of food, quality and serving size are all spot on. Its really where quality meets quantity. Not to mention their superb service!

Will definitely have more of my nostalgia!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnVeITzqZV54VRfaUMInRm1_kocxRZP3Wy8Re_"],"When":"2024-6-24"},{"Name":"Annalyn J Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9bvNxEiKqtiwTGDkwGn2KS0XVEvcUaD5wHZoxDLcOpoDg-2_x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This resto has been in the same spot for the longest time. The cons: they need to renovate, even just a little.
The place needs to be better-smelling
Toilet upstairs is not fit for seniors and the disabled

If you use too much, it might be too spicy for your taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgZT6pnBumRiIewFzjnfcrUJqAD2yCnzUbVyhs"],"When":"2024-2-26"},{"Name":"CARLOS KENNEY","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eiqQ9SQSJzVb0a7l2dXfayYY4mGw3GyPh_fiFELH0wL7rXo92Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you so much to Cassie and Patrick , you guys have been very accommodating and warm. Fresh meat and premium choices for everything! They have great standards from service to food, atmosphere. IT’s best to go there at 8pm to watch the water fountain show in Okada, they have the best location to view it while enjoying your food. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqbhxKprRRgSJKufaWoTOcdTAinG3ZTi07euse"],"When":"2023-12-13"},{"Name":"一个雪","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjgsNE1ncMaVjFcSOHFWyMD9Nxu6tAIYEsTcbRNAAqggPnggU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food is fresh, the service and environment are very good. [{"Name":"Sridhar Kumar Pasupuletti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiGeuSqi1jw8W33PghU4n3f7Fgg8_V9t_XBgTNb05SAkTHBX5baQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Abe's, where good friends dine! Yeah, that tag line is true. Went with my friends and had a good lunch and good time. Tried lots of Filipino food. My friend Cathy explained each and every item which made my experience so good. Thanks, Emily for sponsoring...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG332NKI1L10dJA2S9b7hh1kV5pCFyD0Yt1nQg"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Kay.Tolentino Gaspar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqXi8pOJAM0TAeQw8Gg-N5v-EhfeKHTYseAhaIJ6Vmtzju9M5kVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We definitely had a great time dining at this place. Everything here is good. Friendly staff, great customer service, quick service. This is one of their better branch. The quality and taste of food are very good, from the mains to the desserts. Will surely return to try their other dishes. Popular place for locals and tourists alike.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNy7aqwFnVj_SpovsRzicxkIv6Bj2aT0YVUy_Ie"],"When":"2023-8-1"},{"Name":"Jay Orilla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-Y4iDcTTXGihTAYIYkBc8jKTfULjRmTjJkvoOoN8-nPoPHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic Filipino restaurant. We had our lunch here on a Sunday afternoon and there were few customers. I love Abe's kamaru and hot chocolate but they are not available. The food that we ordered though was on point and tasty, the mutton adobo was soft and flavorful, so was the kare kare. My favorite was the turon. Great customer service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiSBszwYLTy_OvqT0FvY1niHuf_GyYtMZatYP-"],"When":"2023-3-23"},{"Name":"Elaine De Los Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5Oceh75YnVGRGKHRTm7N7y6fuRsGJXBFYBBpj8lJk7verq7ZB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends and I had our afternoon merienda at this place. All the desserts — toffee sans rival, mango canonigo, and sikreto ni Maria — were fantastic! They all paired well with hot coffee. The staff were attentive and the service was fast. They also have a special surprise for those who celebrate their birthday there. The decors and interiors are Filipino-themed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmKowK-Foe6H49SLZfAIXfd0vyzjVwWU--J5wp"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"DanAGo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3hFBUqs507A4LhUADYnDxZYI7iC28xET8ntEmJ3cXJIQooGPyuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Located near the carpark from the Theater side. Its a quiet and cozy restaurant away from the casino and the main hall. It serves local dishes like Kare-kare, crispy pata and yes they have Halo-halo. Service is quite good. Serving size do tend to be a bit smaller and the price point is way much more. Understandlbly its inside a hotel so prices do tend to be higher than their regular store elsewhere. Serving time can take awhile and all our dishes came out in one out instead of one dish at a time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnPbuq_vhCl_gpn8bw1ACHMC_2RIa-B_4kvjCs"],"When":"2023-5-17"},{"Name":"Jeeekob","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCqig0NIzbnXOXHVQzxMhu7vyMF40jpNc3MrJkUH-fPfaqEsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Summary: Rude Customer Service! If you're a Filipino, you might feel like a 2nd class customer/tourist unless your clothes are all gold plated and diamond crusted.

It took us a while for the staff to take our order. After our order was taken, it took more time for our food to be served than other people who came in later than we did. They got their food served first even though they had a larger quantity of food.

The food itself does taste fine but overall, it tastes mid. We ordered the Klassic Kare Kare, Crispy Pata, and some garlic rice.

When we finished our food and asked for our bill, again, other people's bill got taken of first before ours did. When our change was given, the manager(?)/senior staff just slid the bill over to us rudely while I noticed that he gave it politely to the aforementioned people before us. The senior staff that did this was a balding middle aged fat man with glasses. Mind you, we paid our bill in full which was NOT inexpensive.

It is very ironic that a restaurant that serves Filipino food would treat one of their own like this. I fully understand that food service industry is a very demanding job, however we still expect a decent customer service considering the price you are charging your customers with.

For people looking for a place to eat reading this review, you can still eat here but just wear a big diamond necklace so you can expect decent service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeAEumZEi7BSlamGwTtzoGwGFyWVKBbEobiUkY"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Wei Ming Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBXN3k1cRsTUJCHaFtSO-Vy4l5E3ZGC4pDRrlDe0KcnmQf1WQqKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Most delectable local cuisine - it's like granny's home cooked food. There are so many items that are good - bistro filipino, tuna panga sa bawang (tuna chéri), crispy shrimp binondo, sinuteng baby squid...I cannot name all that I love, just be adventurous and try all of them out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8u6RcbxmDZw8hcixqoiV60wNqjjr4hwv1qP-x"],"When":"2019-5-20"},{"Name":"Mark Jubac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjsof3vhckLUrFBUPVnCo_WDO8j4Yca3JGLMmapfmksZMW8-JApw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"3 stars for now. One of the dish we ordered is not available.

I'm not a fan of their version of pork sisig. Too fatty for me and lacks charring.

Saving grace was the sinantol na hipon. It's hard to find Filipino restaurants that serves it.

Will I go back? Yeah, I still would like to try the other dishes before I decide never to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObpoAX3zzJHpBRvqEJKVsT9JaChnUE91y0vbr9"],"When":"2021-11-3"}]

[{"Name":"Daryl Calderon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-wMbaNacQStbOxs_CrPpjqbf30-7HMwXSXvVy7o0Ey_p-d9VX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are regular in this restaurant. This is probably the best korean restaurant around. Service is always good, and the private room is very nice. They can grill for you if needed. Premium beef is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt8S3sHyli3_v29-CdAWyPNDu4eT4HWd1GGKby"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Villamor Lacambra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK9vEUJK5Eouqt1lDoRlVxYVBCOBCTWlnUStzqQ-n4EmWUPLFI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recommended this Kiwa Korean Restaurant to my Japanese guests and i did not disappoint them. 1 of the best korean resto in Metro Manila.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAn9mF4GnSkkHF0pZip1w9_tYwpbljSZ_BT2sq"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Kit Narciso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2W0zPuo8vg7CmLRlaNZFzkM0yK_NJz_D5xIaGz1ZM59GkK0DI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love eating here.. whenever I’m at solareImake it a paint to have a quiet and delicious meal in this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpxqspVLdG6OQO5Qho4rthNb2SH7naMPNznR_3"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"Wendy Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVBbGmzuVhRSqOBIEuDCQ8ae-L3SAjdqhEV1Z3P9Jyj5tZTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best Korean restaurant in Manila! The quality of their dishes is superb, and the attentive waiters excel in explaining the menu. Don't miss out on the fantastic desserts. While it may be on the pricey side, every bite is worth the well-crafted culinary experience. 🇰🇷🍲","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjRQsxah65fnNXWV_XITVkRf7YWrg37mbPdtQK"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"krō waque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0CXU-2TcWcpEILTUa5sUNuiRtKHXNj7JD0u5YrT5i8fYsifbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We walked in for brunch on a Sunday and were seated immediately.

Service in general is professional, almost cold, but not off-putting. Jill was helpful.

Wooden interiors provide an ample amount of warmth. The tall glass walls allow a good amount of sunlight in while you get a view of what remains of Manila Bay when you look out.

Freshness of ingredients is extraordinary, the absolute highlight of our dining experience.

Every dish we ordered, from mains to accompanying banchan, was excellent, and seasoned right. No spice or seasoning overwhelmed the natural flavors of the meats and the greens.

Spicy fried chicken was fresh foremost, plump and juicy.

Marinated beef ribs, although tender, retained enough pleasant chew to it, and were fresh.

The fried mackerel was a little downer, as although prepared well, it tasted almost either salt-cured or dried.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO_no1wJwce1n8_aRMfbjhnaXyWWTJWsk3_rQf"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Aritzia V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVt62u7H8tmeMJqXmr0s-OWZimFp_uZbCE7_4TKpY7aNquBbtY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The other reviews are right -- the food is too mediocre but very expensive And they only serve you 4 side dishes. Service is so painfully slow and there were only 4 occupied tables in the entire restaurant. It's hard to call the attention of the servers and you need to keep reminding them of your requests because they keep on forgetting. So much so that we skipped ordering dessert because we figured it would take another 30 mins. It's a shame because this is the only restaurant open for early lunch if you are going to catch the matinee show in the theater. Better to just eat the sandwiches and salad at the theater kiosk instead. The restaurants beside it (Yakumi, Finestra, etc) are so much more worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7FNRVjoUvQAkBbFQECkBd6hCWbujxzrtwNqPT"],"When":"2023-9-24"},{"Name":"Rebecca Sy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh38bsMTJZCYQssOy3D1NXbtrxrRPrCW0UKuXhUMD3vQ1RLmaJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has a very nice view, overlooking the sea. They also have private rooms for groups or something intimate. What I like about here is the ambiance, the service, and most especially the food. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMF1_QXzQkuwnI2eN6tmTbOlQmkfgzoaCPQMTb"],"When":"2023-6-19"},{"Name":"Dave Arreglado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqxZA7EJGP3FpAMkWK0uY796ZRmxviVRfHCm-Ql3ma_CEXZejlLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food! Great ambiance","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaWC9j_HL2pfeYV3xp3eR6OusFK7HXRkwYbFNg"],"When":"2024-10-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tyron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6dnW0GeU166heI-FqlY7v1OWlpTOlVfOiWAr2ONnT7UHaYJNo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful authentic Filipino restaurant, this place personifies Intramuros.
The service and the food are both convincing. The price-performance ratio is spot on, and the location is perfect. We ordered many appetizers as we were not really hungry. Since the food was convincing, we ordered a main course as well, which also impressed us.
I highly recommend this restaurant if you want a time travel experience to the past because of the beautiful ambiance. I also find the musicians who entertain the guests very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnwTXnlW1GZF04lhCbOOx20y2q9orW9U1-O5pe"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Franchesca Brianna De Guzman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpUvquTsPHB9qftbH7Sk-DAmAxaaDSw0eNcQ1d5eCllZZRPrWm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried the lunch buffet at this restaurant, and overall, it was a pleasant experience. The ambiance is charming, with its well-preserved old facade that really reflects the rich Filipino heritage. It’s a lovely setting that adds to the dining experience.

However, parking can be a bit tricky; it’s definitely easier if you have a driver. Also, I suggest arriving early for the lunch buffet to ensure the food is served hot, as some dishes tend to cool down over time. Despite these minor challenges, the quality of the food and the atmosphere make it a worthwhile visit. I look forward to returning with my balikbayan relatives in the near future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9Pu2XQOVjr4KODLxoWLr5GLDdEGLaNGuiN50H"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Johnson Badawi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0AQTZGLXL6lUa5n9gWhIM4a0GNfBW6b--zimKB83_28w2QB8Waw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Barbara’s is really a wonderful restaurant, especially for balikbayans who missed a taste of home and foreigners who want to enjoy a fancy Filipino meal. The later was the case when I visited the restaurant—I was with two foreigners. They appreciated the place and food. We had the buffet option, which I thought was not bad. Lastly, the performance was incredible.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORNdW81E3dqW-MCLyPw__ERw984R509YjJgY9v"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Huong Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvIAb5Dk8fN8hFefDXf8n80U2X5ND1gZQWrqlP31uFPMhfmiRX7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very polite service, even with wheelchair.
Beautiful resto in a beautiful house.
Love the pork sisig, even amazing than abodo. The belly pork in abodo has some smell of not good preparation","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTXPrIWjETTPb8VgBX_d1YdSAyLzn_AhAaghq9"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Mimi Leon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfJUkxIu3gTHdSVe-XbwvhcvOQtLJNSFKiFrYSdH19KIvJHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently visited Barbara's Heritage Restaurant and tried their buffet lunch, priced at ₱1200 per person (drinks not included). The ambiance is undeniably charming, with a beautiful Spanish-inspired setting that transports you to a different time. It's a great place if you're looking to soak in the atmosphere.

However, the food selection was quite limited, offering a mix of basic Filipino and Spanish dishes like paella, fried spring rolls, pinapaitan, beef kaldereta ,kare kare, fried chicken, lechon paksiw, pancit malabon, some kakanin, and fruits. Unfortunately, the taste was nothing out of the ordinary—just your typical, everyday flavors. While the dishes were decent, they didn't particularly stand out.

If you're heading here, you're mainly paying for the ambiance rather than the food experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4OcW0OAOwxbdZk1Pji1-5lepX28DtJ8_9mB3O"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Judith Correa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrkp6oBrreTJNKomnXN33vwszVmlllndPhlEXBRoeFhRRVC8s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First timer here and I'm glad I had dinner at Barbara's on my first day in Manila. The cultural show (think musicians and dance performancea) was the absolute highlight. It was truly special. As a filipina-american born in the USA, I felt proud to be a Filipina. I got emotional watching it. You're allowed to take pics and video of the performances. After the show, they invite guests on the dance floor/stage to learn tinikling with the guidance of a professional dance partner. Tinikling is a traditional Filipino dance involving bamboo stilts. I did it, it's fun! Then you can take a group pic with the dancers later. No additional fee, but they lay a hat on the ground if you want to leave a tip. They aren't pushy about it. The hostess also made other special announcements to recognize birthdays and foreign travelers visiting the Philippines for the first time.

We did the dinner buffet and called ahead earlier in the day to make a reservation for two. I'm glad that we did.  I was concerned there wouldn't be any food left since we arrived at 7:07pm (buffet started at 630p). There was a good amount of food left, room temperature as other reviews mentioned. Some food items were refilled. The leche flan was long gone lol. Drinks were additional. I ordered the calamansi juice and if had a flowery taste one that I'm not used to, but if was still drinkable. My husband ordered soursop juice. Total cost for buffet dinner + 2 drinks was  3,500 PHP or $62 USD. Worth it for the show imo.

Also, plan for traffic. I stayed in Makati about 3 miles away and our Grab ride took 45 minutes. Thankfully, the show started around 7:20 pm and lasted an hour. We found a Grab driver easily after dinner. If you have a long wait before your driver arrives, walk around the corner to take pics in the small beautiful courtyard next to the restaurant. Mabuhay!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7jyb2o_cr7wJ2JWt62inZSNjlHskvUuo3HQQ"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Hungry JJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYKdcT3J0tg41EMyN_9lj0YhDIz3p3d4tXqIlf37iJNd3vYaeG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went for a buffet.

Roast beef & mashed potatoes — The roast beef was rather tough and difficult to chew—but if you get a thinner cut it is nice and chewable. The mashed potatoes and nice and creamy!
Barbecue chicken — Get anything but the breast parts. This ensures that your chicken has the best taste-to-food ratio.
Rice — Lacks the rice flavor you’d expect.
Kare-kare — Rather sweet but flavor is not too bad
Lechon Kawali - Rather tough
Pilipit with Coco Jam — Very nice, the Pilipit has a bit of a chew to it and complements the jam very well
Assorted Pastries (Eclair and Cream Puff) — run of the mill, nothing too special
Coffee Jello — Rather nice with a good coffee flavor
Palitaw rice cakes — Tastes nice
Salad — The salads were pretty nice.
Papaitan — Yummy, with a rich flavor.

Overall: Food is rather okay, nothing too special which is a shame considering that hearty Filipino food is not too difficult to make and serve. The inclusion of the French pastries is quite strange considering that they’re not very good. Roast beef could use some work, it is quite tough

Ambience: Very good. The restaurant is set inside a traditional Filipino bahay-na-bato house and in general feels very Filipino. There is a live band performing along with a dance performance which really ups the ambience factor. The food was okay but the ambience was bliss! Keep in mind the performers are a little loud so if you’re fussy about loud noises maybe skip this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM85BKSoGqPo5Zq726xbYGR87do56uPHfKvXFn-"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Jay Sevilla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUd5M-KFHE1nu29Lg-vOwsOXNy5VUeN_1BcRs-C2OPsHXqDlJk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Barbara's in Intramuros offers a dining experience steeped in history and charm. As you step inside, the building, furniture, and decorations immediately transport you back to Manila's colonial period. The path to the toilets even evokes a feeling that a ghost might suddenly appear, thanks to its authentically antique feel.

The restaurant's ambiance perfectly complements the overall historical vibe of Intramuros. The food selection is commendable, with the dishes we tried being genuinely delightful. The desserts stood out the most: the brazo de Mercedes and Halo Halo provided a sweet and refreshing end to a hot afternoon of exploring Intramuros. Barbara's is a must-visit for anyone looking to enjoy good food in a setting rich with heritage.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmpticLXvgmdo884riC-C86ExcfZuvLm7F1Ef2"],"When":"2024-7-9"}]

[{"Name":"Wendy Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVBbGmzuVhRSqOBIEuDCQ8ae-L3SAjdqhEV1Z3P9Jyj5tZTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall, a great experience at the steakhouse with excellent service. The house bread paired wonderfully with the balsamic vinegar. However, the risotto fell short, resembling spaghetti more than expected. On a positive note, the Caesar salad greens were delightfully crispy, and the complementary chocolate was a sweet ending to the meal. 🥩🍞🥗🍫","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2Q_tttnYh_MCVkTl99vi0TBqorcodiwWBIpHm"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"RA O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrELVjFvK-qrZ4ZJxj8SjkX2OsgK5de4dQNmuQabgn6FKLcS6S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Finestra used to be 5 star to me. But now service has declined, orders are mixed up and at worst forgotten. Food is still 5 star, fesh seafoods, and good quality meat. That said, I try to over look though the limited amount of ribeye steaks as they ran out when I asked for some more.The quality of the sparkling wines and red wines have gone down. They had better selections before.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlpXFuDFjB9SvEm0VCG85uslUHDznCxzH6ZEcZ"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Ly Da","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWekcM_0lamk_8BI4aIDqN1kdTSyJ7VCjX_whzcqe_e0Td5lJg7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant has class from the moment you enter, it's cozy and offers a good view of their Chefs busily working in the kitchen. The atmosphere is cozy, warm chandeliers, cushiony semi circular seats for more intimate gatherings. Food is great by the way. The service was par excellence and quite impressive too. Good job to our server Raphael!

We enjoyed the surprise birthday cake and the treats as we billed out. 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpl8XCyjEtuX1SBbZXSrcgkGtPP8Z3y9V3WVsb"],"When":"2023-2-28"},{"Name":"Sheena Yap Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYYAQUlqYzoVTqNQLY10OLSNHgT2j09z1Ws2_xysbPowdgVs3Nyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ok this place is so pretty and the open kitchen is to die for.  They give a basket of bread that’s freshly baked and must have to eat.  I had the mushroom pizza which was also good.  They also have an amuse bouche to start with.

The highlight of my experience of this restaurant is the tiramisu.  They prepare it right at your table and it was sooo good.  I doidnt realize they also give you 2 free chocolates to choose from their box.

Service was great! Definitely a nice place but make sure to bring your wallet cus it can get pricey!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwlZfBAKJgnnjlEGFcaKuGjD0DlvFS4KbKbV6f"],"When":"2024-2-14"},{"Name":"Dimitri Sterlin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlM0vq7uEtYfsA8P3gRpTwzHKXPFtNE6WhRN_6X0MZPUTIPJfT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friend brought me to this fancy restaurant for a date. It was pricey but I guess this was ok due to the type of restaurant it was.
I'll still recommend it to try it once","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"A. P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX83rvzpZe_l0oYNcGn5nCM6lxCWERWdGhTQkp_SwzF2FU8aU46=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My fiancé and I visited from Australia and thank goodness - we chose to indulge here over Spiral Buffet: IT WAS PHENOMENAL! user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Marianne Esguerra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXelBfqOVZAC2a3qv99_Nxvjpz4ywmWldIB97qvkgZAhJDJ5ku-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"To be honest, I expected more. For the original price of 1,998 (999 if you used a voucher) you'd expect a lot of dishes - sashimi for example, and a more diverse selection but the selection was like less than 25-30 dishes in total.

Service was great, no doubt. The servers were really attentive and fast so 5/5 for them.

For the atmosphere and ambience, also 5/5 because the place was clean and aesthetic.

But for the food, I'm sorry but I can only give 2/5 stars. I didn't get my money's worth. The selection was too small. Food itself didn't taste like "wow this is amazing" and it's more like "oh okay". I was really sad there was no sashimi and not much food to choose from. The only dish I liked was the pasta that was prepared to your preference. Crepe was -1/5 :(

All in all, would I come back? Definitely no, but it's still worth the experience. We were disappointed though because we celebrated our 3rd anniversary here, should've chosen a different restaurant/buffet instead.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIcQDGQPAEDz7QmK3A9t9B-la0RTZRoPH-Mybu"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Chanelle D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCEGtGi_rnAXcez2UGfi8tPvkrtnC3uoCyaDz_NpX-tJAfWp2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great selection of western and filipino food. We ordered a la carte. The clubhouse was excellent. Good portion size and the sauce was delicious. The fries were perfectly done and the price overall was of good value. I love that they had a selection of cocktails that were fairly priced. They also host a buffet but we just couldn't eat enough to really get the value. They don't skimp on the alcohol. It was actually one of the few places that do not dilute the liquor and you get your money's worth. The atmosphere is comfortable, clean and modern. There is ample seating and service is prompt. Overall a great experience and would love to try their buffet one day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCxM5KEeGjOrKMsAW4Ag9-DtAZXnLerWxSk2Yd"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Angela Harder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2Kv-IPO6glfqAaMCpkWckodPjYX0m1sr9KVXmT-Wko9Bv_3SV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food and service in Riviera exceeded our expectations. We had a great experience because of their excellent service and quality food. Facilities of the restaurant are well maintained and clean as well. Big shout out to Sir Ri Arr for attending to our needs from time to time - he's very attentive and kind! Would definitely recommend this place to family and friends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maria Aquino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ4A5a2KBXIAVL8LUqmfkWiK7LaFE0pLrooJvb454iKvDrYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family had a great time and food at Riviera Cafe. Staff are very professional and helpful. Big thanks to the whole team Tess, Roel, Bummy, Alyssa, Chloie, Geraldine, Manny and Rimar for happily serving and ensuring all guests are having a great experience.

Personally, i loved how they accommodated our big group 18 pax last minute. It was a dispedida of my husband before his flight, his first time to meet my family. The team welcomed us when no other restaurants in the area would.

To the team, thank you very much.

Other than the wide spread of tasty foods, you are truly amazing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alya Arafa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKbCxP2uRGcpeuAHI0ydI2__Gk0l2OOmjSdbZyV7RJhJq9hOg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Riviera Restaurant is a family must go buffet. Affordable price with exemplary staff. To the team Tess, Roel, Bunny, Alyssa, Chloie, Geraldine, Manny and Rimar...big thank you for giving customers great experience.

The food tastes great with alot of choices from local to international dishes.

Will surely be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lourdes Gargoles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpAvrUEDzdb0grVh6Wod6oAhcE-_iFqheUr01bYJnzmwEP7Ikk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you so much Heritage hotel,for the wonderful staycation there with my family for 1 day. All the amenities,food,service and the atmosphere are well one of the finest. I recommended it for those who wish to have their staycation and put some memories with their families there...It's one of the best!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaoz5HYG44yJlJbOcgFQURcXn_-YonvCNIdOd2"],"When":"2023-12-31"},{"Name":"た","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsghFLyWek2ccGeKUfxmdkU9hjWMhRNegIEGXcMdeHqEV0UVI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The breakfast menu is a little on the light side. I would like to have a menu with more meat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdplfo6rP8edKiGwHUXQnGxlwhmoai67S-7ftB"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Patrick F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhwoM-rJ_GpCuxzyovGsjhDYLVyhiTUIhXKUpAe2LEljDoEuJAIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The restaurant is located in the hotel. We ordered chicken curry and beef burger which were average. Beef was really good and medium as wished. Chicken curry was pretty small and had only one potato.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Your Local Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTRSOCE9Fue5jq3uIkX1lxZ-I5tymkA_KeH0mRJiZRGM1EWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing service! We dined in one of the private rooms of Yu Lei and experienced such VIP treatment from the staff. The food was perfection, and I tried jellyfish for the first time, which was a unique texture that I enjoyed. Everything we ate was beautifully presented and tasted delicious. We were definitely very full afterwards! If you're looking for a luxury dining experience while visiting Okada Manila, I recommend trying Yu Lei atleast once. 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_lOWlQX_OAHAUwknPD8A-PLE902qSdvgMM_Io"],"When":"2023-10-27"},{"Name":"Michael Ranola","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4-fl3wGuZQRaxCwo5KWee6acqKIkb1Iu7HJh_5TtbiJa7BC3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We met up with a friend from Japan. We had dinner at Yu Lei. We ordered char Siu Pao, Shrimp Dumplings, appetizer sampler, hot & sour soup, sweet and sour pork, and many more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOocwdkWtvJLcRBP96oOebxVbJ86G6E9yFK_1WK"],"When":"2023-5-6"},{"Name":"leo vl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKv-LQl9iljwp23DOT_bIz7A5TjO12T8IPvacYj9XYXyuP7qA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great afternoon tea set! You can choose between 2-tier or 3-tier, depending on how hungry you are. And choose either tea or coffee. It's good enough for two people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP68IrrTRX1aNrtcM1P4coFLEQaryo6k3irTtfW"],"When":"2023-10-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Law","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2Tea3B4k80gZW7RKH3M7Nfp426m49h55nWpNotJOueTaxLdtZMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stunning decor, very friendly staff backed by some of the best Chinese dishes available in town. Would definitely go back when in Manila again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPatjFtXu6TNKMLJ7oT8tb7Li4PhNr5a7PFDpN6"],"When":"2023-2-9"},{"Name":"Mayuyi Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXPUPW_SiNpV_jRnMF3WYvUGh9iGQgFcANA-xei76Hj0HPVo8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty, elegant dishes that aren’t too heavy due to the chef’s restraint, with slight gearing towards Japanese tastebuds.

Modern, dramatic and luxurious Interior design with beautiful details.

Really happy and satisfied.

Great value for money for something that is very comparable to the Michelin star Chinese restaurants in Singapore with fairly large portions. Even came with complimentary appetisers and after-meal snacks.

Highly recommend the seafood dumpling, Yangzhou fried rice, prawn Chee Cheong fun, mixed seafood noodle soup, prawn in chili sauce, kurobuta pork in 3 kinds of vinegar.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Reuben Matthew Estabillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK375xRgNTwua8atjt_RZ45cSAOAYGund5YR7dW7nQGR3g-eA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chinese fare with a bit of a modern twist (ie, barbecued pork lathered with honey) Very good dishes, obviously, coming from a 5-star place, but a bit pricey (Nearly P20k for seven pax) and uh, dare I say I liked the kung pao chicken better at Panda Express!? Lol. The good thing is they don’t use an inordinate amount of MSG compared to others, but the food tends to be a little heavy. We were almost full after the appetizers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peyton Eleazar Bravo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUi6qOMtcVT5SuV3Fw7dIwcAT3maMVqqXZ95FdY3qoOsqk2KdphhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"if you're looking for a luxurious fine dining experience. Yu Lei is the place for you. Upon entering you will walk through a beautiful hallway covered with 10,000 pieces of glasses imported from Czech Republic.

The dishes here are described as Modern Shanghainese originated from the city of shanghai. it integrates light japanese ingredients making the taste subtle yet flavorful.

Okada continues to amaze its visitor on its new restaurants. The concepts are well curated designed to amazed every customer.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ferdinand Mercado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKZKWbKcS004J_zHtbb8ycym6HziqKGnkItRmJndz51iLanmA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Servce downgraded needs to call for water refill tea refill unlike before impeccable service no need to call the attention of the waiter/ress they anticipate ur needs seeme like the new ones arent trained as before","Images":null,"When":""}]

We will definitely visit again next time and try their other dishes like kikiam and duck soup.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiVcjSWAfes1Nq0tTkXi1jQSuVPX4qlGR4Wg8b"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Chirag Rao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVA_Ntfl9hOAgWs9I2lgMMNWC9uGs4ahPNfJ-2ccD-FR1TQrzg0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It’s one of the oldest restaurant in Chinatown Manila.
We went there for brunch and I really enjoyed their fried chicken as it was perfectly seasoned & crispy.
We also ordered oyster pancake however it was very slimy & didn’t like the texture probably it’s not for my palate.
We also tired there wonton dumpling with wheat noddle which were bland in taste but after adding some sauce was fine .
Would recommend this place for its Fried 🍗","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNARC9SEpF3j9lcSF-Iskrn11SI5h7LYMzSOBu5"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Abi Aguilar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5FowOnIl6MxvOudhiVrh6I8KkxlLpzrRLr8s5BgEoUL94ORXI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Did not disappoint. Food was amazing. My fave was their fried chicken.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhCWcrmU3MMWResV0exvU-_QfY-KC1Avm2IOPO"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"MJ Joson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzi-2uSZGFW0DUMgxD-7S6fGl_fv5GBpsONgcER84JfMJm0Ocm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food was okay considering the mid range pricing. Situated along the street of binondo.
There was no long queue when I went here but seems like during regular days there is a considerable waiting period.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUyHb2f2cH_KhE8U5AdA1ZvO7cQSVIQxTHYzXg"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Jimbo N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJznWX0ZgxRWEaTHgT1kQk7bctcl5C36fsGF6yxeEG2JPz1ng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I hate to give bad reviews but people needs to know. I ordered oyster omelette and Kikiam which is their house signature dishes. The kikian was too oily and should have slice it as seen in their promo. The OO was a disaster! They didn’t put potato starch to make it gooey like the tradition dish. I heard it’s under new ownership. I hope they can take this review and improve it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjFleQ3MW8u-Rt8TGUwwDEN-Eb4ME2I_0LQtzM"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"Gamz Ros","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBYxcM18QKUqyY9gHbXUahdTq2e3HiP0_aChKzr7lxesWy31b6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Old establishment whose famous throughout the time. Theres a lot of pictures of former customers who are famous people along the walls. The atmosphere really reminds you of the old times with the narrow dining area, the multiple dining floors, and confusing pathways to get to the other floors. Service wise, it does get pretty busy on weekends, especially on holidays, so it might take a while for someone to accommodate u. Food is okay, considering they have been using the same traditional recipe since the old times. We ordered the fried chicken and the fried oyster, which is their specialty. Its not too surprising, but it does have a particular taste that will make u remember this place. Good place to try for the experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUyyFailxIbH0_IHQF22McofGOZPX7E6IiWb-W"],"When":"2024-3-10"},{"Name":"Kris Diane Dayao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaIpz84Uk4Qvx3BDBbY9POISciLxJRxyZ6L6-_URvNjp_czHPy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Arrived 12:30 pm and we’re seated at 3rd level. Food arrived around 30mins. Serving was good. The chicken is awesome.
We were full","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0CwZG0q2dRn69jOFB252oVZdJcnCzDMooRqxT"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Mica Villas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKE3u6ZxGERB48fQ3yCYi_QK-BSgttW_WLigfo2Rf3pKQr3MpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have a new favorite restaurant! Will definitely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlZfAxPZcTQh6n0A5BmtsvGUTJK6TOIL2qDp8L"],"When":"2024-8-10"}]

[{"Name":"Sabian Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn58Ggex0bx5qM8EcHivp6FANQLLNVglYgh_UycPCxWiyoYawU5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A bit pricey for its taste. The dimsum are average at best, siomai and hakaw are a bit underwhelming. The mains are good, especially the prawn salad, and orange chicken. The service is excellent, and the staff are very professional. Overall, needs improvement on dimsum especially if you're marketing the place as a dimsum buffet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMauo6gGPvEjRvN-D41fLJ-NgcTB3KGmcez3jCV"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Madam Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW64SC3kLlBuBizDPmhPox1sp4ERnedDq7rxITlGiUovyYR0ro=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Celebrated birthday here good food and ambiance. All servers are attentive and fast service. Ordered the lunch dimsum buffet so good. I will be back and recommend to my family and friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKAHGSXZ91KTR1tUx1dozWBdkkHF0GUazCl04Y"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Alexander Torrijos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVW79XIdOfr-ZYzjvgfGAMHemcJqYYq5UnnEQ8NnXr1M-av-5_C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Lapu-lapu soup was quite good. Very good food. Seafood Buffet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMY5yO2Gp7Z42KYNTNb10T8XM0aVpy8albp_0mM"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Stephany Malapit","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXN0eaeEXzWNzuqKEXPo72GMhmiB10SkTHxra-hl6EUtGLjII-j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had such a wonderful lunch at Red Lantern in Solaire for my Birthday.
We booked a table for 2 and availed the Dimsum Lunch Buffet. This buffet is different as you have to order the dishes you prefer. Choices varies from Appetizers, Soups, Dimsums, Main Dishes and Desserts.
Price per person is 1,188 excluding taxes and service charge. Buffet time is 11:30 to 2:30PM
All the food we ordered were excellent but my favorite has to be the folloqing: Spicy Stir fry Angus Beef with Aspargus, Seaweed Soup, Deep Fried Taro Ball, Prawn Salad and Mango Sago.
I was also pleasantly surprised when the staff brought a heavenly Chocolate Mousse Cake with candles compliment of Red Lantern. The cake was heavenly!!!
Hot Tea and water were also served.
Service was also excellent especially Gerry who made sure that we were sufficiently fed and not lacking in anything during our meal.
I will definitely recommend this place if you are celebrating special occasion but make sure to book ahead as the place tends to get full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNE4Y0AGNCnZ3rLWT58nFKJVdCOzDy81iVWf6gM"],"When":"2022-11-11"},{"Name":"David Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9ybS23zKx63hZLus-ZlF-LwNcBTh5FMLZjvxwLny9DVCW0ZE6Iw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Elegant, exquisite, elevated. Red Lantern's dim sum buffet takes Chinese food to a higher-end level to match its higher-end prices. Would have liked more dim sum offerings in a dim sum buffet, but the rest of the menu has enough variety to keep things interesting. Service is efficient and professional, place is beautiful. A definite treat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMbQc_5GFhdO0DVLd8Lq8alMG5SCjjZAC4aRBt"],"When":"2023-3-22"},{"Name":"Steven Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkVekOXgV6D3HpGvYxPSDG9Crpy2XDSI8nRPPWw4FiNfbxYPQ_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We first came here nearly 2 years ago and was impressed with their food and customer service and couldn't wait to return. Unfortunately i cannot say the same for our return trip. The food is still good but sad to say the customer service had somewhat deteriorated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVjWcUTlqPdENA1c4XFtrV3WjbuURLTQwETB_6"],"When":"2023-4-19"},{"Name":"theo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtVAtSbwv3ppcxm3qQBH5T_bN0hXJhXveB36FQ8goQcwEAog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Favorite foods among all of them is the beef and salted egg prawns!

Excellent service, we are allowed to bring birthday cake, but not allow to eat outsider food.

I came again for the second time, for buffet all you can eat dimsum ₱1500/ person. They gave us a paper and tick it what we want to order. The food was amazing taste and worth it. Unfortunately, the service in this time is super slow & we waiting for quite some time for food coming (like 30min until the food coming) & we are follow up for a few times. Hopefully, they maintain the services better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUHfdvzxndGI11C7TelcajK6YSKF45qYa_ScaE"],"When":"2022-5-26"},{"Name":"Rymnd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXU97ictWkzFqyZRkyA4bDssJbDX5-WqlswJqucKhBFFqPXaJSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best dining experience. Food is quality. Service is outstanding. Vicky and her team are very professional. Vicky is always checking our table if we need anything else. She speaks Chinese and English. No Tagalog. Beverage is not included. 200.89 for a can of coke. You can have free hot Oolong tea. I love all the food.   The chicken feet, crispy fried prawn with mixed fruits is excellent👏👏👏. Chilled mango sago with pomelo is amazing ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐. Thai-style bean curd so so masarap. I love the steamed seaweed roll. I love the ambiance. I like the dining set-up and luxurious atmosphere. If they see you with your handbags or big bag, they will provide you a bin where you can safely put all your belongings! Amazing!

Parking is free. Plenty of parking space.

Highly recommended ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Amount: 1688+++ per person
Date: lunch (11:00 to 2:30pm)
With reservation.
Mode of payment: Credit card
Last call for order 2:00pm","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-o7UdF-iAEAIC7P_-dXWbrXqAtkXH5QMfhCdH"],"When":"2023-8-13"}]

[{"Name":"Angelica “Sylvie” Bertis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMfOSJnQW6XBySxzmlgQdToP4eFCXcvBT_RKI43cRFFTh8-C-2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I was able to visit this nice place. We actually thought that it was a mediocre local cafe, but it turned out to be a fine dining restaurant. Wasn't ready enough when we dined here.

The aircon was pretty blasty, I don't really like how cold it was inside.

Food was nice, the pasta that we ordered had a lot of servings. Did not expect that, the sisig though was kind of overpriced for its small serving size.

The cheesecake has a nice plating, but the taste is okay. Not really my cup of tea.

We weren't able to dine again yesterday due to its private event, but I would like to go there some time if I was able to visit Manila again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPboZz2nR0gwQbq0X3yW-On7RqwJU3XEyo305it"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Jenny Gomez-Aragon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBohoNeRTxg1vELvK1Vd9-zcvsa73Q7qNRVmriFLR-RvyEJPs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fun-filled Meet and Eat with my RareJob coworkers. A mouthful event, yummy food, rustic place and a 4-hour event with full of laughter made my day🥰 5⭐ for the POTATO GRATIN👏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhrBMZICbmVxDDuETltjP08CMKJ3yzclzGwdFr"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"valentina gonzalez torres","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1XQO1XsB0OFrQHaUEJv3-V1gNAj-OYXrykEkbX3Smwe-r_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We enjoyed our experience at this place so much that we decided to come back for dinner. The service was outstanding, with a lovely decor and music. The food deserves a 10/10, delicious with excellent presentation. We also tried the coffee and churros, both very tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsS8uWD8jcF2XqxutT8c2nO8IuEnpYa6rBNNh7"],"When":"2024-1-20"},{"Name":"Ykla Sea","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIalGNc_FrJaNT2_iLItJosHk6pvBO4TebINyqdGVaN0vRmhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Very cozy place with excellent customer service. Staff is really kind and accommodating. We even received some complimentary nachos. The cheese they made for it was good.
The mango shake was sweet even without sugar which is just the way I like it.
The paella we had was so-so. They didn’t have the one with squid ink.

Update: I went there a second time and the waiter/waitress kept going back to me to tell me that what I wanted was unavailable.
Guess a lot of what’s in the menu is unavailable and they don’t bother to update or change it.
Carbonara was so-so and overpriced imo

First experience was great. Second experience was not so great","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3gM8ptgVxhCNV80ElA3KSraMrgI4u4IWUTjAI"],"When":"2023-3-6"},{"Name":"Derrick Pizarro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjG8yAJCBe1CpP3slX-GiZ7bXuNeLsLkGzDSlMMnSk9kYLOqg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place serves good food and the ambiance is perfect for dates and simple gatherings. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jereth Tolentino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiSdU2nDCmECCZpdjPotOox9RsbCu24D5Q0QP2qYTIDf-SZb6Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Before immigrating to the US in the early 90s, I had very fond memories of The Aristocrat Restaurant. My dad would take us there on the weekends, creating cherished family moments.

After flying back to the Philippines after 30 years, the first place I decided to eat was The Aristocrat Restaurant, at the same location my dad used to take us. It's not the fanciest place, but it holds special memories for me.

The food is still as delicious as I remember. After 30 years, it definitely didn’t disappoint. I noticed that the restaurant is currently undergoing renovation, which is a positive sign. I'm glad to see this, as I hope this beloved establishment continues to thrive for many more years.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgzJqTnCIkMUtRxFqtoF5_xcy1pDRwdKIGs65B"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Dave Fulton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXajgjuFS-f8V0PRp1Eq6dgVkxLArIPJrzW8YhP0ZWf88Top4E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After working 'in country' for 18 years, this was my first visit. I told my driver to take us to a competitor's establishment just down the road from here and he said you really need to try Aristocrats. I know now, I should have made it a point to dine here many years ago. All our entrées were tasted exceptional and the service was very friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrZn3zFjyk1RTG81Nvlbg-P3WA5MNRfZ441Nd0"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"Off Duty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOe9GaQ7uzML_gLc7dExXXV8Nz9Isy_WJycyMNbJDzmyW_ZQ0b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoy traditional Filipino food served just as Aling Asiang did back in 1939.

The place was bustling when we got there.  We waited under 7 minutes just to be seated.   It is currently undergoing expansion-renovation.

Once we were led to our tables, we placed our order for the Aristo Feast Set 2 priced at ₱2,471 which includes Chicken Honey with atsara, Bistek Tagalog, Sinigang ng Tyan ng Bangus, Pancit Guisado, a bowl of rice and Pepsi Cola.

Our orders was served under 15minutes which is fast considering the place is swarmed by guests.
Wait staffs are efficient and courteuos.
Table is clean, utensils are spotless.
Comfort room is neat.
side note:  Am not a fan of their atsara.  It is too sweet and the taste is complicated.
Over all dining experience meets our expectations.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkp5FWP8BPv6G6I-sJFVQrulK0P2ySQV95kWmw"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Richard A Francisco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKB3RUhFLtt7ImosmwoSu6nunMGPyPyAxwHXozmwk8SfivDzjhcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a classic Filipino restaurant with plenty of history. Locals come here to celebrate special events and milestones like weddings, graduation, birthdays and more. They are famous for their barbeque chicken which can be boneless or with the bone in. They also have fried noodle dishes, stews, and so much more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMInjH3EwUq5djWG49l6jYpKXI9tb-N84Fd94SO"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Marie C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkrPrfE13_l7nuxgKNkUjhIfGIRj9hsLeFIAy0v80c1w_0Cg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had been looking forward to eating here after having been away from the Philippines for so long.

The place had been spruced up and it’s all air conditioned now. Tip - the inner sanction (near the toilets) is still the coldest place.

The sotanghon soup, pancit canton, chicken pork adobo, flying saucer adobo sandwich were still very good. But their best selling chicken and pork barbecue with java rice were disappointing - chicken and pork were almost indistinguishable, no umami. Even the sauce was not as it was😞

Gulaman sago very good. Halo halo not bad. Macapundo pandan was just sweetened macapuno strings with pandan jello cubes on top of ice cream - mediocre in my opinion.

Humenu with reasonable prices. Service was haphazard maybe because the place was almost full even before noon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvpGJwXUfQL0tz4UaxWftcOE6Ue_kfndK8OSKo"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Patricia A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9zd5DF1Owx-Xf_F3MuSYEcAhP0UXF0C_xMg6iQ8Srs_obvKJI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The signature barbecue dishes are always excellent and delicious. The restaurant’s ambiance is nostalgic, comfy and clean with several function rooms for events. The staff members from the waiters to the security guards were very polite, friendly and are always smiling which gives the place a more welcoming environment even for local citizens. This is why we love it here, a True Filipino Legacy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPhBZAMYlSQUDnxFfs671lUoxe1zURwaVAyjK_"],"When":"2024-3-7"},{"Name":"Hewey H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFWSeoj6DE-0x1BJ83i7hEpmEq_8_7K3vcOLaJt6t_El1x1gI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a delicious find in Manila.

Traditional food, at great prices with attentive service in a comfortable environment.

We were advised to try here by both of our drivers to and from the Fort of Santiago on our short stay.

We ordered the pork ribs (whole), abodo chicken, and the famous lumpiang. For four of us this was ample servings with delicious flavours of the Philippines.

We ordered rice with ours and ordered two but note the pork comes with its own rice.

I recommend all of these meals plus I believe, from looking around, you would struggle to find something that you won’t like.

Must try and thank you to the team for the wonderful service and delicious food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeEo7Q1ElWg94aEP-O1b9zGxN6eLeWT1AmfRp6"],"When":"2024-5-22"},{"Name":"Kat Moskito","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhjhtEKG0IaD5jgEdClumeXiqfO5xU8DVOwFSraWJQWe0N-MZoJw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"OG tambayan, I guess- and is back to 24-hour operation. Now managed by the 3rd generation fam but feedback from the foodie friend that the taste and menu stayed the same.

If you like your bbq sweet, this is the place for you. They give u a special dipping sauce, which I find to be a filipinized satey sauce.

They have pretty cakes that I have appreciated close and personal. I think I will buy pastries as gifts from here next time. Grabfood markup is 100 for small cakes and 200 for the big ones. Fyi.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMa6rw_kqvHr7-mQv2E0-867W9VoraJMGth2Sv"],"When":"2024-6-1"}]
