[{"Name":"Sridhar Kumar Pasupuletti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiGeuSqi1jw8W33PghU4n3f7Fgg8_V9t_XBgTNb05SAkTHBX5baQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Abe's, where good friends dine! Yeah, that tag line is true. Went with my friends and had a good lunch and good time. Tried lots of Filipino food. My friend Cathy explained each and every item which made my experience so good. Thanks, Emily for sponsoring...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG332NKI1L10dJA2S9b7hh1kV5pCFyD0Yt1nQg"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Kay.Tolentino Gaspar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqXi8pOJAM0TAeQw8Gg-N5v-EhfeKHTYseAhaIJ6Vmtzju9M5kVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We definitely had a great time dining at this place. Everything here is good. Friendly staff, great customer service, quick service. This is one of their better branch. The quality and taste of food are very good, from the mains to the desserts. Will surely return to try their other dishes. Popular place for locals and tourists alike.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNy7aqwFnVj_SpovsRzicxkIv6Bj2aT0YVUy_Ie"],"When":"2023-8-1"},{"Name":"Jay Orilla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-Y4iDcTTXGihTAYIYkBc8jKTfULjRmTjJkvoOoN8-nPoPHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Authentic Filipino restaurant. We had our lunch here on a Sunday afternoon and there were few customers. I love Abe's kamaru and hot chocolate but they are not available. The food that we ordered though was on point and tasty, the mutton adobo was soft and flavorful, so was the kare kare. My favorite was the turon. Great customer service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiSBszwYLTy_OvqT0FvY1niHuf_GyYtMZatYP-"],"When":"2023-3-23"},{"Name":"Elaine De Los Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5Oceh75YnVGRGKHRTm7N7y6fuRsGJXBFYBBpj8lJk7verq7ZB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends and I had our afternoon merienda at this place. All the desserts — toffee sans rival, mango canonigo, and sikreto ni Maria — were fantastic! They all paired well with hot coffee. The staff were attentive and the service was fast. They also have a special surprise for those who celebrate their birthday there. The decors and interiors are Filipino-themed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmKowK-Foe6H49SLZfAIXfd0vyzjVwWU--J5wp"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"DanAGo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3hFBUqs507A4LhUADYnDxZYI7iC28xET8ntEmJ3cXJIQooGPyuQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Located near the carpark from the Theater side. Its a quiet and cozy restaurant away from the casino and the main hall. It serves local dishes like Kare-kare, crispy pata and yes they have Halo-halo. Service is quite good. Serving size do tend to be a bit smaller and the price point is way much more. Understandlbly its inside a hotel so prices do tend to be higher than their regular store elsewhere. Serving time can take awhile and all our dishes came out in one out instead of one dish at a time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnPbuq_vhCl_gpn8bw1ACHMC_2RIa-B_4kvjCs"],"When":"2023-5-17"},{"Name":"Jeeekob","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCqig0NIzbnXOXHVQzxMhu7vyMF40jpNc3MrJkUH-fPfaqEsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Summary: Rude Customer Service! If you're a Filipino, you might feel like a 2nd class customer/tourist unless your clothes are all gold plated and diamond crusted.

It took us a while for the staff to take our order. After our order was taken, it took more time for our food to be served than other people who came in later than we did. They got their food served first even though they had a larger quantity of food.

The food itself does taste fine but overall, it tastes mid. We ordered the Klassic Kare Kare, Crispy Pata, and some garlic rice.

When we finished our food and asked for our bill, again, other people's bill got taken of first before ours did. When our change was given, the manager(?)/senior staff just slid the bill over to us rudely while I noticed that he gave it politely to the aforementioned people before us. The senior staff that did this was a balding middle aged fat man with glasses. Mind you, we paid our bill in full which was NOT inexpensive.

It is very ironic that a restaurant that serves Filipino food would treat one of their own like this. I fully understand that food service industry is a very demanding job, however we still expect a decent customer service considering the price you are charging your customers with.

For people looking for a place to eat reading this review, you can still eat here but just wear a big diamond necklace so you can expect decent service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeAEumZEi7BSlamGwTtzoGwGFyWVKBbEobiUkY"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Wei Ming Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBXN3k1cRsTUJCHaFtSO-Vy4l5E3ZGC4pDRrlDe0KcnmQf1WQqKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Most delectable local cuisine - it's like granny's home cooked food. There are so many items that are good - bistro filipino, tuna panga sa bawang (tuna chéri), crispy shrimp binondo, sinuteng baby squid...I cannot name all that I love, just be adventurous and try all of them out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8u6RcbxmDZw8hcixqoiV60wNqjjr4hwv1qP-x"],"When":"2019-5-20"},{"Name":"Mark Jubac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjsof3vhckLUrFBUPVnCo_WDO8j4Yca3JGLMmapfmksZMW8-JApw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"3 stars for now. One of the dish we ordered is not available.

I'm not a fan of their version of pork sisig. Too fatty for me and lacks charring.

Saving grace was the sinantol na hipon. It's hard to find Filipino restaurants that serves it.

Will I go back? Yeah, I still would like to try the other dishes before I decide never to come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObpoAX3zzJHpBRvqEJKVsT9JaChnUE91y0vbr9"],"When":"2021-11-3"}]

[{"Name":"Juan Mariano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrzcnCKH9YXiRxBywf_R6DbluLKRyTxLkMGJdJjNlFlkDFldO2iw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Charming and elegant setting, perfect for relaxed dining. The Spanish sardine pasta was well-presented and flavorful, with fresh ingredients. Not included on the photo but their Clam chowder taste good as well. The price is just right for the quality. This place would be great for anyone seeking a cozy yet refined atmosphere for a meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhDFeE5ipRBJCndg3rQg5r5mi7USjLykiYt3sY"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Sly Maranga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVdYscEdP9DYher8nEq89OeNuEsWJDLUobOQFPW-6yjCvSyMtTfPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always a happy experience in a Mary Grace but this one feels so much like Christmas. Everyone is warm and welcoming. Kudos the supervisor and leaders of this branch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUydbjVIKfXT57h31uvXc_UwllTi7XkLrRjqk_"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Zeus Canillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS-SiBMTjOxcgRo2Oj-e91i2K3cAzlx2c_bg0h8I--nowsvTIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mary Grace no questions asked!!! Food was and will always be great!!! The place as usual the best!!! And the exceptional and outstanding service provided by the crew, 5 stars!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMJOkfjArRjtJbR3icl9G3vf-KvP5sUhKnYfqD"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Joel Calderon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqyIFVNg_jULkLP0eVeQos0claI9NKdThO4zBbsYEwC82wGMAO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’ve never really thought of trying Mary Grace before. I dunno…there was just nothing on its facade that pulled us in before. But we finally tried them (Okada branch) last week and, oh boy, was it a delightful dining experience.

“Mary Grace” as a restaurant name doesn’t exactly convey  a “great pizzas” impression, but my god their pizzas were  heavenly! I dare say that a case can be made that their pizzas are better than Italiani’s, or even Amici. The toppings were nothing out of the usual, so it must have been the sauce.

Their rice meals were wonderful too, according to my companions who ordered them.

We didn’t order any cake or pastries on our first visit, but judging by the food we did order, I bet these are must-try too.

With that said, I feel compelled to give their service 4 stars only because it felt “mechanical”. Their staff were not rude or anything, mind you, but they lack the warmth, friendliness, and attentiveness that the “elite” servers demonstrate—for whom I reserve 5 star ratings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-twtOghf-v2tW9hUgxZ-lEAASctsU82aDAXBc"],"When":"2023-8-25"},{"Name":"Teng Mangansakan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-aZq7FLPb_DAJ1tTAoySqDdOo9PneLKS3YeJsAj4QnGDTQ5s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The seafood pasta was so good. The serving was generous too. I love it. I'll be back definitely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFGty4W00dbZisfaZTIqzgL1Y03aqNJW3j0KL4"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"행복하게 살자","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9IR-QeU0clUlkhpvZNUX1x_RECL4uUxVZdByU1DUAmZBhL17Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Many customers in this cafe.
The price is somewhat high considering the price in Philippines.
The quality of food is just acceptable, but not recommendable.
Employee Service is quite slow.
10% service charge beyond the menu price on the bill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOP6wZfBpGy6cDcO3_zq-cdOGd5Z_LgLMSlo50i"],"When":"2023-8-1"},{"Name":"shaq svl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjBNrq17kbG-DCC5xm2HYggtG6Ro8dS8JllJM-jzx9zQ9B3Gal=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Like everything's feels perfect to dine with. From the Food down to their service, I must say sobrang feel at home. The interior is well-designed from the decors, hanged displays. Seafood pasta grabe ansarap tas yung pizza not sp chewy pagkinain esp ung crust.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGgLMRinxcTn5A7S3XPjrME-tiGubuAP7Qs_xV"],"When":"2023-8-17"},{"Name":"Hui Ling Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUihQwKLnm5-bMSgryfEHebPVQYYkc0kYv9XPAzmz9Fg1DD_JZT4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very cozy place to hang out, ordered two types of cakes: mango & almond; very special combination of the cakes, not sweet types but very refreshing especially the mango types, the drinks are acceptable, but the mango smoothie was a bit sweet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQ0ofTeWRwzYWLt_oLW-i1LAIXieZqKqm5Ec-S"],"When":"2023-5-24"}]

[{"Name":"Evita Daan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHop4cYIy4AG80dA8o5lBRpkQArbwkym3t2Y-KdDiZ3iJxA4yEzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a Filipino restaurant. Pork sisig is highly recommended. Chicken arrozcaldo is also good. Most of the foods are sumptuous and the drinks are also delightful . It has nice ambiance and it is a cozy place to have lunch with the family. Food servings are good for 2-3 persons depending on the appetite. It is worth the try.

It has access to the casino.
The staff are courteous and fast. Service charge is included in the bill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-pnm_0j43x30sELlhqZqxlNqmm7xydkld0BKA"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Precious Pauline Pajarellano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLh3VF8MAsLB70XPdIvoJggbX2j51Y4sJr_KKFBpc868nVfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"On a relatively slow saturday night with a lot of tables available and by a lot I mean a lot see photo. We had to wait more than 30 mins for a table to be ready for a party of 3. And talked to another party who waited for an hour just to have a table even with the number of tables empty. They decided that setting up all the tables for DIFFERENT big groups before calling them would be ideal without taking advanced orders (yes I talked to most of them)🤣. Very slow for a supposed 5 star service unlike the previous staff pre-pandemic. The seated patrons in the photo are actually finishing up their meals already too so no reason for the wait staff to be busy.

10:30PM
June 15, 2024","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODrJWmLtlMIBi24SvGMjl6SMQIWlnC6dkSFgom"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Ann Daiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxePslcHQMtjOQFO6J-HTr4EQChqwtLz91NSpEAQmSdpoSr7sjAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's my go restaurants after playing casino. I loved their Kare-kare. It's pure beef meat. It's a little bit pricy for the pinoy Foods, but yeah, it's located at 5,Star Hotel xoxo. They also offered merienda in some season like ginataang bilo-bilo or binignit and banana turon during holyweek here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIQwW_A_MFlTQFjZvKmZL_0d-FfLW_WD0UbXjt"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Gerald Muriel (Temiatwork)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVavuOH-OSgYCJdwc2qP_Ta_-oaq93Al5rULVa4drFCvvp7TvsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the restaurants surrounding Okada casino. This restaurant serves Filipino comfort food, from grilled seafood to breakfast favorite, congee.

One last comment: do not order their grilled seafood if it's not served on a sizzling plate, the food gets cold quickly due to the AC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNp-bph_8fJ9BCfE0IkY-VePOueuElq4l0BJNE"],"When":"2023-12-28"},{"Name":"Rolando Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaxBKBhBqanQe2XbD04XxSAIfDGlGm73xM29LrEPL7SQAfvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was good. Service was good. Obviously it's kind of pricey because it's in a casino. The ordering process is pretty interesting. Your place mat also has the menu in which you mark what you want to order and tear it off to give to your server. Pretty interesting way of ordering and convenient to be honest. I would eat here if you want to eat quick Filipino food if you're taking a break from the casino activities.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONymRIVS-6hyAkKTFqJdWEdfnSVo0MoBbqdWwZ"],"When":"2019-10-29"},{"Name":"Norman Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU56fM6wa-lJciOgjIs-rz7DoGZ8P1Qk885NUdWeYv_XrykmJkr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Probably (arguably) the most value-for-money of the Okada restaurants. The food is satisfying, serving sizes for groups of 2 or more, with rice bowls for those in a bit of a budget. A standout for me is their sizzling tofu. Not the best location, being right next to the slot machines, but there's no smoke smell.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cyprian Bergonia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsv2SXHAPACk8nkhTz7jrugvIraefIHXT2w0xfUJAY82ZMkleexg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We only had a small order.
Lumpia was decent. A little oily.

We also got Pandan De kiapo and CoCo Leche.

We went at 10pm not too busy at all at the restaurant. But the service was very slow.

It took a long time for the waiter to get our order, even after I signalled for them.
They also took a long time returning my card and I had to go up to the cashier and it was just sitting there.

Expect long service times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKf_wPAmMuQ9Hvl3ha3yDWqQr-PckIms40PGol"],"When":"2024-2-7"},{"Name":"Hesther Fuentebella","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXymlSpbJ9BoS9fuwuijNG_rjysJ520XRh1BJ2wtAlvwL73A_A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Their service was terrible.  We were seated near the entrance hoping to be seen by staff when we call them but unfortunately, i had to raise my hand for a long time to be given attention to.  There was a confusion in our order which caused initially by a misunderstanding on our parts but when clarified, even the garlic rice took minutes to be served. Upon bill out, i had to stand up to follow up on the check out request. Will not go back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Myles Chuahiock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeNG2nNmob78xQyovxUkYccsGbxn7c8UowOEv3rBJcdCh9NPmc7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bangus offers a delightful dining experience that highlights classic Filipino flavors in a relaxed, casual setting. This restaurant successfully brings traditional dishes to the table with a level of finesse and authenticity that can satisfy both locals and newcomers to Filipino cuisine.

The food at Bangus is a testament to the rich culinary traditions of the Philippines. The laing was particularly good, with its creamy and savory blend that was beautifully executed. The pork sisig was another standout, cooked with just the right level of crunchiness and flavor. The Bangus with green mango provided a refreshing and tangy twist, complementing the heavier dishes nicely. Additionally, the garlic rice, often a simple side, was notable for its perfect texture and ideal balance of saltiness, making it a fundamental yet memorable part of the meal.

The decor of Bangus maintains a minimalist Filipino style, which adds to the unpretentious and welcoming atmosphere of the restaurant. This simplicity in the setting ensures that the focus remains firmly on the food and the dining experience.

Service at Bangus was both attentive and efficient, with food arriving promptly and staff showing great care to ensure a pleasant meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgrkWiagkG2tE7Jev1QiP2tEsX8TQKZaKck7Fc"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"L R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHrTNX-1fIIVvcZ0S5c0crYpe4QdEOD73p7DY3zWXXUQKkdA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fantastic service. We were in a hurry and asked if the meal would be able to get to us quickly which they accommodated without sacrificing the quality nor friendliness.

Garlic fried rice had nice crispy browned  garlic bits. Daing na bangus was done up right. Sinigang na baboy was full of veggies and pork belly.

Interior is sort of fast food-like and isn't a huge place but is conveniently located. We appreciate their quick service. We were in and out of their super quick in time for an appointment we had to get to on a full stomach.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmCAsn0_0SEVelHU4fhSHv72tEVhuGI8oq5RiD"],"When":"2023-3-16"},{"Name":"Dane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLmPxXT_UYxUJG_QmNXE3s5wdcqqI-1GwLK7sYD7fd7N6J0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food is very pricey and greasy. I don’t like the atmospere of the restaurant, the staff make us uncomfortable. We heard one of the waiters saying that, its good that we already left the restaurant, not knowing that we are in the comfort room when he said that.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophia Velasco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU9gjJAOg6igfErimdD598jluL_v3InGfrKxRbPOlZKETjI-PWOw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don't be fooled by the name - there's a good selection of Filipino food, including pork sisig and pork sinigang. The restaurant is small and cozy, and servers were friendly and respectful. The food was delicious and fairly priced. I do wish they gave more sisig for my "Busog Meal" (combo). For rice lovers: They give plenty of rice! Overall, would come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMe-pmHJl5l3MGXX-CW12TlUfkXc9hxp7cOgMeA"],"When":"2023-5-14"},{"Name":"William (Asurai)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxipSjGnovITAZCYxL9kwp5W7BeK7N017_WIAUtyJl2lfVtIFB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst filipino restaurant I ever visited. This is not a joke. Overpriced, so many mosquitos, too few bangus meat from dish and poor taste (so fishy) and we ordered 1 sizzling bulalo but didn't come out. But their food tastes weird and so overpriced. I won't go back there again. The name of the restaurant is 'Bangus' but their Bangus are so bad.

P.S to other foreigners - try other filipino restaurant first and rate this restaurant. This can't be a best filipino reataurant unless your intention is in sarcasm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRvzKSZopL69zw8e0nmvwGd_nWr1TaUBJEDBBG"],"When":"2017-12-29"},{"Name":"Ritzi Yap","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P80RXt8_g-f3IwyfnSyVC692hRojnfha_lGXpKqgqDY36pVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's not bad, it's not great either. Dishes are expensive compared to the taste of their dishes. I ordered kare-kare which was one of their expensive dishes. I was not satisfied. Feels like Kuya J is better. The plain steamed rice is very low quality rice that somehow looks and tastes like NFA rice. I would not recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUTnp6bVn46hFXUC_NDm_p5Ci0x2ig7IgMKoJk"],"When":"2021-4-23"},{"Name":"Antonia AL","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMV-NdJVRE-5ta7QQRDwPhZViS44ZtJs9cuMKpI_CUEtRuy91d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty Philippine traditional food with very affordable price, the staffs are polite and helpful, highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrRISUWNxjG4noAJgaHzLwhAStHUBcmOw6fbKY"],"When":"2019-5-23"},{"Name":"Michelle Morales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxDEUNX10nUgHb7AN6BDsNMQCSpCrNoJBTz7hfChuGlYcs2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We order garlic rice, pinalutong na bangus at ensaladang mangga, lumpiang bangus, kare-kare, & bangus bicol express and we were satisfied with the taste.

The garlic rice was savory and not salty. Pinalutong na bangus was really light and goes perfectly with the sour ensaladang mangga. Bangus bicol express was quite good, but not the best. Kare-kare was good & had ample vegetables.  I can't say much about the lumpiang bangus as it wasn't crispy and taste was quite forgettable but it was so easy to eat & we still finished it.

We used to eat here a lot 10ish years ago because of their pinalutong na bangus, lumpiang bangus, & watermelon shake. And overall, I'd say it's still pretty good! Save for the fact that their servings were smaller than I remember.

We would eat here again! 👌","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ven Mar Balboa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPCbCfRepP-hgvmsvkYUZOH523G1Z0FBxiX0Uhu5SW3qmBese1JA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently dined at las Flores okada and had an exceptional experience. The ambiance was cozy and inviting, perfect for a special evening out. The service was impeccable, with attentive staff who made great recommendations and ensured we were well taken care of throughout the meal. As for the food, each dish was a culinary delight, beautifully presented and bursting with flavor. I especially loved the paella’s which was cooked to perfection. Overall, Las Flores exceeded my expectations in every way and I can't wait to return."","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNWa-9_iYyK2R9uRwfKgHUvv_ddNEwMlIqVWnEx"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Madam Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW64SC3kLlBuBizDPmhPox1sp4ERnedDq7rxITlGiUovyYR0ro=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food if youre looking best Paella. Located inside Okada Hotel. Staff are friendly too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPjlXVMTeVjaMW8aTCfl8BAROayqXtiArg-5M3"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Nicholas Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUnn16Jz359SG2kIKqs7ys2tzQCZzzJmjBJI0-wM0qy6sSxqJo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loved the cheese board and the tiny fried squids. However, the rest of the dishes were just so-so. The gambas lacked punch and the squid ink paella was pretty bland. Can get pretty noisy as well with the loud music. Service was prompt and thoughtful nonetheless.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPlkod3ClgyHqKr6NyKTIrPohytAXItVeUjYT7"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Joshua Eliason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOwjkLe9mUzX05LHk26xStmTKfqVNEXjUcLhWfTN9mGokDRRTn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I must say that this experience has been a major disappointment. To start our meal me ordered the Foie gras. Sadly the sauce it was served with was very strong and overwhelming. I couldn’t taste the Foie gras at all.

I ordered the pork loin with a vegetable sauce and mashed potatoes. The pork was sliced incredibly thin and then smothered in what I can only explain as a cheap brown gravy with canned mushrooms in it, very disappointing. The mashed potatoes were bland and needed seasoning.

My partner ordered Grilled Halibut. Sadly they brought us a halibut that was Pan Seared.
We called the attention of the waitress for her to check if our order is correct.
The Menu says Grilled Halibut but when the order arrived, it was Pan Seared and Thinly sliced.
Not worth of a One Thousand plus Pesos.
Aside from not giving us what we ordered the waitress came back from the kitchen and lied telling us that it was grilled when it was obviously Fried.

We replaced the halibut with a baked salmon.
Waited for more than 15mins for it to be served.

The baked salmon was SABOTAGED
The sauce was filled with chilly that cannot be tolerated. Even we called the Manager to taste the sauce for him to check if it’s on his standard of serving, as he also cough like us after tasting the sauce.

The manager did apologize to us and offered us our food on the house. I do appreciate that.

Sadly this experience was a nightmare.
We hope they serve better in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwEXUMA9qdPeEPbKR_uy9s4Cp5oTSKMVnOFPae"],"When":"2024-1-28"},{"Name":"James Dylan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVO4GgpZZ_PoL7BcnFiRCT8stPJY7AaMXTsMltAVXR0hdyP6QsX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place, but it is literally open to the mall walkway, so it isn’t very private. There is loud disco music, playing in the walkway area, and then the restaurant has their own music, so you have two different songs, playing at the same time, which is an assault on the senses.

We ordered the Cochinillo Segoviano (suckling pig), which was great.

Food and service are great, no complaints.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNDGObT7VnS9YkwTcJdPRtMDO1u_ucxylPuQbN"],"When":"2023-11-3"},{"Name":"F S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVk2FZiEs8Q2ZNTxA2MBFXh6utNVGQ-JG1vdkT_KpTUvwKYRjJzTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Lovely place and people in the Okada branch. Friendly and efficient. Food wise, loved their version of calamares...and oxtail stew. Paella  is passable. Sad that there was no socarrat. Arborio rice a bit mushy... Not really something I would return for. Ordered also the cochinillo which was tender as expected. Could do with a bit of seasoning... Seafood used for their pasta is fresh. Shrimps were sweet. For the price , I feel like we couldve  eaten at a better place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI-ne2NTKsFg4B8UnAqVQs0qos16wfKbCzCybr"],"When":"2023-8-20"},{"Name":"Rossele","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdt_t_Bh4Qa5FngIovlAQ2K-whARqxnSjcXAkPKfeI73PYYtk-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pro Tip: Take advantage of your credit card promotion if you have any because paying full price is not worth it.

Our orders were:
Paella Negra 4/5
Seafood Pasta 4/5
2 Crocquets of different shape 3/5 (medyo nakakaumay)
Calamari 3/5
Gambas 4/5

Paid 3,500 just for all of these. See photos to judge if I'm right or wrong.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqEFX8lFAEq_XBRuilLcM_zksvItgeZ0Us74_g"],"When":"2023-12-25"},{"Name":"Kissa Paroli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTknhWNVkhnrLrjdjiONZdHlwieNdyjCXmpgYu64TxL6DggNZo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Las Flores is a spanish food chain. We have tried this the first time in Greenbelt. This time, we had lunch here in Okada. It's always great. It never disappoints. From pinxtos to sangria, it's all worth every buck. Albeit, if I may say, the amount of serving of the paella can be reconsidered. It's kind of little.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYQo4knVMq3-tkZ4QHc2vm0HYkZQjXF3L9JJjt"],"When":"2023-11-13"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Michelle Buentipo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvg0w6ksItkzon_FDIYnBXXv_vweH4E_dqhL1oDj_bE-KBlxHv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Spent Father’s Day here and we really enjoyed the food! My dad’s an Ilokano and he was so happy to have found a restaurant that mainly serves Ilokano dishes. We got Fiesta Rice (5/5), Ensaladang Swa (5/5) the dressing was so yummy!, Pinirito nga Baby Pusit (4/5)- the quantity is just so little but it’s yummy!, Lumpiang Tinapa Flakes (4/5), Karabasa Soup, Ladec (4/5)- wish this was more crunchy, Kinilaw Tanigue (2/5)- have high standards for Kinilaw and it was just not it sadly. But I feel like pwede na siya here sa Manila haha,
Adobong Kambing (4/5) - love the garlic confit and the meat was so tender, again portion size lang talaga medyo sad but it’s yummy!.

For drinks we got Dalandan Shake, Pomelo Shake, Watermelon Shake, and Sago’t Gulaman. All great, didn’t know you could shake Pomelo 😅

For dessert, we had the Pistachio Sanseival and NY Cheesecake. Both were also so good.

All in all the food was yummy the only set back was the staff. Medyo ma-attitude lang sila and we were seated right in front of the bar so servers were quite loud, mas malakas pa sila mag chikahan haha. Other than that atmosphere was great except for the SOBRANG DAMING LANGAW. Even the table behind us had to tell the staff about it. 😭","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOGHCn7c9tuB4xcgUe6rq9zm5X8KJqMqND-YEm8"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Franchesca Brianna De Guzman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpUvquTsPHB9qftbH7Sk-DAmAxaaDSw0eNcQ1d5eCllZZRPrWm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Went here earlier with my partner and mother-in-law for late lunch. We always loved the food here. When we arrived at 1:30pm, the ambiance was peaceful as usual, just the way we like it. Their security guard assisted us with the parking and Clark the server was very friendly and attentive. Their food is always good! It never disappoints. However, we were upset when they told us they can’t separate the igado sauce from the pork anymore (photo attached was from our previous visit). We totally understand the chef’s policy. I don’t usually give low ratings but I’m really disappointed with the other server who bust out our plates, the way he took our plates is really irresponsible. He ended up spilling a lot of vinegar in my louis vuitton bag. I don’t want to name drop but his colleague, Clark, knows his name. The server also had ego when we called him out, on his defense, he’s just newly hired, he didn’t saw my bag placed in the seat. I would understand if he just say that he’s sorry since I know he won’t pay for the damage. So, they just randomly spill food/condiments at their chairs? I don’t understand. Additionally, what’s inside my bag is my Passport and Passbook since we’re heading to the bank after. Thank God, there’s no marks but it really smells! Is that how Victorino’s train their employees? It’s kinda upsetting that they have staff who lacks basic hospitality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNW4Qhz6WFurBSGqnJiNzcy0ag940deXT_QJrwj"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Sherwin Clarence Go","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsOZqxdklF9eaO2J-sGBARoj6HG5At4eXNQWA9UKPbNtFOgodnLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dine in on a Sunday lunch. Victorinos specializes on Ilocano food. Delicious overall, especially the bagnet. I also liked the adobong baby pusit and kalabasa soup. Service is good overall. Although the airconditioning seems lacking on a hot Sunday lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPgbLtfiAdeAj0jVw3zgm-EYAJH7S6xDgvzNoW"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Mike Carmona","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXD7yT61iokB2BBgs6NOijRuOsGS-u6TxSxr9JCXTdZ-E9SKiH9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pricey for small portion dishes. Crispy tadyang and rellenong alimasag were good. Hope they consider offering espresso coffee. Hard to call for service, staff runs around and not organised.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjkpkqV10UpaI4UWvYfKgy32i8tUDoaOLDEvcr"],"When":"2024-8-1"},{"Name":"MG SLGDO","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8BckyqmFB053lm6eYE7B3fsrLumtSdGPOGz9nEVWFzYHk5Wy-4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We enjoyed our dine-in experience. Food is okay for its price. Kaso for some reason na huli dumating yung chicken 😂 The service is great waiters are attentive to our needs and were polite. Heny Sison cakes is the best! We tried two different cake and its delicous.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsYFHefMDLURCj8Ogr9LFsGlOz20aC3vSJ9qcx"],"When":"2024-3-6"},{"Name":"Adama Coulibaly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwlRaqeYuFJP9vSA7H4b8C71khpJdBOh2ve-EJrGL5kI02h0X2kQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'm writing this review right after a group dinner with my colleagues where we enjoyed traditional Filipino food. 🇵🇭🍲

I got a big bowl of salmon soup that could clearly feed two or three people. We're getting our money's worth, that's for sure. 💰💸 This desert, Halo Halo, in the picture is a living example. #HaloHalo #FilipinoFood #Yummy","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATufMwfpKMpozavZmHnXd21iGhhPeWGIt-Fit"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Joseph Samuel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCtbyvcs3lJ0lPdDCYB2kBQmIzQ1-7qbcFFISnpfTiJiWm3VNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful resto, good food, excellent cake.
The toilet is so clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNK5bzYI9aYIki70QU47lFbZYXuoNmIkl-5Sm-I"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Lawrence Agpasa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU57geDVnIcI-uEJV5trG-aPCkutgDIEspoOZwNeMEAgNRR4kr6UA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice Ilocano restaurant. Their Cristy Pata really tasted good. The pinakbet was a bit sweet though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR87prEqzF7dbLVbqwDYTWEZaGjppUwBtU4JZz"],"When":"2024-6-9"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Karam Devnani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpF58evjqCKY3LHkOGOxQWapl3TbnhfMycwn6Kr_u9qLAP4EpW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of my favourite Filipino restaurants. They are very creative with their dishes and modernized Filipino food. This is not the place to gonif you want traditional Filipino food, but they definitely did it justice. My favourite is the lechon oyster sisig. It is so sinful but just so good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbH9cEiM3PRCUtw7V_-tRXhpe-H9Fc4lb5qZWr"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Joed Panopio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC3uCkLJZ4klzBcHxOEh28bJrzdlZ7ZErba-66jxdYiFZTEUch=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The attention or service provided by the crew or staffs are excellent that reflects the kind of Management they have headed by the Operations Manager...I personally talk to the Operations Mananger giving him my highest commendation to their branch at the ground floor of Conrad Hotel in MOA.  Likewise, the foods recommended by their crew are excellent.  The taste of the foods are all great. This dine in restaurant is highly recommended at all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuXYf_v17ZlFbd5PSVTNUsSiyC6xdsvp3wsCd2"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Krantzl Kaneko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsOD8okEOFVmonljMJB67US7zAeLI3nnba2sVyHRbYH5hYpNab=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place to hang out with friends and kids. Very nice Filipino food. The Palabok and Gising Gising were my favorites. Very cute cocktails too. Nice interior and tableware. It seems like they renovated their menu from the last time I ate there in 2018.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHTfhuc8eoKdj4N-zQi2atdyo265EMLPRqe_Da"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Joyce Corrine Cuerbo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4bDDRPO7YfCToe-yFuwR2eSyoaOSw_YQFXzUNxitdQngwGDdv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and very attentive staff! Absolutely loved our experience. Definitely a spot to go back to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt0XYborECPFOAgyhChsIjUg5si7-V6roLwJ-K"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Max Brand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_06FfBhLT3JzuHRScxh9sNuc318znw0RI2b6KM1Czx1Xkaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was our first foray into Filipino food and we were more disappointed than pleased. To be fair, every item we ordered was really tasty, but most of them felt like an invitation to a heart attack. Just too greasy, especially the corned beef dish. It was 80% just fat! Even the watermelon salad tasted greasy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN90lE2bUH9tIvx47Dv14RLupsj0BPMiugaQFLH"],"When":"2023-7-9"},{"Name":"Mikhail Tiu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcw-NOaX3S_kTbn1gh3XBMviFm-CCHQrsdxJ0vuPKCrFkWtumy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant offers Filipino food with a twist. Most dishes have the classic Filipino way of cooking or taste but they elevated them and made them into something new and interesting. What stood out was the mangga't bagoong with chicken wings since you wouldn't find this combo elsewhere. It is a good way to enjoy classic Filipino dishes in a new way.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZwEAtFgmUW4IPUsxru0UWnT52_ZFOffAoVuTg"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"ARBN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI91quIZyFx7RE23ebBhQKPSqmmJV2ao298jSVBpvY8m_hxCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Be careful not to think this place serves traditional or typical Filipino cuisine. On the contrary, the place has been renowned among locals as a place to sample Filipino food with a twist - a big twist, if I might say so. The ambience is befitting of the quality and style of food they serve - fancy, different, yet somewhat still homey.\n\nThe Filipinos food which you may have been accustomed to becomes out of the ordinary, and is not very typical of the cuisines. For most dishes, the only thing that perhaps made them Filipino was the name given - the combination of spices, ingredients, taste, look and even manner of serving actually becomes alien to most locals. Nonetheless, it has become popular to most Filipinos, at least ones who can affors the place, so it may still be worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuNAhQNWm4s_bnQB7inkxxQDPQl4elU8ISzCbQ"],"When":"2024-1-26"},{"Name":"EatsForYou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1cSyPXx9IRs_f4GFo4CNf6yw5LE-_B6gNt050naDoIFRPPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Usually I go to their branch in Kapitolyo, but tonight I decided to bring some colleagues to the S Maison branch. It was the first time to try the restaurant for most of them and I’m glad the quality of food is very consistent. Serving portions were just right; I think I even over ordered. My favorite is sizzling sinigang and garlic baby squid. Everything was great! Even the garlic and onions are flavorful. Eat them! :) Could improve on service though. Order taking was not seamless. There was a miscom on the drinks. Server said all shakes were unavailable so we ordered juice but still mango shake was served instead. Overall a pleasant and enjoyable meal after a long day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6aA3A5KgdfNnwYW-hK4YPD1EC1x-lRkmcoNbJ"],"When":"2023-10-28"}]

[{"Name":"Carolyn Asuncion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHXe4diaFBlgmMt6sU3WRUz5P8nDTyzf0vuEiv2lZKccW_3I_1xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’ve been looking forward to trying the   V.I.P’s Lunch at Amis Restaurant for awhile now, and was so glad that I did! The food was so delicious and the service was really great. And for dessert, I ordered maiz con yelo. The food was great and cheap, especially for the area. Everything was well cooked and the food filled me up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPayE1y2uxErJTet9UODQIyuvXespSgxqBhHxRa"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Jho Celero","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU87GgQVGT9NZLeA3SxX55mGmHSk-uV49PCZod5BOLVAOY3hGlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here for a late lunch. It's past 12nn but people were still on queue waiting to get in. The staff was kind to direct us to the second floor for our table. We had the lechon kawali rice meal and the amis special set. Turn around time was under 20 minutes. The taste was pretty decent but nothing fancy. I appreciated the staff for their attentiveness. Their guyabano and mango fruit shakes were refreshing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSRQVQlcoRvz6ydwW8rsicDc0JcKlRTxvGz3ka"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"Norman Giovanni Guevarra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQRQ7S21TUwt9OfkypexYRO4bIxnIwxsO8IZKMcREuJgVXwHqu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amis Restaurant in the heart of Quiapo, Manila, is a delightful culinary journey through traditional Filipino flavors. The ambiance exudes a nostalgic charm, reminiscent of old-world Manila. The menu boasts a variety of classic Filipino dishes, making it a haven for those seeking an authentic gastronomic experience.

The pancit miki bihon is a standout dish, showcasing a perfect blend of savory noodles and a medley of fresh vegetables. Each bite is a symphony of flavors, capturing the essence of Filipino cuisine. The set meals offer a convenient way to explore a combination of local favorites, providing a satisfying and well-rounded dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNCd1qPFrYIpKrXUv26BQBXc_pZEr2XHMsUQMw"],"When":"2023-12-6"},{"Name":"Mark Miguel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpm4V-Tfezyai9hhdluB03l4QkijGlt9QREW9WFIITLCWeZolq4Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had this amazing lunch at Amis Restaurant. The sinigang na isda was amazing! I highly recommend the lunch sets. We went here Saturday and the customers are not that compacted. People visit this restaurant after attending mass at Quiapo church. They offer the best options for Filipino foods.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8BbjFvv7mV_Sh78COicYbgS4Azglt3ctoUuya"],"When":"2023-10-21"},{"Name":"Chris Cariño","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISyAt7mvadfE8hquRe5pShaYvoM13tevqyHpAK8AMFMmfJSjWB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here around lunch time on a Friday and they were not too busy. They gave me a table and the menu. Quick and pleasant service.

Chinese vibe resto a block away from Muslim Center, within earshot of Quiapo Church and a kilometer from China Town.

I got the president's plate?? Came with Camaron Rebosado (breaded shrimp), siomai (dumplings), fried chicken (thigh part) and fried rice (chao fan style). All that  for 180 pesos. Also ordered pineapple juice (canned juice served with ice) for an additional 70 php. Good deal 👍

Chicken was great. One of the better ones I've tried. It's not like Max's or Savory restaurant's texture or taste. Definitely a different spice mix. Must try!
Could barely taste the quality of the dumplings since it's fried. Better if you could get it steamed.
Shrimp was good.
Fried rice was ok.
Overall it was quite good. Great for the price point.

Definitely recommended
Will eat here again
5 ⭐ all the way","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMOg60LA_jR3Fk5gTZ-LwqDP8QadGxnhwlZYIW"],"When":"2022-6-27"},{"Name":"K Vest","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK56YPrhb1rsMP6Dnzz-GybyIl3z9J5G-FXYDu4VK1j1VT5yea=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everytime we pay visit to Mahal Na Poong Nazareno and do Raon electronics hopping, we are always looking forward in eating to this restaurant. It is a truly hidden gem because you can't spot their place easily because they are covered by street vendors... We love their package meals. Their shakes is a yes,yes! Their waitresses are all friendly. They also have dining area upstairs but people are lining up outside waiting for vacant tables. A really must try resto in Quiapo.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk2tkrqlZyzSzQf3IPXphGWjsHNKxAFaqyz4il"],"When":"2022-8-31"},{"Name":"BrianChinito89 TV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1KQDsbk0jr5Pjt9j7_rShfz_87oGAGzji9TzOO4R2dFOtSqFdhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just recently found this hidden gem in the heart of Quiapo Manila. It really pays to look around your surroundings so that you could find that gem, the place was very nostalgic it reminded me of the past designs of restaurants that you could only see now from old tv series or an old movie. The uniform of the servants here are very unique it looks very neat and tidy as everybody looks the same but more importantly the food that they serve are really delicious and delectable and considering the current situation they are able to maintain a very reasonable price on their food without neglecting the quality that is why people are always coming back to this place if you happen to be somewhere in Quiapo Manila, I suggest that you pay a visit to Amis Restaurant. You'll not regret it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRzV0i7mMJiLZ5Jk06j6aUoCmwG9RaEHjgbvry"],"When":"2022-7-7"},{"Name":"Jei Filipino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYIKxZuDrqPeTdtUAuaBLRoEeklHtQRFTu_KW0AbHsecVJPTRofg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's my first time here and the experience was good. The food was fine. They said it was legit Chinese cuisine here, their palabok is not usual from what I Filipino style. The Ami Lunch was the one I get, it was fine. For me the food was good but not something I can say that I'll always look forward to taste. But their shake and gulaman was really good! Also their staff were accommodating the place looks clean and comfy for eating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOF0gtr0oXR6WcADBxdvwEpZwzPwBmIDFv5j85T"],"When":"2020-2-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Myles Chuahiock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeNG2nNmob78xQyovxUkYccsGbxn7c8UowOEv3rBJcdCh9NPmc7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bangus offers a delightful dining experience that highlights classic Filipino flavors in a relaxed, casual setting. This restaurant successfully brings traditional dishes to the table with a level of finesse and authenticity that can satisfy both locals and newcomers to Filipino cuisine.

The food at Bangus is a testament to the rich culinary traditions of the Philippines. The laing was particularly good, with its creamy and savory blend that was beautifully executed. The pork sisig was another standout, cooked with just the right level of crunchiness and flavor. The Bangus with green mango provided a refreshing and tangy twist, complementing the heavier dishes nicely. Additionally, the garlic rice, often a simple side, was notable for its perfect texture and ideal balance of saltiness, making it a fundamental yet memorable part of the meal.

The decor of Bangus maintains a minimalist Filipino style, which adds to the unpretentious and welcoming atmosphere of the restaurant. This simplicity in the setting ensures that the focus remains firmly on the food and the dining experience.

Service at Bangus was both attentive and efficient, with food arriving promptly and staff showing great care to ensure a pleasant meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgrkWiagkG2tE7Jev1QiP2tEsX8TQKZaKck7Fc"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"L R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHrTNX-1fIIVvcZ0S5c0crYpe4QdEOD73p7DY3zWXXUQKkdA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fantastic service. We were in a hurry and asked if the meal would be able to get to us quickly which they accommodated without sacrificing the quality nor friendliness.

Garlic fried rice had nice crispy browned  garlic bits. Daing na bangus was done up right. Sinigang na baboy was full of veggies and pork belly.

Interior is sort of fast food-like and isn't a huge place but is conveniently located. We appreciate their quick service. We were in and out of their super quick in time for an appointment we had to get to on a full stomach.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmCAsn0_0SEVelHU4fhSHv72tEVhuGI8oq5RiD"],"When":"2023-3-16"},{"Name":"Dane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLmPxXT_UYxUJG_QmNXE3s5wdcqqI-1GwLK7sYD7fd7N6J0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The food is very pricey and greasy. I don’t like the atmospere of the restaurant, the staff make us uncomfortable. We heard one of the waiters saying that, its good that we already left the restaurant, not knowing that we are in the comfort room when he said that.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophia Velasco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUU9gjJAOg6igfErimdD598jluL_v3InGfrKxRbPOlZKETjI-PWOw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don't be fooled by the name - there's a good selection of Filipino food, including pork sisig and pork sinigang. The restaurant is small and cozy, and servers were friendly and respectful. The food was delicious and fairly priced. I do wish they gave more sisig for my "Busog Meal" (combo). For rice lovers: They give plenty of rice! Overall, would come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMe-pmHJl5l3MGXX-CW12TlUfkXc9hxp7cOgMeA"],"When":"2023-5-14"},{"Name":"William (Asurai)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxipSjGnovITAZCYxL9kwp5W7BeK7N017_WIAUtyJl2lfVtIFB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst filipino restaurant I ever visited. This is not a joke. Overpriced, so many mosquitos, too few bangus meat from dish and poor taste (so fishy) and we ordered 1 sizzling bulalo but didn't come out. But their food tastes weird and so overpriced. I won't go back there again. The name of the restaurant is 'Bangus' but their Bangus are so bad.

P.S to other foreigners - try other filipino restaurant first and rate this restaurant. This can't be a best filipino reataurant unless your intention is in sarcasm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRvzKSZopL69zw8e0nmvwGd_nWr1TaUBJEDBBG"],"When":"2017-12-29"},{"Name":"Ritzi Yap","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0P80RXt8_g-f3IwyfnSyVC692hRojnfha_lGXpKqgqDY36pVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's not bad, it's not great either. Dishes are expensive compared to the taste of their dishes. I ordered kare-kare which was one of their expensive dishes. I was not satisfied. Feels like Kuya J is better. The plain steamed rice is very low quality rice that somehow looks and tastes like NFA rice. I would not recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUTnp6bVn46hFXUC_NDm_p5Ci0x2ig7IgMKoJk"],"When":"2021-4-23"},{"Name":"Antonia AL","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMV-NdJVRE-5ta7QQRDwPhZViS44ZtJs9cuMKpI_CUEtRuy91d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty Philippine traditional food with very affordable price, the staffs are polite and helpful, highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrRISUWNxjG4noAJgaHzLwhAStHUBcmOw6fbKY"],"When":"2019-5-23"},{"Name":"Michelle Morales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxDEUNX10nUgHb7AN6BDsNMQCSpCrNoJBTz7hfChuGlYcs2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We order garlic rice, pinalutong na bangus at ensaladang mangga, lumpiang bangus, kare-kare, & bangus bicol express and we were satisfied with the taste.

The garlic rice was savory and not salty. Pinalutong na bangus was really light and goes perfectly with the sour ensaladang mangga. Bangus bicol express was quite good, but not the best. Kare-kare was good & had ample vegetables.  I can't say much about the lumpiang bangus as it wasn't crispy and taste was quite forgettable but it was so easy to eat & we still finished it.

We used to eat here a lot 10ish years ago because of their pinalutong na bangus, lumpiang bangus, & watermelon shake. And overall, I'd say it's still pretty good! Save for the fact that their servings were smaller than I remember.

We would eat here again! 👌","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Gracie Fernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6wOT8oaoeb2-m-NUAogwQEDCzMsL5ADYRk4CKzPB0q1RLoU3T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not consistent with food availability.
Though the food is always great, it's not satisfying to eat the food that isn't your first choice in the menu.
Happened twice already.

Please understand that some people (like me) goes to restaurants  with a particular food in mind already.

I will pay another visit and to see if they have improved their inventory.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNrQYTcnaqRlZfooFqolM2HV6S-cH_ZBuyMI5QS"],"When":"2022-10-27"},{"Name":"Andres Narra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSeKEyL3sT2luQcG-pXEL7GEWeXDTHBtioBcPUL6-igoRjsnYv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here at around 8:45pm

Pros:
Food is delicious for the most part
Place is clean and spacious
Fitting atmosphere for the cuisine
Large and filling service sizes
Steep prices but worth it
Vegan Options Available

Cons:
No Service Water (they sell bottled instead)

Us 4 friends shared our foods with each other and almost unanimously agreed that the Sharooq Platter was the best in terms of price  taste and serving portions (ideal for sharing 2-3persons). The Thawm Macaroni is different and is best appreciated if you dont compare it to Italian and/or Filipino pasta.

Overall, I wouldn't know if this it the "authentic" Middle Eastern taste, but it's worth the glimpse. Will be coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMZJ-WRWovzSzY1X57qggYzj0kuMqmkG4ZDZQf"],"When":"2020-2-20"},{"Name":"Mary Rose Mercado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULo7LekC-cnLzD0mfGsMzw-gMpoi6rGwAys_WNL4oBMAEoS6fSfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried their branch near UST..Authentic Arabic shawarma I must say.Same with their felafel.Brought back good memories during my Middle East days.Loved their spicy garlic sauce as well.Their staff is very polite and very efficient.Highly recommended for those who loves Arabic cuisine or anyone who wants to try something new to their taste.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOUZW3fSVPGaTGv-TDBw3ZVmvCuveeQQVl0fYA"],"When":"2021-2-15"},{"Name":"K.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKFoTXXA97ZchtOdR3QVPGVGJ7kQGS5owI9_44Iz30yLwt5c02=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My initial experience at Saffron left me with mixed feelings. I sampled their Shawarma Rice and Chicken Kabsa, finding the former to be good but somewhat lacking in portion size compared to other options at a similar price point. However, the Chicken Kabsa was a standout, boasting tender meat infused with delightful spices, accentuated by their irresistible garlic sauce.

Then during my second visit to Saffron, accompanied by a friend who had an insatiable craving for their Shawarma Rice (he ordered two servings, by the way), I decided to switch things up and try the Sharooq. The dish surpassed my expectations, offering a burst of flavors that left me thoroughly satisfied, especially when paired with their delectable garlic sauce. It's safe to say I'll be revisiting someday to indulge in the Sharooq again. Despite the worn-down walls and ceilings in some parts of the interior, the flavorful offerings of Saffron remain the highlight of the dining experience.

— Ah, adding to the ambiance, they also provides a cozy setting with board games like Uno and Jenga available for customers to enjoy. It's a nice touch, adding an element of fun and entertainment to the dining experience, especially when shared with friends.

edit ㅡ During my recent visit (maybe my 3rd) to Saffron, I decided to try the Sharooq platter for the first time. This option, which includes the flavorful Sharooq alongside fries and a serving of garlic sauce, comes at just a 20 PHP (afair) difference from the standalone Sharooq. It's worth noting that while the Sharooq is still covered with tin foil for freshness, in the platter, they cut it into portions along with the tin foil. Diners should be cautious of the tin foil while enjoying their meal. Despite this minor consideration, the Sharooq lived up to its reputation, tantalizing taste buds and leaving me thoroughly satisfied. With this satisfying meal option available, Saffron continues to impress with both flavor and value.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JM Manuel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXujCxgu8IkWh_lPjESmXZa_G8A9GBXbOZ2H1OyMjhmf7WcKH_G=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very delicious food.. same taste like middle east shawarma, kabsa and fries and even sauces..  very yummy.. thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM41A-wBTXFvqLa_BGViTe-IXigcUM9atF6WanH"],"When":"2023-5-18"},{"Name":"ACM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWSzv7S-JKQzZ5Asz6XPdFBTsfPmkjlmlZsDtkyLhAckLt3Fdb4iQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the first and very few authentic middle eastern restaurants nearby UST. Food menu is atleast a 90% duplicate of what and how food is served in the middle east. Price is also good enough and is comparable to the prices you get overseas. Location is great but place may seem to get crowded due to large institutions it serves nearby as well as customers travelling from other places. Parking space in the area might be an issue for some customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray Pua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7TK6Eyf76hJtR4sumkLNqX3kTyWE1q_0RDccUX-AHkcdzbJrJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is great and authentic middle eastern food !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5hcWi6SCiOmdtnM3YE6cZ3VLZ2JHKLgfxZDVb"],"When":"2019-9-27"},{"Name":"Aelin Ashryver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-mfmqutZg6FasPL3T7GBHAANBV2s3Je9GNdrUVPjsy_0Iwg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Shawarma rice is chicken. It was okay, but I think you can get better shawarma rice from other restos for the same price. If you're nearby, this place won't hurt to try naman.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Very attentive staff. Food are worth the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOx8BlsBRPoQedLovvrKCuBseYSJ36pajlVA0Kv"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Meil Anthony Desales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqRda-MEVR3Wuq0uqV_2q2yqi14LHB1NQenqM7V6FqsZOWdCy1SA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food here is great especially the bread and dessert. I don't like the pasta but maybe my tongue is not meant for Italian taste for past. Their rice meals are good and serving was big enough. Their regular servings is already good for a Filipino tummy. The meat dishes are also good as well. My personal favorite is the bread with artichoke then have their free herbed bread dip on it. You can have UNLI refill for the service bread which makes the place having good value for money. If you have a BFF card you will save tons of money since they give generous discount. They also give free coffee which is really good when you have the card. The Caesar salad is also good especially the dressing and you can ask the waitress to add additional dressing for free. The biggest discount is on monday which will give you thirty percent discount for every transaction. The staffs are also giving super service, they are kind and attentive to your needs. I didnt have to tell them when i want a refill a water in my glass. They automatically refill it when it was 1/4 empty. This is a go to Italian restaurant that is worth the value on your money. Thisrestaurant is also available in other malls and if you find the other places lurking with ppeople, go here. This a hidden gem that most people don't know.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbwB_jcCtgwYHbQmYJ4wItUY5qTav1Odkk9MSM"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Meriam Dayao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyTQyZUFjsu5kGv_BDwRHR0jZVx4Hlzy9lLBZVu54QdzuA1ZgL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good restaurant.
Service is superb.
Food is very good like 9/10.
Location is a bit far if you will enter the MOA on the other side.
Pizza was really good and the fish filet is awesome or we were just hungry.
Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoNiG0m73TY7A5qCyXEgyqdgnJvivRRsZGh5ig"],"When":"2024-4-11"},{"Name":"Glenn Carlo Clavel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJYmzl8fgWIpdygRH67MlEz3BgJw9mFRiDW4I9x64Tr7wzpi2jxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was so tasty. The staff was nice and accomodating, however, they became so busy during the rush of customers during lunch.

I think they were still fixing their comfort rooms though and some areas are a bit dark - they should maximize the view of the seaside blvd.

The food though was really good -  we got the bundle order so we saved a few hundreds.

They also quickly packaged the pizza and the eggplant dish when we asked for it to be taken out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM42QMh8vN-kcnEccsj6zmwj1JxweCqWuIwH9Sr"],"When":"2023-11-5"},{"Name":"Byron Velasquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7xCBV1ZOuw9XiheKY_448g_fqp9I57a3Abjmm9gttTGQ7Jfs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love that you have al fresco dining. Pet friendly. 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZQllQC5r7T9FQp-lYx2FrAH01sfXmo0P9iWuV"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Genevieve De Pio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5-oZ7cDnsKObz78g6JjLBulSTmU1zhLrRcOAyg5A8eG4AQTsBXg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The ambiance of the place was nice. [{"Name":"Ray and Sheena P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW21X5I_xdptdULaaQzmB7Ek1xL6fZBUyIyIBCA0ZKsFVALsyFE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a quick service ramen vendor in the casino of Okada Manila. I stopped by here late at night while my husband was playing poker. Food came out pretty quick which was nice. The ramen was OK. Noodles were good but chashu was sooo thin! Also the broth was way thicker than other ramen I've had. It can hit the spot if your craving for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQQktvnOfU1GPFi9U-4VToCenWW37mDEpgs-qw"],"When":"2023-10-31"},{"Name":"pjacp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6GnkkwVdDdzT0GGxC813lLZtPi_XLfccdU8dpkho8jJkHiyk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A good ramen place to try in the Pasay Area while conveniently located in the grandious Okada Hotel. Perfect for those who want a hearty meal without emptying out their wallets.

For our dinner we tried both the Tonkotsu Shoyo Ramen and Tonkotsu Miso Ramen - which were both surprisingly good. It is now wonder this ramen stall is frequented by Japanese, Korean and Chinese guests!

A friendly tip esp for those who are not really into salty broth, opt for adjust the Shoyo Ramen broth to a lighter taste so as not to overwhelm the other potent flavors. As for the Miso Ramen, it is best enjoyed with its Original Taste.

A bit of improvement is needed for the overall cleanliness of the glassware and condiments station though. The glass they initially gave us still had lipstick stains on the rim while the condiments station was unrefilled and messy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJBl6eQRgsxFc3wqnH0IhCovs4hSUWQRnHTUPn"],"When":"2020-1-3"},{"Name":"Ray Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgYEgp6woycrTg6bhmvMt6tFCrfYaes7spw9x_qi7yzxyEjGORNQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A bowl of ramen and a beer costs you about US$7 here, which is a great deal, and the perfect meal for a snack when you need a break from the poker tables next door.  It's hardly the best ramen you've ever had, but it's a good bowl and worth the price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Paragas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUxMAcGQyDGcGq0N2CqSFyWMQPPK0m5UiwdcwkYeMK4uHrxl0U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best tasting Japanese Ramen house at affordable pricing. [{"Name":"Angelica Iguet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvxp62ejQD9PTo1vk9NafPhG60UjVuEyxYYr9XJ7hBNZA8iVL9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Never disappointed at this restaurant! From the service to the food, the staff is friendly, attentive, and above all to ensure an unforgettable dining experience. Kudos to the entire team especially to Mr. JP and Ms. Jane is amazing! Prepared with attention to detail and served with attention to service. The food here is really good. Our dining experience was perfect!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObN2odG2xPMC2xtFSNzKi9LEcRyh4u5Vjyt1_V"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Paola Quitalig","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkSLjFqMVdQBe85PDCuYAeNem1dumago5BvGXcZjWhwZcRePI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is so cozy, classy, and fancy. The food is superb, especially the steak. All the ingredients are fresh. We want to commend the outstanding service of Ems. He's so knowledgeable of the menu and we enjoyed all of his recommendations. He was so engaging and friendly which we really loved. We will definitely visit again and for sure will request for Ems! 💯","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4OUANt8ohuZcXQH138JmtNR3jaLiuCOLmElGC"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Claire Miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrb8QNWMGfF1TrsumUOKFXukuMSptrGev87YGR8ZpWmoMfE0GC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re looking for the most amazing Italian in Manila served by the most wonderful and amazing staff look no further than Okada - La Piazza.

My server Kayla was simply a delight, her recommendations spot on and she didn’t forget to let me j is before the kitchen closed to order dessert.

The starter, a lovely scallop in lemon butter with mushrooms, perfectly cooked and simply amazing.

The main was a delightful beef ragu pappardelle. Just the perfect amount of richness.

The dessert topped it all, a wonderful Panna cotta with a light berry coulis and berry sorbet.

If it wasn’t for leaving Manila soon I would be returning for more wonderful Italian.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOUpenH_GbnVEVI48YzlFV0e__PadaLcTAb3wL"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Ianne Buluran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPsnMXsJ-OAu5ZMl4RLmNIVpCaG0R7TtycrRmJCIE0za3O9tQ6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed the tagliatelle, soft noodles and a very pure creme sauce. We usually come here for the great pizza and panacotta. You won't see it when you walk by but they have a private deck for the okada watershow so you can easily take pictures or video.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdRqmyGo6_ct3a0BJgV4463ITIVRFnK7USvVo7"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Marieglo V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJo_u_gMZp9rrpatqskCchBzkp7gfGX7R_CI-lvJ1qMjXCMCDj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food:
Complimentary Focaccia - 3/5 (Bit greasy)
Burrata - 5/5
Insalata di Cesare - 4/5 (Nothing remarkable)
Salmone and spinaci - 5/5
Costata - 6/5 (Ordered the steak medium well since I'm pregnant so it's not juicy at first sight but I was proven wrong when we're able to taste how tender and juicy it is. The steak is also well seasoned.)
Panna Cotta - 5/5
Diplomatico - 3/5 (Sponge cake is a bit tough, maybe it was frozen)

Service: 5/5
I commend Tricia (our server) as she a good representation of the restaurant which boasts of sophistication. She is delicate and mindful in taking orders especially to specific requests (since we specifically asked the cured salmon to be baked well with the pizza). She is also attentive so the pacing of the food serving is timely and she offers condiments that would match our orders before we even ask for it. We also appreciated that she is soft spoken.

Atmosphere: 5/5
The interior of the restaurant is exquisite. You'll really feel the italian vibe. Also a plus since there's a viewing deck outside to watch the fountain show.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRdoY4RczMTCsLNM08V-ebXDeoWoPNOFsRnaVK"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"mark bernardo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwG2dx94kkzhSCOvv7Vuq_ZVCIOglCJaZEpMZUzgS-_TAkSb74=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We booked last June 2 for me and my partner's Anniversary Ems & Bert assisted us. They know everything about the food from ingredients and some small details very accommodating. So for me ambiance and food are giving but because of them they give more extra special.

Thank you again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5zLQ3HCdEawN4CFYeHAvLabyT4QK8ZCU47ILp"],"When":"2024-6-28"},{"Name":"Manuel Garing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVsvw1o-CURZcVPRWTkUzAn3EAg59PNAgPPxcdVetfnb4JIjOd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We celebrated our anniversary at La Piazza.
All the food we ordered were excellent.  Superb service from Marco.  Magnifico, La Piazza!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiGCetOxrhg6mydGX5xHYCKUuk1tysKv-bgPly"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Larissa Gonzales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJORd2siNC6FjaVZ-N0TPGk-cphjYSGk5nxN--HUwzJEvaRd54=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They just reopened the fountain area, and what a sight to behold! Kenneth our server was very pleasant, knowledgeable, and attentive. He was not doing hard sell.

Truffle pasta’s flavor was not overwhelming, it was just refreshingly good. I have a truffle bottle at home which I can whip up anytime, so I’m not that Gaga over truffle. Their pizza was “pugon” baked so it maintained the flavor, albeit it became soggy in the middle. Would’ve preferred a crunch in the middle, but taste is really good when I drizzled with honey! The dark chocolate from Davao was exceptional, I indulged without the guilt. Finally, their freshly baked bread is flavorful with the right crunch on top perfectly paired with EVO, balsamic, and Parmesan!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHwiII0GZknIcpch2elh7fcWHrjCtj_K_T8lKf"],"When":"2023-7-8"}]
