user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bill Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVLTz3CuMAAg_SiEpIhczTRjrBWJhI-hWlRKRwBvpTpRkgPTPW7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I’m amazed they were able to timpla all our dishes appropriately as well as cooking them with the right doneness. Here’s our selected paluto dishes: steamed suahe, lato with onion and tomato salad, tausi elephant shell, black pepper bakla crab, jumbo green lobster sashimi, sugpo tempura, fried maya-maya head in sauce, lobster head sotanghon, chopped papaya dessert.

A great feature from this restaurant is if the dish served requires a dip or sauce, they’ll give an individual bowl of sauce to each person in the party. Each of us in our party of 9 got 3 sauce bowls containing: soy sauce with chili and green onions (for the suahe), soy sauce with wasabi (for sashimi), tentsuyu with grated radish (for the tempura). I also appreciate the convenience of a giant bowl provided for discarding the shells and emptied regularly.

The seafood stalls fronting the row of restaurants as you enter the main entrance gate are probably more expensive than the inner rows of seafood sellers where we chose to buy from.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzvptmQNuzVul6zelRc5dxYsJHjznO1xnRXmpQ"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Matt Quebec","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5KPOqYE1xeG6k5Jo4JxJnWGtMtD7PDjZb9ksS0E4k2wX9YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We go here as a couple. The Paluto service is superb , excellent authentic Chinese and consistent in taste and flavor whenever we go back. The staff and crew were also nice. We tried other seafood local resto in dampa macapagal before but when we went here we always came back here for consistency.
I recommended this resto to my relatives and friends already and their input is the cook seafood flavor was great Chinese authentic.
I advise to go here on a weekday because the parking here is difficult on weekends and holidays.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIt8EfCIfw1YvQ1h9bfF3NNJm9JUyTFJp905vL"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Mark Richmund de Leon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJs55mSf1S0lSPqGpdy2cgFX6xJ0TIvcXOx4asWpyCGAmq17g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best resto in dampa. Quality of food is consistent. Not too salty and greasy.
Best tempura with the crunch in the outside, and right chewiness in the inside. You can still taste the shrimp’s sweetness.
Service just takes time. Be patient","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhMx5F83yrGWIwjw2dzw81ygQ1klP6GwVOd3Ja"],"When":"2024-1-26"},{"Name":"Tita Friday PH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxjRRfSvLkVpooR85DGi1wdhwig9FoLOlZGng_46yIO4g7sK_W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was absolutely DELICIOUS 😋 The clams with black bean sauce were AMAZING! Made a mental note to have the same sauce for crabs next time. The Ebi Tempura was PERFECT (as expected). They’re way better than most Japanese restaurants.

Service was a bit slow, must be because of their many take-out/delivery orders.

Best to visit with an empty stomach.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAhWVS1UYPX_6Pxc1AiI9UAdXUW_uU-A4y1NBu"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"Earlene Ang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqc9aASQ5-6swe0DCH2ErdUxbS3YCnTXUI27EpMNy6tDap9r37ug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best paluto restaurant in Dampa, and it's not as expensive as the other Dampa restaurants!! Honestly, the best tempura I've ever had. Would recommend that you try the baked scallops (with cheese), liempo, calamares, and salt and pepper squid too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCbbSaGdEWrIhdoKhpHDQEse8eoDguk5Z0XG8S"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"SHARE TV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7SxF19p8xkPZ6gFQFMNKnNsQ_xfxJI5V9ArvqmMY88nPHCacQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best tasting paluto in dampa. Service can be a little slow maybe because of the volume of customers. One problem is the parking spaces because the parking lot available got smaller. But overall experience is ok. Their tempura are very good. Crab sotanghon also is a favorite and a must try for all!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRx8lE1qzW6YbqPDWi93jW2PnNHcwwZBEasjo6"],"When":"2024-2-11"},{"Name":"Gel Aguilar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR7T1hNFl2MplGjn1KgT0A27JKCSLqf0bmWchChcHmJ5ENigSq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wanted to go here ever since we’ve watched Chef Jayps’ vlog. He was really vouching for their tempura.

True enough, it’s really good! Just the right ratio of shrimp and batter. Plus point for the extra crunch. Though we have to wait a really long time (20-30mins) for the tempura because there was a lot of order from one group.

We also had garlic kangkong, yangchow fried rice, and calamares. When you have fresh shrimp and squid and their good cooking, you’d really expect to have a good meal. Just have more patience because you wouldn’t know if you have to wait a long time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoJbyvqSwHD6_33-lxWnS2uYHrbmxVw7fRca6J"],"When":"2023-9-22"},{"Name":"Rocky Acot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCoJBhVdfOTKiyzaozra_A7N_wDoALMex3KxqYLw2Bq_lE7yik=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They now accept credit cards here. And parking is tight but you can drop PWD/seniors right to the front of the restaurant.  Call their landline to reserve a table and you can still stay past 9pm.

It's definitely not cheap to eat here- but their food is tasty and very filling.  I've never seen so much shrimp stuffed in yang chow rice.

The tower of shrimp tempura is the crown jewel here.  We also loved the baked scallops. Everything was delicious.

If you don't like to go and haggle in the 'palengke', send one of the staff to do it for you.  They charge +3.5% for palengke purchases if you pay via credit cards.

We checked the palengke bill - not bad but stay away from crabs...unless you're okay with paying P1650/kg! The prawns were at p680/kg","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOf8JP83Sg2j3yIPaXDsV6VvwU0vC2i4v-dd2pp"],"When":"2023-9-24"}]

[{"Name":"Jace Navarro (Jace)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI19rM97KT-gBlI5946dYd0YiZ1cuzZhr87BEj7m0M42QRIl38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I expected a lot for Sarsa. Sadly, it didn’t met my expectations.

3 Way Sisig- It has a distinct taste which tastes like corned beef. Flat lang yung flavors nya. Wala siyang body.

Isol- Gulat kami sa size. Masarap sya. Brined to perfection.

Laing- Nothing grand about it.

Garlic Rice- Decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1Cemp7ibugeozja5fX4NHL9QqCPHEuDQ55ZhF"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Marlene Po","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFKbGFQ8vg_qnCYrTUL9CF1v0RQBw4Q_WVqpfssKcIIZwDnOuC2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's been a while since my last visit to Sarsa.  Thinking of a Filipino restaurant to bring balikbayan friends, my niece suggested Sarsa and the food did not disappoint. Everything we ordered was delicious. Their PALABOK ESPESYAL  is he best I've tasted, better than Via Mare and Milky Way. The sauce was delicious, and not starchy, the noodles al dente.  And the toppings - Longganisa, shrimp, chicharron, smoked fish, squid, egg . Heaven! Writing about it makes me want to go back now.

The 3 way pork sisis was equally a winner, as well as the laing and kinilaw. We ordered the right combo.

The only slight disappointment was the chicken breast Inasal, which in fact we did not finish to the bone.  Perhaps the thigg part would have been better.

Out dessert was leche flan - which had the consistency of yema.  It was too compactvand sweet, chuckloads of condensed milk . We wish we had ordered the turon with ube ice cream - saw our neighbor's order of it!  But we were too full for another dessert.

Service was reasonably acceptable except for the peppermint tea ( not complicated, right) which we had to follow up from 3 waiters about 4-5 times.

Music was a bit too loud , an issue in restaurants here.  So the music plus occasionally boisterous diners - not a relaxing atmosohere.  But ...

All in all, a very satisfying meal for everyone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhT13WZ5AlEzn8BuaXkngxQduZ6g8GC0ocXiiG"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"andi j","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPYGNl1C_osLW1VJw6aNkN2VRAtDVkCBEUIBCs38Smc4Ae8kM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My go-to for Ilonggo food. Truly gastronomic experience every time I come here — I am a big fan of their menu. Love love looove their palabok ala negra, inasal chicken, 3 way pork sisig, and sizzling kansi (make sure to get the sizzling bec the kansi soup version was kinda meh, not like the ones I’ve tried in BCD or even Patpat’s).

Chef Jayp’s personality really echoed throughout the room, ambience is giving surf & shack, with local pieces and furniture here and there. I am impressed with how it all came together 🏄‍♂️

Place could get so busy that service could take long but if you go past peak hours it has quite a relaxing environment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPNsibqKfGH-iWi2bhCNfGUhGoLx1qj6HEBb0o"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Joshua Cruz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL71OMuAUW1PDSrhkBh2iKR4eNQVfh5lm_qSArDGzLjrSkLAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I think the bad reviews here are factual. Here are some highlights of our experience in Sarsa:

1. RESERVATIONS 3/5 - They’re very accessible via Viber and they easily confirmed our reservation. However, we were placed next to the door. There were 2 separate couples that did walk-ins, but they got the table with the booth. We did asked to be placed somewhere else, but we still ended up being near the door. During our meal, two flies keep flying around our food.

2. FOOD 3/5. We ordered Chicken Isaw, Molo Soup, Palabok, Sizzling Kansi, Tortang talong, and 3-way Sisig. In general, the food was ‘lasang malinis’.

(1) Chicken isaw (2/5) was dry, leathery, not juicy, no flavor except it was charred.
(2) Molo Soup (3/5) was served beautifully but Maam’s hastened presentation put the dish off; I like the idea of fried wanton with the soup, however, it went soggy afterwards.
(3) Palabok (2/5) was creamy but I dont know why. Maybe that was the twist? It lacked saltiness from the sahog which shouldve balanced the dish. The noodles used were thick since it was ‘pansit luglug’.
(4) Tortang talong (2/5) was your traditional tortang talong but they tried to
upscale it by placing fried alamang on the side and a minute amount of crab meat at the center of the torta.
(5) For the 3-way Sisig (2/5), the 1st third of the meat was boiled, 2nd third was fried and last third, I think, was buttered. I did not like the fact that I was that trying to be very careful with my bites/chewing just because some meats were heavily fried which gives the pork a hard/rock-like consistency.
(6) Sizzling kansi (5/5) was the only remarkable dish I had. I love that it was reduced so the reduced cream was rich in beef, broth and asim. Kahit ito na lang iorder ninyo at kanin.

I think I marked it low due to my expectations that the meals are outstanding based on articles available online. But in general, they did serve the food in the most honest way without any tricks or surprises.

3. VALUE FOR MONEY (2.5/5) - Yes for the experience. But I wont recommend others from going here. I will ask them instead to go to Gerry’s for Sisig and Palabok, Manam for Isaw/BBQ/Skewers, or Locavore for food with Filipino twists. We spent 3.2k for the whole meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcmS9EWrv4valNVS7yt7iGr23QdO4nJpZGZnJV"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Kat CM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnFdDpBQOqXAOsb7fhkpDXfqfxLRO8A19KulX0x1fvGrENmCw2qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is easily a 5 - one you’d recommend to family and friends.  Standout is their crab tortang talong, sizzling kansi and kinilaw.

Service is okay. We were able to get a reservation. We ordered tanglad iced tea and it took long to arrive. Better if they could serve the appetizer first before the heavy meals without customers having to request it.

Interior is nice, well-lit and ventilated/airconditioned. Just hard to talk to each other perhaps because of the noise (place is packed on a Saturday).

Overall, we will be back! We loved the food after all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPz7of5few7TRe6mTxegwp4yKKEJQYfzhgnkJ_9"],"When":"2024-5-11"},{"Name":"Jayme B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-J9wIvcLY2JMXcmV1kvzvpiuQ3xRZOzyAuuVoFO-MAk4l5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sarap balik-balikan Bacolod comfort food! All is good! Beef empanadas and piyaya are a must try. Discounted cocktail drinks available 2pm onwards. Service is commendable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ_eRqYLvHonfMZ-n3ec-PduNekJNMLshCFi68"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Jeff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9AVwimigMpU91SohBbR9pk96tRU8W1upnBXsbeUmmsYWqoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fun, locally inspired dining area with a tropical-surf vibe. Great food, especially the beef empanadas. Craft beer paired well with all the food flavors. Service was adequate, not unfriendly but not warm or engaging either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Y4lWyueAG3gi7B1Hy6WpakumuZkLol3lccfR"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Jem ____","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq-T47Sepcx73wrHUaxm3ImrkEs2znZlmNB-_crrb3fQZS9tMD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got to experience and understand why there is a lot of hype surrounding this place. Excellent, well balanced food all around, tastefully designed dining space, and warm staff to top the experience off.

We grabbed a few drinks to start our lunch: I had the Sago’t Gulaman and my husband had the Lemongrass. First thing that hit me was that the Gulaman wasn’t overly sweet. I enjoyed the fact that I could taste the herby notes of the grass jelly. For our first main meal, we had the Palabok. Again, well balanced. Chicharon isn’t the only thing I taste, I was able to appreciate the marriage of flavors that all the ingredients brought. Next, we had the 3-Way Pork Sisig and Inasal Paa. Both packed a punch with flavor but not to the point where one would get “umay” easily because of the excessive oiliness. We ended our lunch with the Halo-Halo and Piaya. The Halo-Halo was just like the gulaman- not overly sweet so that you can enjoy all the diverse flavors going on in the dessert. I also love that they were generous with their serving of Ube ice cream as well as the Ube syrup. The only real anomaly in all the dishes we enjoyed was the Piaya. I enjoyed the fact that it was more plump and moist than the usual piaya, which tends to be flat and crumbly. It came with a good serving of Coconut Jam to dip it in but I didn’t feel the need only because the piaya itself was extra sweet. If it wasn’t as sweet, I would have gladly scooped dollops of that coconut jam since it paired so nicely.

Nevertheless, it was such a great experience and we felt like we only skimmed the surface of what Sarsa has to offer. We left with our tummies and hearts filled to the brim.

Pro-Tip: We came on a weekday but the place was packed as soon as the clock struck twelve. Be sure to be there by 11, right when they open.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUTXI67LdfGy2RVqMjBEO0zENdrnAeVckba5dL"],"When":"2024-4-19"}]

[{"Name":"Blue Angel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc0390QXzdreT8WY7TT-r_C1fphF5Ip7SefS5QYQ2c2rr927zlGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"one of my favorite place to eat when in Manila “BUT” recently I got pretty disappointed with their food. presentation and service went from excellent to terrible. I Booked a private room with 4 big tables for my husband birthday. when we got there the room wasn’t ready, servers are nowhere to be found, the room was under a wrong name. Food was served extremely slow! We have to ask several times before they start bringing in food and water! Presentation wasn’t great, some food was over cooked. rice was served late (guests are eating the food without rice.) everything was served late and with two missing orders in one of the tables. Everything was set and ordered few days ahead so I wasn’t expecting that this will turn into a big mess which left me disappointed. Servers are somehow nice but the manager is rude. He never showed up in our room to ask or check if everything is okay (I see him walking in and out the other room checking if their food and if everything is complete). I feel embarrassed that my guests wasn’t able to enjoy the food which also ruined the mood of the celebration. With all this and with the price they charge me I won’t be using this restaurant on any kind of celebration anymore.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpETwuWDWcHQ43sJrOINLwxEvox5XKJrIB-khI"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Travel Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0hQWVxpujhKj9XLTKmsHfAorpN9wZWpzF0hbbn8qtR6ZukzBULA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chinese food is always good here at East Ocean. But sometimes, a good and simple meal brings people together.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEEwKulURwG2qf6-ZJumP9FI5F0tHukzHutiEi"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Gian Tan de Guzman (AG)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPTlpe-makQbXeA5sZRC3l2a1xz_Cwoj48OjcSk4e2M-j82usqhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'd recommend the suckling pork and the jellyfish that comes with it. Great food great service , probably not for a European tourist on holiday.  But fantastic all the same,  i had a fantastic meal","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMV1MP7XiKscaVUyy8lUV-HtGzEKsk0rFq6TQC"],"When":"2024-8-1"},{"Name":"Matthew Joachim Beltran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVegbLtoObjPKHh0eTle1zWT-RXoH6c8fj5laToUapmgw7suAdx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered the hakaw, siomai, steamed spare ribs, sweet and sour fish, spareribs, beef broccoli, yang  chow. [{"Name":"Catherine Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYH-I4RvrfRUXl77LorTgEYOQ9Iu5u4MQ2EyTsBvUTqYmBsYb3iA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed our family reunion lunch last June when my husband was visiting relatives in Manila from the U.S..   The food was delicious, and excellent customer service.  It’s not traditional Filipino restaurant and the food presentation was great.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_ibwYZk6N7XuKWmowfjdyB5o9lG3PJZJSXnKh"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Astrow Ty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-6qlNXEkPj5dAu7r7wQXAKYbWHmwxxXzy8Danw2p7-ZfBvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"📍Manam, Podium
₱325 Daing na Bangsilog
₱295 Sinigang na Beef Short Rib & Watermelon
₱325 Sizzling Corned Beef Belly Kansi
₱130 Tinapa Rice
₱120 Dalandan Juice
₱120 Calamansi Juice

My fave is the short rib w watermelon soup.
We always forget NOT to order hot drinks here because they put it in tiny cups w same price as cold drink but look at the size 👀. Such a ripoff.
Corned beef kansi was also not good.
My mom's fave is the tinapa rice.

/travelspeedx","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOaxOMBqp66_Vwoh15RIilHLBN9e3I-tcBxPM"],"When":"2024-10-9"},{"Name":"Kate DC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXazA2Bu8-C6o8lsnBWMS7jDV44VrIVoPuoBjFa8GsXwpf_lYmywg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Manam offers a delightful mix of classic and modern Filipino dishes. We ordered the crispy palabok, crispy pata, and watermelon sinigang—all of which were exceptional. The crispy palabok was rich and flavorful, while the crispy pata was perfectly tender with a satisfyingly crunchy skin. The watermelon sinigang was a refreshing twist on the traditional sour soup, balancing sweetness and tartness. The restaurant also has a wide variety of beverage options, catering to different tastes. Though slightly pricier, Manam's high-quality food and inviting ambiance make it a must-visit for Filipino cuisine enthusiasts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7k07DfTxiHHw2qlYOhFEaAYyXlIjdclG6qpWL"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"J L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRI0vYWZiCb_lo11jYwTsYL14kKBsFK3UTWGzcsyWdoxVlC9yX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful restaurant with a great food, amazing atmosphere and great service. Our server very knowledgeable and friendly👌🏻 i high recommend Manam Podium","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUZaKBu35GzBqBLpPsL65qK39WdW9-Q8t4MiyV"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Kaye Gee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXv0Qz332XvtkMVTfP8M8r9DLdmpDKZaYpyTzg5l7Xv5Yz3QtET=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Filipino dishes with a twist! I like the crispy palabok but its a bit salty the crispy pata is indeed very crispy! The strawberry camias is a must try same goes with the calamansi tart! Of course dont miss the kare kare. When it comes to the servers, they are very attentive and very good. But there are soooo many flies that I had my glass and plates replaced as they'll join you as you eat. The candles were helpful but i hope they keep them lit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkp37Is8-sVJonA5BZfG2bFty1RFTOOaSTq8nv"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"iynah chie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOP152cNdUuf2T1s223spGYS33DefxjDRrIQ-jA7t9n-ENK9v5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"My elder sister have bought food from Manam for take-out pasalubong to me before which made me curious.

It's my bf's birthday that's why I wanted us to try something different, and Manam Cafe Crispy Palabok crossed my mind.

Manam Cafe in Podium has a nice ambience. We went in almost 2pm that's why we were readily accommodated. We ordered Crispy Palabok, Fresh Lumpiang Ubod, Shiitake and Tofu Kare-kare, and Mango and Kesong Puti Turon.

We were amazed by the presentation of the Crispy Palabok. We thought the serving was generous, like for 2 persons. But when the noodles were mixed with the sauce, the serving was just like Jollibee's solo pancit palabok. Although  Manam's pancit palabok tastes way better of course.

Fresh lumpiang ubod tastes great, the sauce not sugary sweet kinda caramelish yummy. Though I find a single piece of it  small for the price.

Shiitake and Tofu Kare-kare was good. The sauce was creamy delicious, although not the traditional creamy taste I was expecting. It tasted like they used peanut butter. It's alright though. What caught my attention was the taste of the Shiitake mushroom. It still tasted bitter and earthy. And only a couple of pechay stalks and a lot of sitaw was there for veggies.

As for the Sweet Mango and Kesong Puti Turon, I found the Ice Cream they used so overwhelmingly sweet. I was looking for the kesong puti, but it's nowhere to be found. I weren't able to taste it in the dessert to think I ordered it for my kesong puti craving.

Overall, I find the food average. Anyways, I might try other food from their menu some other time...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7EtjfwvvtRLE846ryJpoTwqrzxQyMaf5Rk570"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"bagol 1209","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU91V7OtuU18uGH-CbxP_qC0JRQ6v9PhBqyEqyTOlxmGhZ9-AxM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For me, their menu offered an acquired taste. It's something you would remember tho. This was my 2nd visit since 2019.

5 years apart and the Siningang sa watermelon tastes the same. I still couldn't comprehend the taste. It isn't bad but my buds just couldn't articulate the taste.

I was excited with the crispy palabok but it turned out to be a disappointment for me. It's fun to see it crumpled as the staff pour the sauce. But honestly, there's nothing special as to how it tasted. There's so much more better tasting palabok out there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxEEk808wOVYE7L-N5yUbX04xL8Nja4vm3EWmY"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Johanna Visda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKftwl-iXqValcy3Nwvq2DFFPLU2P0P1R5u0XxAtxrOnZSSQg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was great as always. Service is 👌 we were assisted by Benedict and he was very attentive to all our needs. This is not our first time here and always happy to be assisted by the best staff. Tysm!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSVCm1r4DVTJein4q_8nbcEsKF_UZG2Tp_adfE"],"When":"2024-10-4"}]

[{"Name":"TCL32s65a Go","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlKRmpnmTbuzNLX1wn-0qtijEooVpBsG3CdDsH2r1tkejUig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"ordered baked scallops and pampano sa litik

both were drastically different from how they appeared in the menu photos---

the actual scallops meat were TERRIBLY SMALL.. Big shell but really small scallop meat... NOT WORTH THE PRICE we felt so scammed.

the pampano was good but they were so stingy with the litik... had to ask for extra which they gave anyway.  but you shouldnt wait for ur customer to request before giving the portion as promised in your menu, otherwise, it's just false advertising!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfPz9JlBxlZi63HWiKaBvUxiC6a6xnNZkkc53v"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Sandals And Shorts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnKFupYDo98wSV6T2HCYxKwG-X_HeozubJy5XxWewhtEEy_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for a late lunch and the restaurant wasn't busy at all.

The decor is simplistic yet feels elegant. The staff is attentive and recommended a few dishes to try.

We ordered crispy sisig, eggplants with eggs and bicol express. The sisig was okay because it was mostly crispy pork skins and had too much mayonnaise.

The bicol express was nice, had some 'kick' to it because of the green pepper. The eggplant with egg was cooked perfectly and not oi oily.

The halo halo was very good too.

Overall it was a nice meal and would definitely come back to try other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrT4U1e1zjs2EhSx6g6lkNcDYwmjegVyc1J7v-"],"When":"2024-3-5"},{"Name":"Emilio Dal Poggetto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0kBT-5HXNnedR1gFXD3fmOZY3PtO7pHgQQx-F0YEAIFTEYqY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Easy going place, nice staff good food. Not to much crowded and fast to serve. A restaurant where to go when you dont want fastfood but dont want also to wait too long for food. Right prices for quality and quantity","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4cr-3OqZORHWlrgEf-t_E_ci5FCVOBLPs_JcM"],"When":"2024-6-25"},{"Name":"John Bart Lovern Dumalag","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUO3e6mNjjQwBJxf-zWVgw1YsbrOSw5GI539A2Tl-y5FZ0xAOui=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there coz we were looking for a resto with an on-going promo with one of my credit cards. There were a lot of customers when we arrived, but we were still able to sit right away. After placing our order, we waiting for around 15mins before they were served. Food were good, and my companion like the food that we ordered. It was actually too much for the four of us (di malakas kumain yung mga kasama ko) so we ended up taking out the food that we were unable to consume that time. Recommended resto especially if you can avail their promos coz prices of their food are kinda expensive (pero sulit naman).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnId-rHh95DYq10tkM7GOOXSQafxLWmttplpaz"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Jemay SJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiM-NRiM6bvmhPshv2v0rIDVH339muVIqzzqRt6AKFeuWTt_nehw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mesa is our go-to place for some Filipino gastronomic delight. I love their Laing 2-ways and their crunchy sisig.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRw9kldcjyvHEp7xL3vhNIs7KrDmhf1cUrgN7p"],"When":"2023-12-26"},{"Name":"April Sasan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPe62bIVsj_OXXEyCfqOJIZg7JYvsMtjkTon9qICzRoMNf3oX3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ambiance is cozy and very Filipino :) You can see the outside of the mall in its strategic location at Pedro Gil Wing. Food! Tastyyyy! Ordered sinigang na Salmon, Salted Egg Shrimp, Sisig and Green Mango Shake :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arnold","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWF4MIUHMb9UwqGH4YLfi9f2gaVugJVVIAEjOk9YPtZMHadmp8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came for dinner and wanted to try a grill. The serving size was good but it was served cold. Maybe they wanted to bring all dishes out at the same time but a little bit of planning in the kitchen would help.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elmor Dela Torre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIjQL5nVOBqlktg_hwA261pF906qgv-K3a97ID0m6nlWhbvp4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Took to-go pancit. Staff is fast and efficient, alert. While waiting for my food, I was quickly seated and served chilled water! What more if I dined in? Wifey would be happy for the pasalubong. Thanks Mesa.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlsZr69U2efkpRWOJU-Tt0XHf5m9429Q49QDx5"],"When":"2022-11-4"}]

Real nice, native "Eatery", with Karaoke.
Offering local, affordable food.
Good quality and taste.

Service is outstanding, comparing to food-chains. Employees really give an lot of real attention to their customer.

"SERVICE" is not an bad word in this place. Nobody is busy texting all the time, but busy doing an great job comparing to best Europe standard.

You needn't wait for anything.

It's an 100% recommendable place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOej4hYXsQYvtGnyccqq-R81kDI0_U1ZClbh1J5"],"When":"2022-8-17"},{"Name":"Mark Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSe9eKZ-shoosGHfkxw-BrHVndRN1v3zD34YyVPuRGtrC_z-9j=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot, afternoon or evening, and we loved the outdoor patio, cold beer and wonderful staff. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Netie Perez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1Wth9soipOm_CsbHKY1IC1IYg7-1T_E37iY3Br7cLShqaJdtKDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been avoiding Wildflour restaurants because of a previous bad experience at their BGC branch. However, today's dining experience proved to be a redeeming arc.

Starting with our assigned server, Pei, who was the most remarkable and attentive person you will ever meet. Both my husband and eldest kid have food allergies. As soon as this was mentioned, she radio-ed the kitchen, and discussed whatever was used in the preparation of our orders. The other servers were also very helpful with even the little requests we had.

As for the food, everything was delectable and served on time. The price point seems fair, given the taste, presentation, and restaurant atmosphere.

We will definitely visit this branch again. 🥰","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNt_NU75BhAXpZu9wsVVZFBJj_Im4PFXv5sCJoQ"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Russ and Vir","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVj10eGRz6rbBAcAgD1i8TySSAiWXXEd47I4YWpjQu1VVpXh_EP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends and I dined here recently, and we had a really enjoyable experience. The staff were quick to respond to our orders, and the food arrived faster than expected, which was a nice surprise.

The Chicken Piccata was excellent—definitely one of my favorites now. We also ordered from Little Flour Bakery and had it delivered to Wild Flour, which was super convenient and a great option if you want to try more from their menu.

Looking forward to trying their steaks next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrKlIXsE3UmvPlClItgabwNpy6EkpckHGitVWG"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Norman Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU56fM6wa-lJciOgjIs-rz7DoGZ8P1Qk885NUdWeYv_XrykmJkr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food was great. The braised beef was tender, the risotto - flavorful. The chicken was juicy. The calamari was light and seasoned just right. Serving size was fairly generous. Most items could be shared.

Service was quick. Note that prices are a bit on the high side (for me).

Staff were fairly attentive, but there were moments where it was difficult to get their attention, or nobody was monitoring our area.

Atmosphere was alright. The interiors were nice, but the setting felt a little cramped considering the price point.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzfdOXV3L3btcLB8v-KbxPP4jHTlq-A6aWTABA"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Chris Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_eNRiaRD27NSu-jocxwtszouJiqYswmwEkx1XAVEnpFQ00Y-b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Let’s be real: the food quality just isn’t there. The best item is the freshly baked bread appetizers, everything else is low quality ingredients with good presentation

This looks like an impressive date spot because the prices are high. You do not want to bring your friend here, it just doesn’t make sense

Ambience: it looks cozy in the pictures, but the restaurant is allowed since it’s located inside the mall. The acoustics is terrible.

Service: below average","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNay8H8_TeKVdwcMHUhw8zC7uClZ8ITvJPF5f3S"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Helen Samonte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOMKTSCl-TKfcpi3JraCKILiJ8GbLjeNLhoP9419egsP9Grw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a very sumptuous dinner. We made the right decision to order steak salad, fried calamari, roasted organic chicken and egg pie. Everything was delicious. Great job to all the crew (from the kitchen to the dining area) for making our dinner a satisfying one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIc1OxXQEPy3QJIWnedbxDT0klTYnFWD9j-xN4"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Alexander Unterköfler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_yVAooqA_yXsI9q_pJCN1NHUFqXSl6tF1lgnJf7_nou_OI48=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great restaurant with outstanding service. The waiters are really very attentive and unobtrusively friendly. The dishes are very tasty and the plates are beautifully presented. The restaurant is very fairly priced. We will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOl1LaNSW-1yntPpVow1FecMFh9uoYkE6PXamLp"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Princess Princess","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1V8huUfPuF71_pDoth_XuDn8utlKJRTGuIUMqxnU-h-5Yu8o8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Celebrated my birthday here! Staffs are accommodating and the food was good. Thanks to EWB we were able to get 50% off in our total bill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMybv7rj7E_Fi65tbh2ZmbYS6-BoVnNFasj5-nP"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Warren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ4JtdjIfYreenwFieOaUM07lwyUb0_C6eTS3Q0WmLSHjVYac1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had dinner here at Wildflour, via walk in and did not wait. Ambience and table set up was really nice and fancy. Food was also okay could be better for it’s price (but then it could be also because of our palate), we tried their Buratta Cheese and Tomatoes, Avocado Sandwich and Roasted Chicken thinking it was good for 2 but the servings were plenty. Their drinks were also good, they had some promos for beer and wine that time but we did not try it. Waiters were very attentive and offered us a larger table for our orders when it was getting full. We had the sandwiches to go and their take-out bag looked really nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6ovTSj2-MO7xGURp75Wd7RCooY0s0VUEkNNsD"],"When":"2024-4-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lyn Enriquez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAnBXI9-S1gREL_HV-neEH5hNV0k3_p3VH0ESg2ABFMTjLjsM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Dragon roll is the only okay dish. Crunchy with tempura flakes on top, sweet with teriyaki sauce
Ebi Tempura disappointing since the shrimp they used is frozen not fresh, small pieces and not worth the price.
Pork Katsudon nothing special.
Also we’re celebrating our son’s birthday but they said they only give out complimentary cake to those with reservations (walk in lang kami). Don’t understand the difference, we ate here before with reservation, but we didn’t tell them of our friend’s birthday until we arrived and got seated, but they gave a cake then. O well, so much for not making our son’s birthday extra special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIdAZEFPfWwnGrGZgvJT9aTt3bccOwDgiW8zDr"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Sheffer Soria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdV6ShtN79DNOSVAL-p1Pu80I_f8FfJZ3SKk7aZ0D1E9ETDEy4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enbu offers an amazing dining experience at very affordable prices! While other spots may attract crowds, Enbu truly stands out for what they deliver. The ambiance feels like fine dining, but without the premium price tag. Their seafood selection is fresh, and everything we ordered—tempura, donburi set, and the rainbow sushi set for two—was absolutely worth it. We left feeling completely satisfied, all without breaking the bank. Highly recommend coming here with an appetite; you’ll definitely want to come back for more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaGvSvT4ETDY89yPJspua50svDyxiVFOt_JAv7"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Juan Mariano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrzcnCKH9YXiRxBywf_R6DbluLKRyTxLkMGJdJjNlFlkDFldO2iw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Contemporary approach to traditional Japanese cuisine. The ambiance is sleek and modern, creating a relaxed yet upscale dining experience. Features variety of dishes, including sushi, sashimi, and robata (Japanese charcoal grill). High quality ingredients, and the presentation is artful. However, some diners might find the prices a bit on the higher side. Overall, it's a great spot for those looking to enjoy a refined Japanese meal with a modern twist.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpNba62zcynhlH1-wAtq-ek6OY8DTKJDq4dal6"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Bon Francis Nuestro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsLD-D9tQfdCWGhZ7YiBVvMcOatLCPXb7iZAAStjpiuaFn7Qrqhw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ambiance is nice. Area is spacious. Servers are nice and moves quickly. Food taste better compared to other Japanese restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKi0oiuQehSdj2HCesQuGmEt4dw776IrCS71A0"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Aiqi Han","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocICCPfd8FnsB1ohixznQEof96nPEayFCAOERyQ2JTzZgJuxjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered 2 set lunches which were quite nice. Especially the oyako don , very yummy ! The eel sushi was so so cos the sushi rice had no vinegar taste , tempura was rather nice. Value for money as each set was about 900pesos only . Worthy to mention was the tofu salad cos they fry the tofu which was a nice touch! COD fish was nice too !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3xcoHPJ9THmob9q--0QsMrEZzWaZVY_k0UmTb"],"When":"2024-4-1"},{"Name":"Femia Mouso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxv20AIehVe3wEAqnl1Co04-MdFijjXpPeM7sE1GgytShbsgQi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a pleasant experience at Enbu. We dine on a weekday and it was packed. We were assisted by friendly staff and was accommodated despite no reservations, so kuddos to front staff and management. Food is typical for japanese restaurant. Beer are serve on cold glass, had some wine and sake selections. Some good options on food as well including yakitori, sashimi, sushi roll, ramen, some appetizer such as karaage, yakiniku or okonomiyaki. It's a lot nicer to eat inside this than other open restaurants in Okada.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAGepr8BPDxtf6UALzGKE5kMFGRly9qK6DcEg9"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"cute nacat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4P5lHoyhC_Ohzhb3e-Jms3L2NyZ6MGntudKMy-0JI4-wrNAMzfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Feb 2024: Long queue but we patiently waited for our turn to be seated. The place is stunning, the red lanterns really added to the classy ambience. The tables are evenly distributed around the restaurant.

We ordered 3 kinds of ramen, and every one of them is salty. It wasn't rich and flavorful. The Tendon is okay but the sauce is also on the salty side. The food is pricey but taste and quality is not worth it. And service is sooo slow, food arrived after almost an hour of waiting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWiHGSeQvepgt2MFgpZBLOxvsARqGCNOSewcJQ"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Theresa Mendoza (spotontheresa)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqsW-l71Rzhy8d2DYjWSwPzdGIsai08sMYRnvRNj51MkjiVCpl5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We got to seat around 2:30-3pm on Mother's Day. We ordered Eel Maki, Moriawase (5kinds), 10 pieces Kushiyaki and lunch ramen and donburi set. Eel Maki, Moiawase and 10 pieces Kushiyaki - loved them! Our fave was the Eel Maki though! By the time our ramen and donburi set came we're pretty much full (cause of all the protein). I liked my Tonkotsu ramen, Oyakodon can do better though. Ube Matcha latte was so-so. Overall food came in quick and flavorful! Would come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZQuDT3WLI42XqHp_xXTZXDn4NfFN7C21mO2zm"],"When":"2024-5-12"}]

High quality ingredients, and the presentation is artful. However, some diners might find the prices a bit on the higher side. Overall, it's a great spot for those looking to enjoy a refined Japanese meal with a modern twist.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpNba62zcynhlH1-wAtq-ek6OY8DTKJDq4dal6"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Bon Francis Nuestro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsLD-D9tQfdCWGhZ7YiBVvMcOatLCPXb7iZAAStjpiuaFn7Qrqhw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ambiance is nice. Area is spacious. Servers are nice and moves quickly. Food taste better compared to other Japanese restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKi0oiuQehSdj2HCesQuGmEt4dw776IrCS71A0"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Aiqi Han","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocICCPfd8FnsB1ohixznQEof96nPEayFCAOERyQ2JTzZgJuxjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ordered 2 set lunches which were quite nice. Especially the oyako don , very yummy ! The eel sushi was so so cos the sushi rice had no vinegar taste , tempura was rather nice. Value for money as each set was about 900pesos only . Worthy to mention was the tofu salad cos they fry the tofu which was a nice touch! COD fish was nice too !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3xcoHPJ9THmob9q--0QsMrEZzWaZVY_k0UmTb"],"When":"2024-4-1"},{"Name":"Femia Mouso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxv20AIehVe3wEAqnl1Co04-MdFijjXpPeM7sE1GgytShbsgQi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had a pleasant experience at Enbu. We dine on a weekday and it was packed. We were assisted by friendly staff and was accommodated despite no reservations, so kuddos to front staff and management. Food is typical for japanese restaurant. Beer are serve on cold glass, had some wine and sake selections. Some good options on food as well including yakitori, sashimi, sushi roll, ramen, some appetizer such as karaage, yakiniku or okonomiyaki. It's a lot nicer to eat inside this than other open restaurants in Okada.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAGepr8BPDxtf6UALzGKE5kMFGRly9qK6DcEg9"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"cute nacat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4P5lHoyhC_Ohzhb3e-Jms3L2NyZ6MGntudKMy-0JI4-wrNAMzfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Feb 2024: Long queue but we patiently waited for our turn to be seated. The place is stunning, the red lanterns really added to the classy ambience. The tables are evenly distributed around the restaurant.

We ordered 3 kinds of ramen, and every one of them is salty. It wasn't rich and flavorful. The Tendon is okay but the sauce is also on the salty side. The food is pricey but taste and quality is not worth it. And service is sooo slow, food arrived after almost an hour of waiting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWiHGSeQvepgt2MFgpZBLOxvsARqGCNOSewcJQ"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Theresa Mendoza (spotontheresa)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqsW-l71Rzhy8d2DYjWSwPzdGIsai08sMYRnvRNj51MkjiVCpl5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We got to seat around 2:30-3pm on Mother's Day. We ordered Eel Maki, Moriawase (5kinds), 10 pieces Kushiyaki and lunch ramen and donburi set. Eel Maki, Moiawase and 10 pieces Kushiyaki - loved them! Our fave was the Eel Maki though! By the time our ramen and donburi set came we're pretty much full (cause of all the protein). I liked my Tonkotsu ramen, Oyakodon can do better though. Ube Matcha latte was so-so. Overall food came in quick and flavorful! Would come back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZQuDT3WLI42XqHp_xXTZXDn4NfFN7C21mO2zm"],"When":"2024-5-12"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Evita Daan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHop4cYIy4AG80dA8o5lBRpkQArbwkym3t2Y-KdDiZ3iJxA4yEzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a Filipino restaurant. Pork sisig is highly recommended. Chicken arrozcaldo is also good. Most of the foods are sumptuous and the drinks are also delightful . It has nice ambiance and it is a cozy place to have lunch with the family. Food servings are good for 2-3 persons depending on the appetite. It is worth the try.

It has access to the casino.
The staff are courteous and fast. Service charge is included in the bill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-pnm_0j43x30sELlhqZqxlNqmm7xydkld0BKA"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Precious Pauline Pajarellano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLh3VF8MAsLB70XPdIvoJggbX2j51Y4sJr_KKFBpc868nVfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"On a relatively slow saturday night with a lot of tables available and by a lot I mean a lot see photo. We had to wait more than 30 mins for a table to be ready for a party of 3. And talked to another party who waited for an hour just to have a table even with the number of tables empty. They decided that setting up all the tables for DIFFERENT big groups before calling them would be ideal without taking advanced orders (yes I talked to most of them)🤣. Very slow for a supposed 5 star service unlike the previous staff pre-pandemic. The seated patrons in the photo are actually finishing up their meals already too so no reason for the wait staff to be busy.

10:30PM
June 15, 2024","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODrJWmLtlMIBi24SvGMjl6SMQIWlnC6dkSFgom"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Ann Daiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxePslcHQMtjOQFO6J-HTr4EQChqwtLz91NSpEAQmSdpoSr7sjAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's my go restaurants after playing casino. I loved their Kare-kare. It's pure beef meat. It's a little bit pricy for the pinoy Foods, but yeah, it's located at 5,Star Hotel xoxo. They also offered merienda in some season like ginataang bilo-bilo or binignit and banana turon during holyweek here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIQwW_A_MFlTQFjZvKmZL_0d-FfLW_WD0UbXjt"],"When":"2024-3-31"},{"Name":"Gerald Muriel (Temiatwork)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVavuOH-OSgYCJdwc2qP_Ta_-oaq93Al5rULVa4drFCvvp7TvsA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the restaurants surrounding Okada casino. This restaurant serves Filipino comfort food, from grilled seafood to breakfast favorite, congee.

One last comment: do not order their grilled seafood if it's not served on a sizzling plate, the food gets cold quickly due to the AC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNp-bph_8fJ9BCfE0IkY-VePOueuElq4l0BJNE"],"When":"2023-12-28"},{"Name":"Rolando Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaxBKBhBqanQe2XbD04XxSAIfDGlGm73xM29LrEPL7SQAfvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was good. Service was good. Obviously it's kind of pricey because it's in a casino. The ordering process is pretty interesting. Your place mat also has the menu in which you mark what you want to order and tear it off to give to your server. Pretty interesting way of ordering and convenient to be honest. I would eat here if you want to eat quick Filipino food if you're taking a break from the casino activities.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipONymRIVS-6hyAkKTFqJdWEdfnSVo0MoBbqdWwZ"],"When":"2019-10-29"},{"Name":"Norman Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU56fM6wa-lJciOgjIs-rz7DoGZ8P1Qk885NUdWeYv_XrykmJkr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Probably (arguably) the most value-for-money of the Okada restaurants. The food is satisfying, serving sizes for groups of 2 or more, with rice bowls for those in a bit of a budget. A standout for me is their sizzling tofu. Not the best location, being right next to the slot machines, but there's no smoke smell.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cyprian Bergonia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsv2SXHAPACk8nkhTz7jrugvIraefIHXT2w0xfUJAY82ZMkleexg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We only had a small order.
Lumpia was decent. A little oily.

We also got Pandan De kiapo and CoCo Leche.

We went at 10pm not too busy at all at the restaurant. But the service was very slow.

It took a long time for the waiter to get our order, even after I signalled for them.
They also took a long time returning my card and I had to go up to the cashier and it was just sitting there.

Expect long service times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKf_wPAmMuQ9Hvl3ha3yDWqQr-PckIms40PGol"],"When":"2024-2-7"},{"Name":"Hesther Fuentebella","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXymlSpbJ9BoS9fuwuijNG_rjysJ520XRh1BJ2wtAlvwL73A_A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Their service was terrible.  We were seated near the entrance hoping to be seen by staff when we call them but unfortunately, i had to raise my hand for a long time to be given attention to.  There was a confusion in our order which caused initially by a misunderstanding on our parts but when clarified, even the garlic rice took minutes to be served. Upon bill out, i had to stand up to follow up on the check out request. Will not go back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mark Anthony Cervancia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXp8wfRrCwONp45po_-RjTXZdULe6lzWciVCdxmRLJiZJewFbeTZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all, I'd like to commend Ms Corrin's attentiveness to us and others.

If I were to recommend a place to try Filipino to someone who hasn't, this place has got to be it. Amazingly cooked local dishes for a budget friendly price. Will definitely come back with friends and family soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWj2bI3K-Ti408nGYNzd5YggvtwPgxyJWzLR61"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Jonee Azucena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8I5PBm7VBInq_sO-uU85lpPHMDoeMfh77UZe5Or5C5tW4MilBrw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Value for money - the price is just right for the choices offered.

I don't find any of the dishes as memorable, but the I really like the feels of the place. It's like getting invited to that rich, distant relative's fiesta - a welcome surprise; a relaxed party in an intimate and personal space.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUEQVRafjMJE0K-vF05OWcuD31lt4PIcsOiWUa"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Jamie 87","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPE_94PEKdt80mA0sa6Hk_ts3NoU_A95m8lWm7sVTWxgqOLzjW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of you'll need a reservation. Went there early morning around 7ish as walk-in and you'll have to wait for someone to cancel so you can get seated.

Luckily, there's cancellation so we are able to try this out and experience they breakfast buffet. This place had great variety of food selection.

Must try the Angus Tapa, Bacon, Longganisa.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLIvS1qwO0sTGbY-RsGDvKDuuD508y2M9FWhfA"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Arielle Pamela Frias","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGmXOsBpOcpBlQ9OwDN9Nqt8ttawXsi8QumiSDsB5pUB02fg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Their breakfast buffet were pretty amazing! All their savory food were delicious except for the corned beef.
Their dessert station was just okay for us. Nothing special.

All in all, we will definetely come back for our post run meal❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPwsvALNA0p6wjsHyEQtyHHZsMAKKE1L6XaIZo"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"grace m","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtnousgV0h24Jdd8-L6anukF1W_HJPpWNYJpn7qs5gdtXhKKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"the BEST buffet in my opinion. at first it may not look like a lot but they have great and quality options for all their sections. they have so much meat and they are all cooked so well. they have lechon, steak, even crabs and shrimps (not the small kind either!) and they all are juicy. One thing with buffets even the best ones that cost 4k+, some are inevitably going to be dry or overcooked when it comes to their meat and seafood. Not Gueverras. They were perfectly cooked and tasty! With possibly the best and most affordable price for a buffet like this. We went on father's day (waited because we had no reservation), it was 799php and it was so worth it for all the meats, lots of sauce options, multiple soda and juices and even gulaman included. They also have free birthday cakes (and as of when we went, they didn't check and servers seemed happy to serve them anyway). The place is very home-y and is a traditional filipino house too. They have their own parking lot as well. Service is good. They do require you to wear a mask (which they provide) when you enter the buffet area. No problems with it personally, just surprising but better safe than sorry! I definitely recommend for everyone!

The only food I didn't like was their paella. The rice was overcooked and TOO sticky so it actually tasted more like chinese machang. Another things is that someone who might have allergies or prefer healthier/greener foods might not enjoy it as there isn't that much veggie options besides the salad bar and one or two dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPkcgqrO9NTXQbM3woE36_iDJAw-VqcC4oeiRD"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"Jessica Marie Lapitan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbKhGY6ozeUuy6Qcn12WYoUELodM4Ev3l0QAx3bdpwCD9YLA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a late lunch at Guevarra's last 7 September 2024, and it was a fantastic experience for the whole family. Make sure to secure a reservation before going, as it gets quite busy.

The service was excellent, and there was a wide variety of dishes to choose from. The standout for me was definitely their lechon—crispy, flavorful, and simply irresistible! The restaurant’s ambiance is warm and inviting, making it feel like you're eating at home.

With prices ranging from ₱700 to ₱800, it's great value for the quality and selection of food. Highly recommended for family gatherings or special occasions!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkHbmP1ewnbG_68t1-wJBEL3ze67gjQIIx_7rj"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Jerg Gamarcha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV77lDqkUL15u4kvGIQZ4nkUCxAElWmvKwRYqM78eTChsZIJP79=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently visited Guevara's in San Juan, and it was an unforgettable experience for my family and me. The ambiance was fantastic, providing the perfect setting for a relaxed meal. The food? Simply outstanding! From the wide variety of dishes, the traditional Filipino *handaán* stood out for me—it brought back fond memories, especially since I’ve been working abroad. It was like a taste of home I’ve missed for so long. Overall, it was a delightful dining experience. Highly recommend! **8/10**"","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTiU3rlMkFHpH0pnsWnQZwXVmTV2ZDoNj4iLdz"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"jara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCIwD5nqno4CsGVRcU7sphcN7BVDHFdCinDPrjWWcfwdV9Xd48og=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"July 28 lunch buffet at 11am for 15pax.
Secured reservation a month prior (walk-in not recommended esp if group)

We arrived around 10:45 and there’s enough parking space. The place itself was cozy and breezy (dahil gloomy din ang weather) esp when we went inside. Pagpasok palang, you’ll feel how homey the place is and staffs were everywhere to welcome guests. It was great that they placed us in Abad Santos room. Spacious enough for the 15 of us (with addtl 2 chairs pa), hindi siksikan. The washroom was also nearby.

As for the main part…the chibog, a lot of great feedback were shared here, and true enough, meats were the highlight. Not dry and super tasty. The best bagnet bacon and lechon! Lechon melts in your mouth. Even the roast beef was good. As for drinks, no free coffee but it’s just P50. Really liked their home brewed iced tea. In terms of cleanliness, i liked the way they ensure no contaminants in their food. Not only that there’s covered glass on top of the food, they also require mask, which they provide before entering the main buffet area ✨

Staffs were awesome! 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 Service at its finest. Salamat po :) Mukhang ito na ang go to buffet namin, may celebration man or just simple cravings 😅 vs other well-known buffet places. Lux na abot-kaya 👌🏼","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPjf3yidUNhWZI4hdRfqu1P06Ao5jlL5M4D8uc"],"When":"2024-7-30"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Георгий Литягин","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxoDyici3JHXiURJLc-24u-upfSe41MVbIPtzCp-lPJzn7_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quiet and cozy place with polite staff. Very attentive staff. Food are worth the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOx8BlsBRPoQedLovvrKCuBseYSJ36pajlVA0Kv"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"Meil Anthony Desales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqRda-MEVR3Wuq0uqV_2q2yqi14LHB1NQenqM7V6FqsZOWdCy1SA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food here is great especially the bread and dessert. I don't like the pasta but maybe my tongue is not meant for Italian taste for past. Their rice meals are good and serving was big enough. Their regular servings is already good for a Filipino tummy. The meat dishes are also good as well. My personal favorite is the bread with artichoke then have their free herbed bread dip on it. You can have UNLI refill for the service bread which makes the place having good value for money. If you have a BFF card you will save tons of money since they give generous discount. They also give free coffee which is really good when you have the card. The Caesar salad is also good especially the dressing and you can ask the waitress to add additional dressing for free. The biggest discount is on monday which will give you thirty percent discount for every transaction. The staffs are also giving super service, they are kind and attentive to your needs. I didnt have to tell them when i want a refill a water in my glass. They automatically refill it when it was 1/4 empty. This is a go to Italian restaurant that is worth the value on your money. Thisrestaurant is also available in other malls and if you find the other places lurking with ppeople, go here. This a hidden gem that most people don't know.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbwB_jcCtgwYHbQmYJ4wItUY5qTav1Odkk9MSM"],"When":"2024-5-8"},{"Name":"Meriam Dayao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyTQyZUFjsu5kGv_BDwRHR0jZVx4Hlzy9lLBZVu54QdzuA1ZgL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good restaurant.
Service is superb.
Food is very good like 9/10.
Location is a bit far if you will enter the MOA on the other side.
Pizza was really good and the fish filet is awesome or we were just hungry.
Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoNiG0m73TY7A5qCyXEgyqdgnJvivRRsZGh5ig"],"When":"2024-4-11"},{"Name":"Glenn Carlo Clavel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJYmzl8fgWIpdygRH67MlEz3BgJw9mFRiDW4I9x64Tr7wzpi2jxA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was so tasty. Their paella is delicious! We also had the Iberian chicken and Thanh long crab. So so good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZKPyIatD6qDlz-Bix-DynNj7ciuVj7zXmpjoz"],"When":"2023-5-28"},{"Name":"Paul Abordo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8KZiG9rXpCJl_kOx0YHTzDUbbIhLu3Z2GKUi4UUIsEa6wuWbtMw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Its a classic go to place here in Malate, it does serve Spanish food and a trio band plays while you dine. This place is great for dates, close family celebrations and friendly dinners, i will include casual meetings also. Over all its a 5 star for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyzyZ6OjtEh5tqsd9VgHs7WcpXF6ZyfOnfQ1kx"],"When":"2019-3-17"},{"Name":"Benjalyn Walawala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0hd9W0B9MPlE7G-M7Crs1BxICQjGY-2uHvD0R0DRhP8V6eHC7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant is amazing! The food tastes even better than I expected, with a unique combination of flavors. The service is top-notch, and the atmosphere is cozy and welcoming. They pay attention to every little detail, from how the food is presented to the overall ambiance, which makes dining here truly special.\n\nI highly recommend this restaurant to anyone who wants a memorable dining experience. It's perfect for special occasions, a romantic date night, or simply enjoying delicious food in a classy but relaxed environment. Don't miss out on this culinary gem; you won't be let down!","Images":null,"When":""}]

The only difference on our orders is that they ordered on a different waiter. Ours took our order the same time as theirs but our bagoong rice was only served 45 mins after we were seated. The kicker the tables around us plus our friends got their order at a reasonable time.

The food and atmosphere is great. However we felt we were robbed out of our quality time at okada because of what happened to us.

I know this maybe a one off kind of situation but these experiences tend to leave a lasting impression.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lior Bodner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnBMXkeqWwuRtjPnfn2OxPpdsUGTbEikoVxrZ2I_75FRZlsx0yEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"First time to Okada and this place looked promising.  The spring rolls were amazing 👍but then came the two dishes we ordered.  The GOONG PAD NAM was a bit off 🫤, the shell on the shrimp did not crisp enough to be edible and the shrimp tasted bland and powdery.  The worse was the TOM KHA GAI 😧(this is the dish I order in every Thai restaurant I been to).  The coconut milk was either added to soon to a too hot soup or cooked with the soup.  It separated and looked like curds.  The chicken was tough to chew, and the broth was flavorless as if watered down.  Not worth the price, can get much better Thai for less in many places in Manila.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Inside is not that big, got few tables maybe like total of 10 or 12 tables inside. They got toilet as well

Food is Great!! Small quantity serving and expensive but for us it's worth it. Because Thai cuisine has a unique taste and also the ingredients are imported and pretty much expensive to buy. I recommend the Catfish salad, chicken with lemongrass and Pad Thai, good for 2 - 3 person. I also recommend the mango sticky rice for dessert

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ian Pastorfide","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVmtnbsxCgBbqY0tp-KJL-9vLzFgqjdOxk5j_LUaDuUocuwt62=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to Shi Lin on a Saturday noon to have a family lunch. Fortunately, the place was still uncrowded when we arrived. Service crew was very attentive and approachable right from the get-go.

Here’s a rundown of what we have ordered.
We had the Braised Beef Noodle for out soup which tastes very rich and has a powerful kick in it. For the dumplings, we tried their original Xiao Long Bao which I find very appetizing. Might say that I find their XLBs way better than those of other Chinese restaurants so far. Spicy Shrimp and Pork Wonton live up to its name with right amount of spice. We also tried their Char Siu Pork Bao which I personally like since the meat melts in my mouth and has this very sweet and savory taste that comes with it.

For the mains, we got the Spicy Spare Ribs and the Cantonese Style Fish Fillet. Both dishes were very delicious. The dishes were seasoned and were really tasty. Of course we had one of their rice to sum it up.

Milk Tea tasted authentic and really up to our liking since it not sweet. Green Mango Shake was decent. I was curious about the Crimson Berry and gave it a try. It was basically a raspberry drink kind of thing which was sweet, cool and refreshing.

Shi Lin is a must for Chinese cuisine lovers. The best Chinese resto I been to so far!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqb418wVKVcPNGxNsghFcZrkNyXmmQLnrTJg-u"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Samuel Carlos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVowc4LiL6s2FZeam7MnVvyrfIKKTnnY4df81PoypSSNMhiCeTN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Found a strand of hair in their crispy sweet and sour pork(which they suggested us to order). It was inside the breading of the pork. They then proceeded to still charge us for the dish (which we have lost desire on finishing) because "it was only one piece" with no regard to food contamination. The manager was excellent though, she greeted us properly and made excellent suggestions for our orders. She also apologized profusely and gave us a free almond jelly dessert after telling us that we still need to pay for the contaminated dish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXsqB8ndfRf1GXMpi-ue1QPWBG_xQ8eSgPDLEn"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Jean-Paul Quintana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXjuiy4R5PA8UkeygFYKLq-ZdpY0EyqMnhTNAHp1RNcb_q18s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service and excellent Chinese food here in Ayala Malls By The Bay... That Cantonese Fish was a unique explosion of flavors and textures which deserves the distinction as one of this resto's bestsellers! The pork chop noodles was so tender and tasted fantastic! This place is highly recommended as a dining spot for your Chinese food fix! 😘😘😘","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQFSTHge2AzuxxfkH7Bv91vwCpPYb0Hny2v9hA"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Thessa Dela Rosa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBn_0KOBWabJiLxxzzxnsv2U1q2Tc_wkf8kicdIIhuX6sWrH_7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Staff are very friendly, pleasant, and attentive. The place is clean and has great ambience. We also love the food, esp. the reasonable serving. The staff really served us well and we appreciate that. Will definitely come back. Maraming salamat!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMRQcBPpc3Fhna0xOM9o7tmy3YsKCXGNqVTYR3s"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Bea Katrina Bautista (Bey)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtXznyppje-pmloG1DqNa6SZbx2930ivs8vf3dsq5xkm70bBzvwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved our experience here! Mabait staff, generous servings, price is reasonable and remarkable service. Hindi din super crowded so mabilis lang magka seat. Fave namin was the braised beef - we asked na mild spice lang and they delivered really well! Xlb is exceptional as always and the chicken sa fried rice with chicken chops was super malambot!! Will def come back! 💖💖","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyeTXZDkOW8_FuK6eTuK_KeNPPKprhQYddDgDF"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"rhyan tiangco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTpoPEkV-FN74yWKfdk9xrEadhqC7yKpY48ntAky0Wklm90LU5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is good, staff are helpful and very friendly.
Ordered shrimp and pork shaomai, the best! Regret not getting 2 orders. I thinj it has a bit of soup also. A must order.
Xiao long bao is ok for my taste.
Pork char siu bun is good as well. But I think I like a little bit of sweetness.
Fried pork asado with condensed milk dip is good as well. I think it is better without the dip.
Will definitely go back to this branch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3L5H2woPTtTw_xtWAE25b2uS7uhQjyRIufzHo"],"When":"2024-4-13"},{"Name":"Laura Abutin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQ8xqhBpEN13Ti4ixNEIsdstEDHQ5UtwtCMRJGlwOjaAsJcV8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Xiao long bao was really good. Something you'd go back for.

Other stuff we ordered was Beef soup , porkchop with fried rice and spicy spareribs.

Soup was a bit salty for my liking and the some of the beef chewy.

Fried rice was okay but Porkchop was really challenging to eat. Like ready-your-floss kinda challenging. Overall taste was okay.

Spicy spareribs was okay. Not that spicy but the meat was soft.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNO8rQg739iGqfS6Z5QZk8d5I4vNUhy6MY6A-w"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Joiichi Oda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLGtaHvxN7OQf1dOKvr4Rq60v4b8LfnieUhBLPsKtuVFp1Eh_E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is crazy good for reasonable price!
Staff (Theo) is grest too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWBafSyJsXQdrdQ6P7cePGPL7LEM_CGj7K39KA"],"When":"2024-10-11"}]

This exclusive dining lounge and bar provides a serene setting for guests to indulge in a leisurely dining experience. The menu showcases a diverse range of global cuisines, meticulously crafted using only the finest and freshest ingredients. The extensive wine selection and imaginative, delightful cocktails further enhance the culinary journey. The service is devoted and warm, while the ambiance exudes an air of refinement and sophistication. Silere Manila serves as an ideal sanctuary, allowing individuals to retreat from the city's commotion and savor a remarkable meal with loved ones.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gerald Robenta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNcAfQ7rL5g9asQRhBu-UAN8uT6q26uHgBwG4UcowRLNuzi8E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There are also a lot of wine options to choose from where most of the uncles in the family took advantage of. The ambiance of the place will make you feel comfortable and relaxed. I'm recommending this to my friends and colleagues.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Princess Buenavista","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXN5dkTo8dOLfSYyHAcH966bAKXBJ3jyydL1goyqpde0IWaa34D=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We celebrated my daughter's bday here and we all had fun. The place has enough space to gather many visitors. Overall, highly recommended for any events!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Casey Gayoso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2uifZECXHTCJl08SKjTsR38OuV-0thnZrL4PT7TJf98RXyhE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Silere Manila: A Luxurious Retreat with Exquisite Cocktails

During my recent visit to Silere Manila, I was absolutely enchanted by the exceptional experience it offered, particularly when it came to their delightful cocktails.

Nestled in the heart of the city, Silere Manila seamlessly blends modern sophistication with timeless charm. The interior design is stylish and sleek, creating an ambiance that immediately made me feel at home. The staff members were warm and welcoming, adding to the overall inviting atmosphere.

The rooms at Silere Manila are a testament to elegance and comfort. Impeccably designed and tastefully furnished, they provide a peaceful escape from the outside world. Every detail is thoughtfully considered, ensuring a comfortable and indulgent stay.

The culinary experience at Silere Manila is a true delight, with a particular highlight being their exceptional cocktails. The bar boasts a diverse and impressive menu of expertly crafted concoctions. Each cocktail I sampled was a work of art, bursting with unique flavors and imaginative presentations. The bartenders showcased their skill and creativity, making the experience all the more enjoyable.

What truly sets Silere Manila apart is its exceptional level of service. The staff members go above and beyond to ensure that every guest's needs are met with professionalism and care. From the moment I arrived until the moment I left, I felt genuinely valued and attended to.

In conclusion, Silere Manila is a hidden gem that surpasses expectations. It offers an unrivaled experience of elegance, luxury, and impeccable service. Whether you're looking for a relaxing getaway or a place to enjoy exquisite cocktails, Silere Manila is the perfect destination. I highly recommend Silere Manila as a testament to exceptional hospitality and remarkable cocktail creations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pinath Waity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocILDX7MfzZLgGTFA-pLBILwaE25iz1wJqzh7eAP01P9283wQh8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you would like to enjoy time with someone who are so precious with you to allow them experiencing fine dining in a livelier ambiance, bring them here. Service is outstanding, you will not have a second thought when people respond to your needs.","Images":null,"When":""}]
