user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Leony Cherry “DgreatVenturer” Perito","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXR6K4uk6yHnY3FlpS1BB0EBROHYLvkEcYtMPcP-ibNg83QkU8y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"So today I decided to bring my family here to celebrate my birthday and since we missed eating Crab with aligue (crab fat) this is the place I decided to bring them.
We aren't supposed to end up in this restaurant but since it rained we had no choice but to park in front of their restaurant.

If only we had an option to look around, maybe there are other places that have reasonable paluto and seafood prices.

The food experience was okay. They didn't exceed my expectation for the crab, but i loved the squid Calamares. I actually enjoyed that one. It was tender not rubbery, so it was easy to chew and swallow.

The price is what shocked me. I was expecting to pay around 2 to 3k, but we ended up  paying just the same price of the food. Here are the breakdowns:

1 Kilo Crab - 950.00
1 Kilo Tahong- 200.00
1 Kilo Talaba- 200.00
1/2Kilo shrimp - 325.00
1/2Kilo pork Liempo- 165.00
1/2Kilo Squid- 325.00

Total= P2165.00

Paluto price:

Pork Liempo BBQ - 190.00
Calamares- 210.00
Buttered Shrimp - 210.00
Baked Mussel - 220.00
Baked Oyster - 290.00
Mussel soup - 150.00
Sweet chili Crab - 290.00
2 platter rice - 360.00
1.5L soda - 150.00
Service charge 5pax- 75.00

Total= P2145.00

Total expenses P4,310.00

HAPPY BDAY TO ME. NEXT TIME WILL COOK IT OUR SELF.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlI9jXBl_kSe5KBqcgqn0nNaWjQm1EuDi2DMiq"],"When":"2023-6-7"},{"Name":"Rianne De Guzman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhpMWNGvP_r2DpnNTOGjcHWEQeRTHGU6mzetyIrhm-1suIzJ08=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was baked tahong, buttered garlic shrimp and crabs and ginataang tuna. It was good and fresh but the thing is it was very expensive that I think it was not really worth it because of the quantity that I have bought in this store really did not reach the expectation. They have small servings compare with the other restaurants. I think it was good to try but it is not something you will come back for.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOEd8aRqYuuJwSeYsUVL0RfKZZjkTUKMeXR7flU"],"When":"2022-9-23"},{"Name":"Joan Zamora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGA1wjrM7oPG-dT4RLaIX8Ke2KqwWTuikaLPWHyGCQnGLkShqB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A bit expensive cooking charge. The food is cooked just right. Nothing special. Service water could be improved though. It taste like kalawang when we dine there. Parking is easy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdV8X3qAowPKTTcfql35TK9aws_euFTkTORImB"],"When":"2023-7-15"},{"Name":"Lai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnzlRBU7fTkI3MM3vGQmKWIeQUCi0Wt8L5Opw98D29gv9JkK-yxA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It's the second time that my family's dined here, and today's experience was disapointing. Three out of five dishes turned out wrong (e.g. ordered calamares; received grilled squid). They replaced it with the correct ones, of course, but it's not the ones we bought from the wet market. The way they were cooked looked like they were made and seasoned in a rush too.

If you want great entertainment and helpful/cheerful servers, do try Soupah Bowl. But do pay attention that the food you ordered matches what they serve.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3O78DIJ2bNrVSvi_MGAQh3eH0oQ0wyVhSpS7Q"],"When":"2020-1-20"},{"Name":"Scuba Buddy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIShNWG4u4JjedlJKgeXxCb0pUvepTLISytt0uPTkdtWr5R=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Enjoyed the fresh seafood and live entertainment. LGBT+2JGFGBFG etc, etc  friendly. A bit on the pricey side, make sure to check cooking charges as well as cost of seafood you purchase separately. Also buy your seafood from the vendors towards the back of the market for better freshness and maybe price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeQ5cwSuQr4nfVEK0GDRVtcosLPE-eO4GP5M0"],"When":"2020-2-23"},{"Name":"jokh1976","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKg32VqccqCqzsTsUcKuPIP0A2SDeOxA_E3X4XCbkkhniYB9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food here is what you expect from dampa or very other paluto in the area.  It’s like they have a common cookbook and this being a good thing.  Ask them for their personal parking space there if available. You park right in front.  If you have been to the more popular Claire de la Fuentes then this is exactly what you will get.  Toilet is average and usable. h( some in the area are absolutely disgusting straight out from resident evil games), this is a heaven sent after you eat here and looking for the nearest toilet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHuQXsOluDs4HxQC35KfXlADc2O9YHqEuEhdp3"],"When":"2019-4-20"},{"Name":"Corrine Llanera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKySzV_v6HWIdZihnBQZ2ZjXZAhatghAqf7yIWQDQkhasepDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We should have taken one bite and left without paying ,all the seafood we ordered was tough and chewy and the only way it was flavourful was dipping it in vinegar.

I don't even know why we stayed!

Could not believe it when we received the bill it came out to 3700 each!

This was highway robbery !
The sauce on the vegetables looked.like dirt!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jen B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwC5qQeby2UHJKdM7YP4b73-qAxDYOtHzySs3B8MrNPvN_jXwR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The taste of the food was very disappointing and the prices shocking but I can let that go because of how much we enjoyed dining in one of their  private rooms with karaoke. What was meant to be a simple birthday celebration for my mom turned out to be one of her favorite birthdays ever!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Daryl Calderon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-wMbaNacQStbOxs_CrPpjqbf30-7HMwXSXvVy7o0Ey_p-d9VX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are regular in this restaurant. This is probably the best korean restaurant around. Service is always good, and the private room is very nice. They can grill for you if needed. Premium beef is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt8S3sHyli3_v29-CdAWyPNDu4eT4HWd1GGKby"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Villamor Lacambra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVK9vEUJK5Eouqt1lDoRlVxYVBCOBCTWlnUStzqQ-n4EmWUPLFI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recommended this Kiwa Korean Restaurant to my Japanese guests and i did not disappoint them. 1 of the best korean resto in Metro Manila.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAn9mF4GnSkkHF0pZip1w9_tYwpbljSZ_BT2sq"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Kit Narciso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2W0zPuo8vg7CmLRlaNZFzkM0yK_NJz_D5xIaGz1ZM59GkK0DI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love eating here.. whenever I’m at solareImake it a paint to have a quiet and delicious meal in this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpxqspVLdG6OQO5Qho4rthNb2SH7naMPNznR_3"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"Wendy Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVBbGmzuVhRSqOBIEuDCQ8ae-L3SAjdqhEV1Z3P9Jyj5tZTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best Korean restaurant in Manila! The quality of their dishes is superb, and the attentive waiters excel in explaining the menu. Don't miss out on the fantastic desserts. While it may be on the pricey side, every bite is worth the well-crafted culinary experience. 🇰🇷🍲","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjRQsxah65fnNXWV_XITVkRf7YWrg37mbPdtQK"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"krō waque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0CXU-2TcWcpEILTUa5sUNuiRtKHXNj7JD0u5YrT5i8fYsifbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We walked in for brunch on a Sunday and were seated immediately.

Service in general is professional, almost cold, but not off-putting. Jill was helpful.

Wooden interiors provide an ample amount of warmth. The tall glass walls allow a good amount of sunlight in while you get a view of what remains of Manila Bay when you look out.

Freshness of ingredients is extraordinary, the absolute highlight of our dining experience.

Every dish we ordered, from mains to accompanying banchan, was excellent, and seasoned right. No spice or seasoning overwhelmed the natural flavors of the meats and the greens.

Spicy fried chicken was fresh foremost, plump and juicy.

Marinated beef ribs, although tender, retained enough pleasant chew to it, and were fresh.

The fried mackerel was a little downer, as although prepared well, it tasted almost either salt-cured or dried.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO_no1wJwce1n8_aRMfbjhnaXyWWTJWsk3_rQf"],"When":"2023-9-10"},{"Name":"Aritzia V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVt62u7H8tmeMJqXmr0s-OWZimFp_uZbCE7_4TKpY7aNquBbtY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The other reviews are right -- the food is too mediocre but very expensive And they only serve you 4 side dishes. Service is so painfully slow and there were only 4 occupied tables in the entire restaurant. It's hard to call the attention of the servers and you need to keep reminding them of your requests because they keep on forgetting. So much so that we skipped ordering dessert because we figured it would take another 30 mins. It's a shame because this is the only restaurant open for early lunch if you are going to catch the matinee show in the theater. Better to just eat the sandwiches and salad at the theater kiosk instead. The restaurants beside it (Yakumi, Finestra, etc) are so much more worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7FNRVjoUvQAkBbFQECkBd6hCWbujxzrtwNqPT"],"When":"2023-9-24"},{"Name":"Rebecca Sy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh38bsMTJZCYQssOy3D1NXbtrxrRPrCW0UKuXhUMD3vQ1RLmaJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has a very nice view, overlooking the sea. They also have private rooms for groups or something intimate. What I like about here is the ambiance, the service, and most especially the food. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMF1_QXzQkuwnI2eN6tmTbOlQmkfgzoaCPQMTb"],"When":"2023-6-19"},{"Name":"Dave Arreglado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqxZA7EJGP3FpAMkWK0uY796ZRmxviVRfHCm-Ql3ma_CEXZejlLw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food! Great ambiance","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaWC9j_HL2pfeYV3xp3eR6OusFK7HXRkwYbFNg"],"When":"2024-10-10"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ann M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWS9uGkxfPytc161L_x57UW5vBuedEZfvcvantMgtS6-7PKddEi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"No doubt, they have good food! I especially liked their Morty & Ella pizza which was recommended by the owner himself! I would go for their thin crust next time cause their square pizzas are too heavy for me. The flavors were good though. I would just prefer if they have a thin crust version of it.

Their weekend special soft serve was amazing as well. Would definitely go back. Just wish that they would have a bigger restaurant so that it wouldn’t be as crowded.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqVDIsGMYTrwcxCN2JItUExsOALpniVzwpTpFQ"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Eating Eater (Drinking Drinker)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJv9bh9y_Rk0A1CkPoWV6ZBfv1hPyPBtOtAOWso9FnKRUcVxG9S=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The pizzas we tried—Artichoke Spinach, Super Duper Supreme, and The WAP (White Ass Pizza)—were fantastic, with fresh, high-quality ingredients and creative combinations that made each one memorable. The flavors were well thought out, and every bite felt special. The staff was attentive and knowledgeable, adding to the overall great experience. The place was a bit cramped, so you might want to opt for takeout instead. Though it’s on the pricier side, it’s the kind of spot I’d happily save for special occasions—and I’m definitely looking forward to exploring more of the menu next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjWxmcmI8Dq3n3lF67Qhf5nDiDnq9FuF5FKRfG"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Ynna Pique","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlRrS3rNOLnByGH2FEnpaltGMvwzymzg35x_6NW6HjezLWIKjO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best pizza in the Philippines!! My absolute fave is Morty & Ella. Their sourdough crust is perfectly crisp on the outside and wonderfully soft on the inside. The toppings are super fresh and bursting with flavor. It was such a delightful experience overall. I can't wait to come back and try the Drunken Bismark pizza. Highly recommend it to everyone!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPysN3svyWS_ksXK_GXtIi5glWxq3ZevLqjnIBb"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Mimi Truong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfTy_8ZPApoX_Ug6YemPSj58jNG7WXE7yXKvgmFukUykrURcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had! Favorite was definitely the Morty and Ella. High quality ingredients and incredible flavor combinations. The crust was perfection – I usually don’t finish my crust but I couldn’t get enough of this one! Crispy on the outside, soft on the inside, and just the right amount of bite. Don’t forget to make room for soft serve.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_-RAC1VQ9hYIMHKygngbdxaegm9d5JHldMKX9"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"G A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSuh-E-7c3wPvQLEOuHbOM1Y3zKSLhalXEdSpPZWQVwIk5XA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"If you are planning to dine in at the exact opening, go earlier and reserve your seat. I was unaware they let customers in the restaurant before the actual opening, but they can’t order yet. The place was too small, so it was better to be early if you plan to dine.

Even if there are many pick-up orders and a line, the food arrived quickly. We only ordered Morty and Ella for takeout since we had no seats. The pizza was good. I can’t complain about the price because the ingredients used are of quality. I'm definitely,coming back to try the other pizzas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8CKOynNfQh8Zhb0002W8RNJRN1O6F8VH0jrkz"],"When":"2024-6-2"},{"Name":"Makati Mazz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTRp2tUk8phoMkcHG-2oMsrSh4CchKd-adcYY_0dl4907vnlY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am an Italian-American who grew up around delicious pizza in Brooklyn, NY. Believe it or not, this pizzeria in the Philippines rivals the best pizza in New York! The first time I had this pizza I thought I was back in New York for a moment. I couldn’t believe that I was in the Philippines! The crust is perfect; the mozzarella cheese is so fresh; the sauce is not sweet and raw but well-cooked and a little spicy; and real (and expensive) Pecorino Romano is generously sprinkled on top! This is by far the best pizza in the entire Philippines. In fact, nothing even comes close back in Florida! Take it from an Italian from New York - Crosta is like a dream come true for anyone in Metro Manila craving real Italian pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2dUT-vEWSauUCiHbgSTAL5k5QYdqVgPJIRMg"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Anthony Sy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIywU4uGSobX-6QSpiRU9p0IDByXy39JCPpOLXoJuPuuSmvg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Probably one of the best pizzas I’ve ever tasted. A bit on the pricey side considering its size (for an average Filipino).

The space is small so definitely expect some waiting if you go during peak hours. Nonetheless, service was fast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLGy7alGNRjEzSrhIpEuILgqTReYLixyJvyBs"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Eloise van Zuidland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwT9_m82_Ckw51xCdPWcRnJzs-Cy7dnYoWLjJwz3CNOy7jU-1zIw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I braved the rain and the traffic to eat dinner at Crosta Pizzeria as it was highly recommended by the Pepper .ph community. I went there with high hopes, knowing that they were included in the top pizzas in the world. I got Morty & Ella, and it did not disappoint. The crust was Neapolitan style but a bit more oily. Hence, it was not dry and perfect with every bite. The pizza was topped with white sauce, generous mortadella,  pistachios, and herbs. The only letdown was the seating. People were standing waiting for their orders and to be seated. Some inconsiderate patrons who were done dining refused to leave, and the seats were very limited. They also had very interesting dessert options. I regret not ordering wine. It would have paired well with the pizza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5PQgLIt0hKpO6iQLpfUO8DHc8SfSArrSID6Hn"],"When":"2024-6-29"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"cute nacat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4P5lHoyhC_Ohzhb3e-Jms3L2NyZ6MGntudKMy-0JI4-wrNAMzfQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Aug 2024: It's been so long since I last ate here. But the order taking is still the same. There's no menu to choose from. The waiter will lead you to the window in front and from there you will choose the ingredients for your dish. Their popular dishes are kikiam, yang chow fried rice, fried sipa, nilasing na hipon and stuffed squid. All still tasted the same but the size is much smaller now esp the stuffed squid. They accept CASH payments and GCASH.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgrIFdk73eQdQNlByB7rbN9PxtBmJI79v0odoe"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Rich L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFLuZX3sCj7ao8W3f12u61PDs1ycyFdNeD0SNjzv9l7Ey0kIc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wok Inn Restaurant is a hidden gem! Their sipa is a standout—like a lumpia but wrapped like dumplings and fried to crisp perfection. The shell soup is another favorite, full of flavor and warmth. The kikiam is a must-try, and my all-time favorite, the stuffed squid, never disappoints. There are plenty of other dishes to explore as well. The food is not only delicious but also very affordable, and the service is impressively fast. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM_n7FA5tqswFGfxQtdIIyxpV2Rahiub-1jVxB"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Eric Ly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1ds2xUwCeYUeamvFc553p_69q8OdxmcVqhy4xzWN89XR8zthwgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food itself is well priced for what it is, with a few caveats.

Yang Chow Fried Rice: This was served lukewarm, like it was fried well in advance and sitting for a while before it was served to us. Wouldn't order again.

Sipa: I love these and would order them every time.

Buttered Chicken: Flavor was good, but 1 of the pieces was very raw. Luckily I saw the blood running into the plate before I bit into it, so I opened it up and yep, raw chicken. The other 4 pieces were cooked through as they were thinner. I showed it to the server and she agreed that it was raw, showed it to the cook who I saw gave a little gasp lol. I expected the dish to be comped for free, or at least discounted, because 20% of the dish was inedible, but nothing was done about it, barely an apology.

Chili Pork Spareribs: This was decent. I was expecting salt and pepper pork but it wasn't that.

Overall, food can be hit or miss, but fair at this price point. The way they handled the raw chicken incident was a turnoff for me though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1xKh3_5M60l7jewiUsIuw46ARB7fWntMrXEPC"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"FIL Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIM2CG7lpwozwg_6i4tQedqmXS9Wx8dWcjv9FB058j9CmWJhw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"No menus presented instead you have to choose ingredients that you want and how you prefer it cooked as per the staffs suggestions. Ordered the Sipa, Kikiam, Tendons which i thought were mushrooms & the Stuffed Tofu. Sipa was perfectly fried but the filling had a mild off smell to it. Filling was porky soy sauce sweet like asado or hoisin but mild. Kikiam was mild savory sweet & flavor can be  dominated by the same sweet-soy thick sauce  that came with the sipa.  Stuffed tofu was like braised tofu in mild oyster sauce with the stuffing, having a little smell, adding savoryness to the sauce still, tofu flavor dominated and was accented by its sauce. Finally the tendons in a fragrant spicy savory sauce stood out for me because of its chewy rexture and umami. Service was quick like old school Chinese restos same with the atmosphere which made it feel homy. Photos were taken post consumption.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-bb4ME6V564_dQZfK2FuQ-sYoiYx8nyEQTrIU"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Annalyn J Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9bvNxEiKqtiwTGDkwGn2KS0XVEvcUaD5wHZoxDLcOpoDg-2_x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything is tasty here, food is affordable too. Wok Inn hasn't changed through the years. I am glad there's this place in Manila. You need to go to Malate because they don't have any other branch.
Must order: Sipa, stuffed squid, garlic with kang kong etc","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTooML-agUQOW2D48ixXIxIPH-zFaQQsqACwc"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"pochay cruz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWh_vdlryfJs7dno2RgVVK9miXiukCLXjAX5iLJuh0mDLuoa9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Loved the stuffed squid and veggies. Sipa dumplings not for me though. And toilet should be improved and kept clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeqoTXaFScHcKg3hHI2ZViRFb7X4qllPnryxvm"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Carlos Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVl9-U82xQSi-83LmSlTFfTGlPca87NmSLYyS6SUe3V02TLd1AyHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Dropped by for a quick meal. Haven’t been here in ages. Surprised they didn’t have a menu anymore and you just tell them what you want.  Stuffed squid is still superb, tiny though. Salt and pepper pork was good, loved how the fried rice was full of Chinese sausage. Sipa was not as tasty a previous though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_qIC69ULapYdjWnLiKkTwvim0a41rGw9dNXT5"],"When":"2023-11-8"},{"Name":"А. С.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKRxz2AFiWJ4_t6rvn__r0uK3sIHachociWFELMFlsvAAvBwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have no idea why there are so many good reviews here.
1) The rice with vegetables is not tasty at all, and for some reason sausages have been crumbled into it. From vegetarian dishes there is tofu, but it was fried on not fresh oil, so it was covered with black coals. Noodles taste not bad, but greasy. As a result, you can eat it, but you do not get pleasure from the food here.

2) The waiter wiped the table for appearances sake.

3) The biggest disadvantage is that they don't give you a menu, but bring you to the raw food and ask you what you want. It's like I know what they can make with it. There's a menu, but they don't give you one. May be you should insist, I don't know. It's kind of a weird restaurant.

4) The prices of the dishes are taken from their heads, something was calculated more expensive by 30 pesos than the official price, something cheaper by 10 pesos.

In my opinion, it's still eatable, but it's better to find a restaurant with more transparent pricing and better food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTm2RNuzkuQ3_0FdDno4o1zB5YEUOC1wcmoNSl"],"When":"2023-12-8"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Karam Devnani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpF58evjqCKY3LHkOGOxQWapl3TbnhfMycwn6Kr_u9qLAP4EpW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of my favourite Filipino restaurants. They are very creative with their dishes and modernized Filipino food. This is not the place to gonif you want traditional Filipino food, but they definitely did it justice. My favourite is the lechon oyster sisig. It is so sinful but just so good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbH9cEiM3PRCUtw7V_-tRXhpe-H9Fc4lb5qZWr"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Joed Panopio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC3uCkLJZ4klzBcHxOEh28bJrzdlZ7ZErba-66jxdYiFZTEUch=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The attention or service provided by the crew or staffs are excellent that reflects the kind of Management they have headed by the Operations Manager...I personally talk to the Operations Mananger giving him my highest commendation to their branch at the ground floor of Conrad Hotel in MOA.  Likewise, the foods recommended by their crew are excellent.  The taste of the foods are all great. This dine in restaurant is highly recommended at all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuXYf_v17ZlFbd5PSVTNUsSiyC6xdsvp3wsCd2"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Krantzl Kaneko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsOD8okEOFVmonljMJB67US7zAeLI3nnba2sVyHRbYH5hYpNab=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place to hang out with friends and kids. Very nice Filipino food. The Palabok and Gising Gising were my favorites. Very cute cocktails too. Nice interior and tableware. It seems like they renovated their menu from the last time I ate there in 2018.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHTfhuc8eoKdj4N-zQi2atdyo265EMLPRqe_Da"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Joyce Corrine Cuerbo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4bDDRPO7YfCToe-yFuwR2eSyoaOSw_YQFXzUNxitdQngwGDdv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and very attentive staff! Absolutely loved our experience. Definitely a spot to go back to.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPt0XYborECPFOAgyhChsIjUg5si7-V6roLwJ-K"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Max Brand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_06FfBhLT3JzuHRScxh9sNuc318znw0RI2b6KM1Czx1Xkaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was our first foray into Filipino food and we were more disappointed than pleased. To be fair, every item we ordered was really tasty, but most of them felt like an invitation to a heart attack. Just too greasy, especially the corned beef dish. It was 80% just fat! Even the watermelon salad tasted greasy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN90lE2bUH9tIvx47Dv14RLupsj0BPMiugaQFLH"],"When":"2023-7-9"},{"Name":"Mikhail Tiu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcw-NOaX3S_kTbn1gh3XBMviFm-CCHQrsdxJ0vuPKCrFkWtumy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant offers Filipino food with a twist. Most dishes have the classic Filipino way of cooking or taste but they elevated them and made them into something new and interesting. What stood out was the mangga't bagoong with chicken wings since you wouldn't find this combo elsewhere. It is a good way to enjoy classic Filipino dishes in a new way.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZwEAtFgmUW4IPUsxru0UWnT52_ZFOffAoVuTg"],"When":"2024-3-14"},{"Name":"ARBN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI91quIZyFx7RE23ebBhQKPSqmmJV2ao298jSVBpvY8m_hxCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Be careful not to think this place serves traditional or typical Filipino cuisine. On the contrary, the place has been renowned among locals as a place to sample Filipino food with a twist - a big twist, if I might say so. The ambience is befitting of the quality and style of food they serve - fancy, different, yet somewhat still homey.\n\nThe Filipinos food which you may have been accustomed to becomes out of the ordinary, and is not very typical of the cuisines. For most dishes, the only thing that perhaps made them Filipino was the name given - the combination of spices, ingredients, taste, look and even manner of serving actually becomes alien to most locals. Nonetheless, it has become popular to most Filipinos, at least ones who can affors the place, so it may still be worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNuNAhQNWm4s_bnQB7inkxxQDPQl4elU8ISzCbQ"],"When":"2024-1-26"},{"Name":"EatsForYou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1cSyPXx9IRs_f4GFo4CNf6yw5LE-_B6gNt050naDoIFRPPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Usually I go to their branch in Kapitolyo, but tonight I decided to bring some colleagues to the S Maison branch. It was the first time to try the restaurant for most of them and I’m glad the quality of food is very consistent. Serving portions were just right; I think I even over ordered. My favorite is sizzling sinigang and garlic baby squid. Everything was great! Even the garlic and onions are flavorful. Eat them! :) Could improve on service though. Order taking was not seamless. There was a miscom on the drinks. Server said all shakes were unavailable so we ordered juice but still mango shake was served instead. Overall a pleasant and enjoyable meal after a long day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6aA3A5KgdfNnwYW-hK4YPD1EC1x-lRkmcoNbJ"],"When":"2023-10-28"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Marlene Po","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFKbGFQ8vg_qnCYrTUL9CF1v0RQBw4Q_WVqpfssKcIIZwDnOuC2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's been a while since my last visit to Sarsa.  Thinking of a Filipino restaurant to bring balikbayan friends, my niece suggested Sarsa and the food did not disappoint. Everything we ordered was delicious. Their PALABOK ESPESYAL  is he best I've tasted, better than Via Mare and Milky Way. The sauce was delicious, and not starchy, the noodles al dente.  And the toppings - Longganisa, shrimp, chicharron, smoked fish, squid, egg . Heaven! Writing about it makes me want to go back now.

The 3 way pork sisis was equally a winner, as well as the laing and kinilaw. We ordered the right combo.

The only slight disappointment was the chicken breast Inasal, which in fact we did not finish to the bone.  Perhaps the thigg part would have been better.

Out dessert was leche flan - which had the consistency of yema.  It was too compactvand sweet, chuckloads of condensed milk . We wish we had ordered the turon with ube ice cream - saw our neighbor's order of it!  But we were too full for another dessert.

Service was reasonably acceptable except for the peppermint tea ( not complicated, right) which we had to follow up from 3 waiters about 4-5 times.

Music was a bit too loud , an issue in restaurants here.  So the music plus occasionally boisterous diners - not a relaxing atmosohere.  But ...

All in all, a very satisfying meal for everyone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhT13WZ5AlEzn8BuaXkngxQduZ6g8GC0ocXiiG"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"andi j","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPYGNl1C_osLW1VJw6aNkN2VRAtDVkCBEUIBCs38Smc4Ae8kM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My go-to for Ilonggo food. Truly gastronomic experience every time I come here — I am a big fan of their menu. Love love looove their palabok ala negra, inasal chicken, 3 way pork sisig, and sizzling kansi (make sure to get the sizzling bec the kansi soup version was kinda meh, not like the ones I’ve tried in BCD or even Patpat’s).

Chef Jayp’s personality really echoed throughout the room, ambience is giving surf & shack, with local pieces and furniture here and there. I am impressed with how it all came together 🏄‍♂️

Place could get so busy that service could take long but if you go past peak hours it has quite a relaxing environment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPNsibqKfGH-iWi2bhCNfGUhGoLx1qj6HEBb0o"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Joshua Cruz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL71OMuAUW1PDSrhkBh2iKR4eNQVfh5lm_qSArDGzLjrSkLAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I think the bad reviews here are factual. Here are some highlights of our experience in Sarsa:

1. RESERVATIONS 3/5 - They’re very accessible via Viber and they easily confirmed our reservation. However, we were placed next to the door. There were 2 separate couples that did walk-ins, but they got the table with the booth. We did asked to be placed somewhere else, but we still ended up being near the door. During our meal, two flies keep flying around our food.

2. FOOD 3/5. We ordered Chicken Isaw, Molo Soup, Palabok, Sizzling Kansi, Tortang talong, and 3-way Sisig. In general, the food was ‘lasang malinis’.

(1) Chicken isaw (2/5) was dry, leathery, not juicy, no flavor except it was charred.
(2) Molo Soup (3/5) was served beautifully but Maam’s hastened presentation put the dish off; I like the idea of fried wanton with the soup, however, it went soggy afterwards.
(3) Palabok (2/5) was creamy but I dont know why. Maybe that was the twist? It lacked saltiness from the sahog which shouldve balanced the dish. The noodles used were thick since it was ‘pansit luglug’.
(4) Tortang talong (2/5) was your traditional tortang talong but they tried to
upscale it by placing fried alamang on the side and a minute amount of crab meat at the center of the torta.
(5) For the 3-way Sisig (2/5), the 1st third of the meat was boiled, 2nd third was fried and last third, I think, was buttered. I did not like the fact that I was that trying to be very careful with my bites/chewing just because some meats were heavily fried which gives the pork a hard/rock-like consistency.
(6) Sizzling kansi (5/5) was the only remarkable dish I had. I love that it was reduced so the reduced cream was rich in beef, broth and asim. Kahit ito na lang iorder ninyo at kanin.

I think I marked it low due to my expectations that the meals are outstanding based on articles available online. But in general, they did serve the food in the most honest way without any tricks or surprises.

3. VALUE FOR MONEY (2.5/5) - Yes for the experience. But I wont recommend others from going here. I will ask them instead to go to Gerry’s for Sisig and Palabok, Manam for Isaw/BBQ/Skewers, or Locavore for food with Filipino twists. We spent 3.2k for the whole meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcmS9EWrv4valNVS7yt7iGr23QdO4nJpZGZnJV"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Kat CM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnFdDpBQOqXAOsb7fhkpDXfqfxLRO8A19KulX0x1fvGrENmCw2qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is easily a 5 - one you’d recommend to family and friends.  Standout is their crab tortang talong, sizzling kansi and kinilaw.

Service is okay. We were able to get a reservation. We ordered tanglad iced tea and it took long to arrive. Better if they could serve the appetizer first before the heavy meals without customers having to request it.

Interior is nice, well-lit and ventilated/airconditioned. Just hard to talk to each other perhaps because of the noise (place is packed on a Saturday).

Overall, we will be back! We loved the food after all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPz7of5few7TRe6mTxegwp4yKKEJQYfzhgnkJ_9"],"When":"2024-5-11"},{"Name":"Jayme B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-J9wIvcLY2JMXcmV1kvzvpiuQ3xRZOzyAuuVoFO-MAk4l5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sarap balik-balikan Bacolod comfort food! All is good! Beef empanadas and piyaya are a must try. Discounted cocktail drinks available 2pm onwards. Service is commendable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJ_eRqYLvHonfMZ-n3ec-PduNekJNMLshCFi68"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Jace Navarro (Jace)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI19rM97KT-gBlI5946dYd0YiZ1cuzZhr87BEj7m0M42QRIl38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I expected a lot for Sarsa. Sadly, it didn’t met my expectations.

3 Way Sisig- It has a distinct taste which tastes like corned beef. Flat lang yung flavors nya. Wala siyang body.

Isol- Gulat kami sa size. Masarap sya. Brined to perfection.

Laing- Nothing grand about it.

Garlic Rice- Decent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1Cemp7ibugeozja5fX4NHL9QqCPHEuDQ55ZhF"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Jeff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9AVwimigMpU91SohBbR9pk96tRU8W1upnBXsbeUmmsYWqoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fun, locally inspired dining area with a tropical-surf vibe. Great food, especially the beef empanadas. Craft beer paired well with all the food flavors. Service was adequate, not unfriendly but not warm or engaging either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4Y4lWyueAG3gi7B1Hy6WpakumuZkLol3lccfR"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Jem ____","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq-T47Sepcx73wrHUaxm3ImrkEs2znZlmNB-_crrb3fQZS9tMD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got to experience and understand why there is a lot of hype surrounding this place. Excellent, well balanced food all around, tastefully designed dining space, and warm staff to top the experience off.

We grabbed a few drinks to start our lunch: I had the Sago’t Gulaman and my husband had the Lemongrass. First thing that hit me was that the Gulaman wasn’t overly sweet. I enjoyed the fact that I could taste the herby notes of the grass jelly. For our first main meal, we had the Palabok. Again, well balanced. Chicharon isn’t the only thing I taste, I was able to appreciate the marriage of flavors that all the ingredients brought. Next, we had the 3-Way Pork Sisig and Inasal Paa. Both packed a punch with flavor but not to the point where one would get “umay” easily because of the excessive oiliness. We ended our lunch with the Halo-Halo and Piaya. The Halo-Halo was just like the gulaman- not overly sweet so that you can enjoy all the diverse flavors going on in the dessert. I also love that they were generous with their serving of Ube ice cream as well as the Ube syrup. The only real anomaly in all the dishes we enjoyed was the Piaya. I enjoyed the fact that it was more plump and moist than the usual piaya, which tends to be flat and crumbly. It came with a good serving of Coconut Jam to dip it in but I didn’t feel the need only because the piaya itself was extra sweet. If it wasn’t as sweet, I would have gladly scooped dollops of that coconut jam since it paired so nicely.

Nevertheless, it was such a great experience and we felt like we only skimmed the surface of what Sarsa has to offer. We left with our tummies and hearts filled to the brim.

Pro-Tip: We came on a weekday but the place was packed as soon as the clock struck twelve. Be sure to be there by 11, right when they open.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUTXI67LdfGy2RVqMjBEO0zENdrnAeVckba5dL"],"When":"2024-4-19"}]

[{"Name":"Andrew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1IufpckcGsSDmYnfUbHO-X53y_6qOW9XVeVpPDSLMqSEpWq_C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The smell of detergent from the beer glass was so strong that I lost the taste of my food. The recommended wine wasn't tasty, and the pizza wasn't tasty either. The pasta was also not tasty so everyone in my group left it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVLiAZTUCXETuALztzZdcU-hoFGotMvEA4Ydxb"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsLFOFsKbHJVh_GUtELF-O3qBCcuzA9ka8aTJhD_-DWae8Xg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here on an Italian expat's recommendation for authentic Italian pizza, the best pizza place and Italian restaurant he could find in the Philippines (Thanks Loïc). Showed up in the early evening without a reservation but nobody cared because the restaurant was empty, and service was a little slow even when it was only half full.

Margherita Pizza, Mozzarella Bufala Pizza and Gnocchi/Gnochetta are great. Bolognese spaghetti is okay, nothing special like back home in the West or the U.S. Praline nougat ice cream is overpriced and abysmally small.

Fried Calamari was okay, the grilled salmon and spinach were good but overpriced.

The bread and olive oil dip were excellent.

I'd give the pizza a 7/10 from what I've tasted here and elsewhere, though in the U.S. I've certainly had better, though it's made by actual Italians or Italian-Americans. Still, it was good, I liked it, I'd order it again, but it seemed overpriced nonetheless. Yeah, I'll eat here again.

Spent around $197 or P10,800+ in total for 5 people and 1 child.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPqna2RWxrTcYjpUKAqHHFCX5Akl4QJ1vOhY5EI"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"Clark Kent","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJnC_cn9cTUNUAG24wRO24Wva6Z2ntVOGY2Fgmu4BXx6hZIew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Would have been 4 stars if they didn't OVERPRICE THEIR COFFEE. ITS THE MOST EXPENSIVE ESPRESSO IN THE PHILIPPINES. We ordered 2 espressos and the waiter asked if we wanted a single or double. I said double, and my companion said single. They charged P620 for the double and P310 for the single. With VAT and service charge, 2 CUPS OF COFFEE COST P1,134.60!

The food, on the other hand, was quite good. The risotto nero was outstanding.

Overall, it was a good dining experience until  we discovered the price of the espressos. No diner will ask for the menu again just to check the price of coffee. We just assume it'll be a reasonable price.

When we checked after the bill came (we couldn't believe it,  and thought it was a cashier error), we saw that P310 was indeed the price of an espresso. THERE WAS NO PRICE ON THE MENU FOR A DOUBLE ESPRESSO, (P620) FOR OBVIOUS REASONS. Yet the first thing the waiter asked was whether we wanted a single or double. Not sure if the restaurant owner knows about this practice, but buyer beware.

Hope this review helps others avoid (intentional?) overpricing by this otherwise decent establishment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5LKDRCm6vCu1gbzZA2DvF-7m_0aOnN4Tp7kgr"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Leonard Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFPXYrpNzgP9-A_2iJ3oLrNG8Ke3X5-guVwWEVHMPuamkm0uio=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here with friends total of 6 pax, had been order their famous steak for sharing, 2 types of salads, 2 types of famous pizzas, 3 types of soups (Mushroom, tomato, tomato with seafoods and quite tasty by eating with the breads) and 4 types of pastas ( I dont remember all the names and took all pictures so far as recommended by the staffs for their best sellers)

Overall the ambience are so good, so quite for gathering or for dating, staffs are friendly and pro with well manners, got some parking lot from outside and even let us in without reservation as we just pass by and decided to having dinner from here.

We will definitely visited once again~ :))","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2elqEDljGhkhVWqJvrfrLFcXvMSVu7a8o8ogO"],"When":"2023-2-19"},{"Name":"Willie Aquino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVdf-6VbKHOSQP0nWeLkfKk8ZLTRsajNSSm7GndVclgcq41VQH-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food. Professional service. Superb wine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7Nzzy2lB8ZEg1xSsgVKX2RYO77yL9WXcXX4E0"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Gio Ibarreta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-vc5dime8NbI6IN1nKCnMC6fv3fBmdokUdCih65yFb_5ix4q1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best and most authentic experiences in Metro Manila. Staff were great, atmosphere was amazing, and the food was simply delicious. Will come back for sure. On the expensive side but truly worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQIx65z56diBiG--GyAWE4-AgpxO8-h2jxUAGD"],"When":"2023-5-2"},{"Name":"Oskie Ravanera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWvWrnDBvSLZ6i7W1O3OJmp3gMChwP0Ld_kOhpIwrDMSn9AkVjhBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"By today’s standards, this is a fairly large restaurant which features a small club room for more intimate gatherings.  Can probably seat 120 persons or more.

But this is refined dining at its best.  Proper linens here.  Proper serviettes/cloth napkins lightly starched and pressed to perfection.  As they say, the ways of the “Old World” which is now a luxury.  No surprise as the owner is himself a Milanese who relocated and is now with his family in Manila.

High quality selection of fine wines.  Even the sourcing of the saffron used in their risotto was carefully done.

Their staff and servers are sharp and attentive.  And knowledgeable.  They even have a Maitre’ D on board with many years of experience.

No wonder this place is a favored place of diners who want an excellent meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaQQ5zjPHLySJm-sQjwHeM9TgptAlt_IaacJnY"],"When":"2019-9-2"},{"Name":"Alex 489","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUqqnYIClZfZsC261TRhL7dYZHww9imGKIKthTbs3cAhY_Cbo1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Complementary bread basket, parmesan cheese and olives. Bread was ok nothing special.

Seafood soup - tomato base, tasted good.

They cooked my grass fed veal Milanese in olive oil 😍 It was pan fried too - bonus points for that.

Risotto Milanese with saffron - takes time to prepare about 30/40 mins but worth the wait.

Nice staff and quality ingredients.
I’ll be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy3b3WOUhMla_-Ks7NJYBLV_nENUnVLxngdtcN"],"When":"2022-12-27"}]

Randomly walking around, we stumbled upon this diner and something about its appearance just made me want to go in and after checking out the menu, I WAS SOLD!!

They have a supermassive menu with a huge variety of meals to choose from including rice meals, sandwiches, soups, noodles and a lot more! The best part is, this place is very cheap! I had Beef Curry with Vegetables and Rice, with a bottle of water and my wife had Seafood Sotanghon and then after I finished my beef curry - I ordered a fat and delicious Corned Beef Omelet with rice! My wife had a Mais Con Yelo and altogether we spent less than 500 PHP! Filled us both up damn good!

The Nine to Six Food House is one of the best restaurants I've eaten at in Manila so far, I will definitely be paying them another visit!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJniM_-K3zVHVf7ZOUPtx76Eo2kEOApKySt-YeEEMy5k4eTrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Waitresses are attentive and the food is good! [{"Name":"Maria Jenn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaDQRBjDkO5Z85bXZSz7WCUJ4nqfhSQ3FIp-I7ug1id_pklzBY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Undeniably the food is delicious here BUT, the service is almost terrible; we lined up for almost 2 hrs to get inside & waited for the food for about 45mins. It's warm inside when we entered but they have a 2nd floor which is air conditioned. The restaurant is congested with diners that the service crew are having difficulty (they're trying) coping up with cleanliness & service issues of the place; the management should improve this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbEg7jFchnONgxz4wHfGGbLk_cflqWypDcjQzM"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Jorge Izar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI400Jf-AZO-pv3rWcVXqEMSRq4KLGZAiT6PqiKj9fD0JsXow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was good if you like a Filipino/Chinese restaurant. If you're looking for a straight-up Chinese restaurant, this isn't it, but it is pretty tasty. The Oyster Pancake is the best I've had in Binondo. I would highly recommend this place for your Filipino family members who aren't too adventurous about trying new things.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPppIBgNmug4v12hh2xvBshwdjL5rogP6FaQVuO"],"When":"2024-3-25"},{"Name":"Marc Zwillinger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYyJIsmHT9mCzIgZiMzfrretA8L1k16MoARlGdh4BPovHvjUQPyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Popular place. Separate lines for dine in vs take out, so check which line you're in. Ordered oyster sauce beef which was disappointing, pretty chewy not the best. Other dish was sweet and sour pork, better, deep fried but not crispy so could have been better. I'd suggest read the reviews and order the favorites .. chicken and a noodle dish next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKq20_IuAC5zjIHJbT_9FIQCfBqATDYGp1M2Zi"],"When":"2024-1-8"},{"Name":"JeiFer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJ-0fD8OgKIyNa3-162oggc6x7N1sVKX0dbFN4AWQp4cmW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We had the following:
Siomai - I love this! my fave from what we ordered today
Sate Beef Noodles - This was too salty for me. Probably best to pair with siopao? I don’t know 🤷‍♀️
Camto Mi - The soup was so good! Noodles was yum and there was generous serving of camto
Tortang Oyster - Serving was huge! My fave was the crispy edges. The oysters were not malansa. It was good esp if you like oyster omelette

Service: Straightforward and fast. No frills. Don’t expect the usual customer service.

Atmosphere: People come here for the food. Rated this 1 because of the super slippery floor esp at the ground floor (though i think it’s just because of my shoes) and there was a little cockroach that kept on crawling on our table. There are other outdated restaurants in the area but it’s the first time I saw cockroach. This dampened our appetite :( The place is just not clean","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEpSQKlZT1UUt2qgg3D2WQpaVOOcO5HewSY90"],"When":"2023-10-21"},{"Name":"Josh Mante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDmdqw32325UzweA3Hz97CNgzN7e_oMOFCYo2PCDMwblBzcOX5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This spot is a nostalgic haven, offering decent food at a reasonable price. While the taste matches the cost, there's room for improvement. Despite a seemingly low customer volume, ordering can be time-consuming. Also, note that parking is not available.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-4ptXc3RnHtAfYEHlFH-Tmfyz8rZAfT1yGpzm"],"When":"2023-11-14"},{"Name":"Richard A Francisco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKB3RUhFLtt7ImosmwoSu6nunMGPyPyAxwHXozmwk8SfivDzjhcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Considered to be a culinary institution for their chami (fried noodles) by the old school Filipino-Chinese community, Delicious does make delicious noodles as well as maki, fried chicken, oyster cake and other all-time Chinese favourites. Their prices are also inexpensive. They have an open air dining area at the street level and an air conditioner area upstairs","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTwYgLGD5PFrv1sD2z4_HdpZNhlSt_7sB2mdyC"],"When":"2023-8-24"},{"Name":"Rona Maye Trinidad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLBjTX-p7lRz2VAC3yIB3BMVgNPQApwkVITH3INi_N9EhZ9VA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time to try this famous restaurant in Binondo and found that the foods are reasonably priced. We ordered their chicken, pancit canton and beef mami. Servings were generous and I loved them all. However, the place is old and not properly maintained. I saw 2 small cockroaches in a nearby table as we ate.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMR4f9AW1XiiJTcg2rI3tvJexJPscUphp-olyUh"],"When":"2022-12-4"},{"Name":"Bonnu !","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJTs8u9U-TbS7lPH2HqNE4BsABMVN-om5KaRp4qGOeFal58tG_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"If we're ONLY talking about the food then it's definitely an 11/10. We loved it so much specially the fried rice BUT there are other things you should also consider.

Service is pretty below average, we waited for 34 minutes before we got our order. A staff member was also very unfriendly but I don't think all of them have an attitude like her. Moreover, the restrooms are in terrible shape.

Overall, I'll rate this restaurant a 7/10.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Mark Anthony Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVK4QcKEyM8hR8rQbSJTEurRuS8uluhy6BEHzZIOw1QWZYtBl_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jatujak Thai Restaurant at Mall of Asia is a true gem for anyone who loves authentic Thai cuisine. From the moment you step in, you’re transported to a cozy corner of Thailand with the restaurant’s warm and inviting ambiance. The decor is charming, blending traditional Thai elements with a modern touch, making it a perfect spot for a relaxed meal.

The menu is a delightful journey through the flavors of Thailand, offering a wide variety of dishes that cater to every palate. I was particularly impressed with the Tom Yum soup, which had the perfect balance of spice and tanginess. The Pad Thai was another highlight—perfectly cooked noodles with a wonderful mix of textures and flavors. The green curry was rich and creamy, with just the right amount of heat, and the portions were generous, leaving us fully satisfied.

The service at Jatujak was impeccable. The staff was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable, making sure we were comfortable and had everything we needed. They were quick to offer recommendations and were more than happy to accommodate any special requests we had. It was clear that they were passionate about providing a top-notch dining experience.

In addition to the amazing food and service, the prices are very reasonable, especially considering the quality and authenticity of the dishes. Jatujak offers great value for money, making it an ideal choice for both casual dining and special occasions.

Overall, Jatujak Thai Restaurant at Mall of Asia is a must-visit for anyone craving authentic Thai food in Manila. The delicious food, excellent service, and inviting atmosphere make it a five-star experience. I can’t wait to return and try more of their fantastic dishes!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3L091ZybNyjgz0UmW-A0QqwBQ9B9Dxsr8tGQs"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Mary Mayol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSlsGNfVexr7xK8sIuWHEWJUmj-iPZpZfMxKZ9TSOrxhnFKBU5yw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best Thai resto I've tried to date. Service was great. Their staffs are all inviting and courteous. Pretty much enjoyed everything we had. We tried their stir-fried noodles, tofu and Pad Thai. It was an unforgettable tease of flavors and textures with a bit of spice and crunch. Too bad I never had the chance to try their Mango sticky rice. Will definitely come back for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKdzIvEYqW9iAIJTsOPU8y4Uorw5_m9L1McEN7"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Abbie Dimaano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsxcaxJ1ZDd3qQ8ptMHrky5_ZcfCaCGFBwBEwdL81RqoknyD___w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Unbelievably good Thai food! We dined here and had a great meal. It was all delicious. Wishing they are in food delivery apps!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMznbf2X4bUHLSk-xHb6TVbM37uZwFxp2JNP3K"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Jad Kheirallah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiqfABQbqZOcFBs0yAmrvmXkraNeRDlmN12bmHIG5PgnOHgdgl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is next to the cinema on the facing corner above Sbarro Pizza. Good spot for Thai food. The service is swift, and the flavors are authentic.

You have a lot of options for sharing food, so make sure you are not alone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7VKrvAdA1zC2KhLclOKKiUkh9Kr9Rq7VLQvVC"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Sean Byrne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJlIHnhvF2z358v-HTP-c7gHw7B12E_VU7xPk5cJf2FrfjZ-V1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stumbled upon this eatery at the new back section of Mall of Asia and was pleasantly surprised by how good the food was. The servings are good to share and are served pretty quickly. There's a reasonable range of options on the menu and the staff are prompt and efficient. The pork skewers were really delicious and the spring rolls with glass noodles made a great appetiser, all accompanied by great sauces and condiments typical in Thai restaurants. Well worth a visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMme0Z8G2WSw_Zch0E7-Yyk8qxD2qIE0GxinTMp"],"When":"2024-2-7"},{"Name":"Jillė","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqnf3SJtqHcm_1N_RWEg7NMHzUg7tt3_lOCIcqB0vG6wA4qpe2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food tastes homey, and served hot. The quantity is great considering the price. It's a well ventilated area as well. Maybe even too cold.

The tom yum soup surprised me. It had so many shrimps! We adjusted the spice level on our own since there were seasonings provided on the table, but the taste itself wasn't lacking.

The beef red curry was on a sweet note. It complimented the taste of the shrimp fried rice.

The chicken cashews we ordered was flavorful, smokey and spicy.

Overall we had a pleasant experience in this restaurant. We do see ourselves coming back here because of the quality and quantity. Servers were attentive as well. Thank you","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzNMKjUag09zuR0u_Hft7Iu92DiQBRarAs-so"],"When":"2023-11-3"},{"Name":"Travel Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0hQWVxpujhKj9XLTKmsHfAorpN9wZWpzF0hbbn8qtR6ZukzBULA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Missed eating Thai food so we opted to have lunch at Jatujak Mall of Asia. It has been a long time since we last ate here. They have renovated their place and it looks nicer. We did not wait to be seated since it was a weekday. We ordered our favorite Thai dishes and they were all yummy. Craving satisfied!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5OTQ1ZNDsN23JZJK9SRqV_8Htdn84fBzfvdFZ"],"When":"2023-9-27"},{"Name":"Angelo Gabriel Caraon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXr9VpTW0OlL1BQZJMp12qeGAr9s0uuaK5zuP2yrqXF6qoItZnhQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our first time eating at this restaurant. We've had some good Thai food before but this resto prolly is one of the best.

The MOA branch people were very friendly. Didn't judge us as we ordered food good for about four people kahit dalawa lang kami lol. Waiting time was ok, a little slow but responded quickly after one follow up.

Green Papaya Salad
Very refreshing. Will definitely make you want to eat more. Sour, kinda sweet, a bit funky. And it has some heat. 4/5

Pad Kaprow
Wok fried basil and chili dish with crispy fried egg. We got the one that came with the crispy soft shell crab.

I am telling you now, I almost cried at how tasty this dish was. The fried basil with the sauce plus the crispy outside and soft and tender inside of the soft shell crab. I am salivating now as I write about this dish. Buy it, buy it now. 5/5

Pad See Iew
Stir fried flat noodles with dark soy sauce.

Soft, ample, well-seasoned noodles. The mouth feel is great. The noods were soft but still had enough chew in it. Perhaps one of the best noodle dishes I've ever had. 5/5

From The Grill
We had the Plamug Yang (squid) and Moo Yang (pork). Both were beautifully seasoned, tender, and came with a side of green papaya salad. Yum! 5/5

Adding this one to our usual rotation. I suggest you guys try it out too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM11qExbD5ZETuwVXKS6_6VL7eSEqIgVrWV11QH"],"When":"2024-2-25"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"pisceanrat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_Eg3RZfpsuT-mmOp9HEv4dX8iMDCGeq50c1TexwN7s0bUbmE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When I saw it while passing by, it looked so aesthetic! The waiter went outside to greet and assist us. Unfortunately they don't have any vegetarian dish  (only could replace the pork and shrimp into tofu for the made to order spring rolls but same price). He is very polite and even thanked us even though we didn't dine there that very moment.

But after a few minutes I returned as the other restos around were not my type.

The howling fish set in a small kaldero, with rice, veggie and meat soup and pickled veggies, is good for one. About Php 400++

The refreshing and yummy beef pho seems good for two. About Php 400

Spring roll was fresh, but dip too spicy.
Was first told it was ok, the pork and shrimp spring roll can be made into tofu and shrimp. But then after a while he returned saying it cannot be pala. Just tofu only, and remove both pork and shrimp for the same price.  Since lugi so I just said ok just make it into original (seems my switch made the kitchen staff annoyed). About php 300

The top of the rice in the small earthen pot was hard and crunchy  (tutong) which we are not a fan of.

Pros
Very courteous waiter.
Free wifi.
Nice Cr (separate male and female) with soap and tissue.
With second floor seating and VIP rooms.
Free hot tea.
Fast serving time.
Instagrammable especially the staircase.
Cute presentation in palayok.

Cons
With insects bothering us (small fruitfly and bangaw), one even managed to land on our drink huhu...
The chair had obviously seen better days - it was rocking.
No pets allowed.

Overall it may look expensive (with Service Charge) but it is justifiable.
